title: nancy's french toast(breakfast dish)
directions: Grease a heavy griddle or pan. In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs, cream, sugar, cinnamon, vanilla, salt and nutmeg together. Dip bread into egg mixture, coating both sides. Cook bread on griddle over medium heat for 2 to 3 minutes on each side or until golden brown. Serve warm with butter or margarine and warm syrup.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese, and place in a casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: moravian christmas cakes
directions: Add the sugar to the molasses and mix well.
Add lard and butter which has been melted and cooled.
Sift the spices and soda with a little flour and add the molasses mixture, stirring in well.
Then add the rest of the flour until you have a stiff dough.
Let stand overnight.
Roll very thin on a floured board; cut in shapes with cookie cutters and bake on greased tins in moderate oven at 350°.
This recipe makes about 6 pounds.

title: chicken tostada
directions: Mix together cabbage, tomato, onion, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Fry tortillas until crisp in hot oil.
Warm beans.
Add a little seasoned salt, if desired.
Spread 2 tablespoons of beans on tortillas, then add cabbage mixture.
Sprinkle diced chicken, cheese and avocado on top.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix chicken, celery, rice, cream of mushroom soup, mayonnaise and onion together and pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Top with mixture of cornflakes, melted butter and almonds.
Bake uncovered for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter refrigerator dessert
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar together.
Add peanut butter and milk.
Beat until creamy.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Turn into graham cracker crust in a pie pan or an 8 x 8-inch dish.
Refrigerate.

title: tomato and bell pepper salad
directions: Cut tomatoes into sixths or eighths; drain.
Seed peppers; cut into bite-size cubes.
Put tomatoes and peppers in a nonmetallic bowl.
In a separate bowl, combine olive oil, vegetable oil, vinegar, lime juice, cumin, salt, pepper and parsley.
Pour this mixture over tomatoes and peppers.
Let marinate in refrigerator several hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve chilled.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Dissolve gleatin in boiling water.
Drain oranges, reserving syrup and set aside.
Add water to reserved syrup to make 3/4 cup. Add to gelatin.
Blend in mayonnaise.
Chill until thick.
Fold in celery and oranges.
Spoon into 1-quart dish.
Chill until firm.
Serves 6.

title: rag pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers and tomatoes in salt water for 3 hours.
Drain. Boil all together 1 hour.
Can in pint jars while hot.
Process in water bath.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Fry sausage until slightly brown; add onions and cook until slightly browned.
Add water and cook 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes, zucchini and canned beans.
Simmer until zucchini are tender.
If too thick, add more water.
Serve on hot rice.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken breasts into 1-inch pieces.
Dip in melted butter. Roll in seasoned corn flake crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: chipped ham barbecue
directions: Bring to a boil catsup, water, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, brown sugar, dry mustard and celery seed.
Add 2 pounds chipped ham, cut into strips.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: breakfast hot pockets
directions: Separate the biscuits and roll them to twice the normal size. Scramble the eggs with any of the fillings that you like or use your own.
Place in the middle of the biscuit and fold in half; seal it tight.
Make 2 or 3 slits in the top for steam vents. Cook according to the package.
When these are cooled, they can be frozen for later use.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Sift together the sugar, flour, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Add eggs, milk, vanilla and syrup.
Bake in a greased cake pan or iron skillet.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Combine blackberries, margarine and sugar in saucepan and heat until margarine melts.

title: corn bread taco bake
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Pour into 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Prepare corn muffin mix according to package directions, except add 1/2 can of onions.
Spoon around outer edge of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes. Top corn bread with cheese and remaining onions.

title: buttermilk pie(makes 2 pies.)
directions: Mix ingredients. Pour into crusts. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: lo-salt, lo-fat barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together in saucepan.
Simmer stirring occasionally 10 to 15 minutes.

title: homemade turkey sausage* * * * *
directions: Slices are more attractive than melon balls when served with the stuffed tomatoes.
They compliment the round shape of the tomatoes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Chill all fruit; mix.
Add cooked dressing, mayonnaise or whipped cream.
Serve on crisp lettuce leaves.

title: bourbon pound cake
directions: Combine raisins, fruits and bourbon in a medium size bowl. Let soak several hours or overnight.
Grease and flour a 10-inch angel cake tube pan.
Sift flour, baking powder and nutmeg onto wax paper.
Beat butter and sugar in a large bowl with electric mixer until smooth.
Beat in eggs until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour mixture alternately with milk, beating until smooth after each addition.
Stir in fruits, bourbon and nuts.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Put cucumbers in salt and lime to carry an egg.
Let stand 5 days.
Drain and soak 2 days in clear water, then cut up in sticks.
Cover with boiling water.
Let stand until cool.
Drain. Boil the remaining ingredients a short time and pour over pickles. Do not heat pickles.
Re-boil this syrup for 3 mornings and pour back over the pickles.
At third heating, pack pickles in jars and pour over hot syrup.
Seal.
A crisp pickle.

title: pasta with shrimp and artichoke hearts
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons oil in large skillet.
Add shrimp and 1 teaspoon garlic.
Cook over medium heat 3 to 5 minutes, stirring often until shrimp becomes opaque.
Remove shrimp with slotted spoon and set aside in bowl.
Add remaining garlic, salt, pepper and chicken broth to skillet.
Bring to a boil and cook 3 to 5 minutes to reduce liquid slightly.
Stir in artichoke hearts and tomatoes.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes, until tender.
Add shrimp mixture and cook about 2 minutes, until hot and shrimp are no longer transparent in center.
Remove from heat; stir in parsley and butter.
Pour over hot pasta and toss.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Bake in 350° oven for 12 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake 1 hour and 25 minutes at 350°. Grease and flour loaf pans before you add mixture to bake.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: grandma's old fashion caramel corn
directions: Mix all ingredients in medium pot over the stove; bring to a boil. Let it boil for about 1 minute. Then pour into popcorn and stir it up.

title: cookie cream pie - baked chocolate pie shell
directions: Pour half and half into large bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat at low speed until well blended, about 1 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip and crushed cookies.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Freeze about 6 hours.
Remove and let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Slice eggplant in
half
lengthwise
and
sprinkle well with salt.
Let stand for about	an hour.
In a skillet over a medium flame, put in oil
and
brown
the	onion,	garlic	and parsley flakes.
Add tomatoes and rest of ingredients; continue cooking for about
10 to 15 minutes.
Add a little water if needed to keep juicy.
Remove skillet from heat.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter together; add remaining ingredients.
Mix well; spread in dish.
Cut when hardened.

title: lumpia
directions: Mix altogether (except wrappers).
Refrigerate for 1 hour. Beat together 1 egg and 2 teaspoons water.
Spoon mixture onto egg roll wrapper and dampen edges with egg and water mixture.
Roll up and deep fry.

title: almond mayonnaise
directions: Whiz almonds in hot water until smooth, approximately 2 minutes.
Add cold water, lemon juice, dates and salt.
Whiz until smooth and creamy.
Measure Clear Jell and have ready to add as quickly as possible while blender is running at high speed.
Yield: 1 quart.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Line casserole dish with tortillas that have been dipped in hot oil.
Add meat mixture that has been cooked until redness is gone and onion is clear.
Add in layers Ranch beans, chicken soup, enchilada sauce, cheese, tortillas, stewed tomatoes and green chili peppers.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° until cheese is melted and casserole is bubbly on top.

title: becky's tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package and drain.
Mix cheese packet with macaroni.
Combine with all ingredients remaining and pour into a covered buttered casserole dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Cook cake mix as directed.
While hot, punch holes in cake. Pour butterscotch caramel topping over.
Let cool.
Put Cool Whip on cake and crush candy bars and sprinkle over top.
Refrigerate.

title: baked carrots and apples
directions: Cook carrots in boiling, salted water until tender (12 to 15 minutes).
Combine drained carrots and apples and put in 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle sugar on top and dot with margarine.
Dash with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix jello per pkg directions and let set slightly.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Put in refrigerator till set.
For decoration you can top with maraschino cherries (halved).
This salad keeps well.

title: strawberry banana salad
directions: Boil 2 cups of water; mix with jello.
Add frozen strawberries; mix.
Add pineapple and bananas.
Pour half of mixture in dish; let set in refrigerator.
When it is ready, spread the sour cream on top.
Add the rest of the jello mixture and let set.

title: potato pork chop bake
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add pork chops and cook until browned.
Drain on paper towel.
Preheat oven to 350°. In a medium bowl mix soup, milk, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Stir in potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 cup onions.
Mix together and spread in the bottom of a 9x13-inch baking dish.
Arrange pork chops over potato mixture.
Cover dish and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover, top with remaining cheese and onions and bake uncovered for 5 more minutes.

title: beef cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Shape into ball and chill.

title: gallagher's beer cheese soup
directions: Combine milk, beer and cheese spread in a medium saucepan. Stir in bacon.
Combine flour and butter; form into a ball.
Add butter mixture to warm milk mixture.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until butter mixture dissolves and soup is thickened. Season with salt and serve.
Makes 6 1/2 cups.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Brown meats; add seasonings and cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
Put in Baggies and use as many as you want.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cheese apples
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: norwegian nut bars
directions: Cream butter, add sugar and mix well.
Combine flour and wheat germ.
Add to butter and sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Turn into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press even.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Remove from oven and let stand 5 minutes before adding topping.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together with mixer and serve with raw vegetables.

title: cracker jax
directions: Put popped corn and nuts in a greased pan.
In a medium pan melt butter.
Add the brown sugar, salt and syrup.
Bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add the baking soda and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn and stir with a wooden spoon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes.
Pour on waxed paper and let cool.

title: easy dessert
directions: Place a layer of one kind of fruit in an ungreased cake pan; sprinkle box of dry cake mix on top of fruit.
Pour melted butter or oleo over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm; top with whipped cream or ice cream if desired.

title: old fashioned cream-style corn
directions: Cook frozen corn according to directions and drain.
Put in skillet and add oleo, 3/4 can milk and sugar.
Mix 2 tablespoons flour with remainder of canned milk.
Can add a little water to thin.
Stir into corn mixture and cook until thick.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cut potatoes into cubes and parboil just enough so a knife can go through.
Combine potatoes, mayo and onions; cut cheese into strips and add to potato mixture.
Put in 9 x 11-inch baking dish and cover with bacon.
Bake 1 hour uncovered at 325°.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Whip whipping cream.
Combine buttermilk and pudding.
Add to whip cream.
Stir in fruits.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Stir boiling water and gelatin in large bowl for 2 minutes. Stir in cool water.
Stir in ice cream until almost smooth. Pour into serving bowl.
Refrigerate for 3 hours or until firm. Garnish with Cool Whip, fruit and nuts.

title: hash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place into greased casserole dish.
Cover and bake in oven (375°) for 1 hour.
Remove cover and cook for additional 15 minutes.

title: sweet pickles from dills
directions: Drain original juice from dills; place in plastic container with lid.
Cut 2 gloves garlic in half; lay on top of pickles. Pour sugar on top of pickles, then pour vinegar over sugar.
Seal and place in refrigerator 3 to 4 days before using.
Stir after 2nd day daily.

title: chili sauce
directions: Boil 2 1/2 hours.
Pour into sterilized jars.

title: spanish delight
directions: Heat oven to 350.° Heat oil, add onion, and green peppers, cook until tender. Add ground beef, tomato paste, mushrooms,

cream style corn, and chili sauce. Salt and pepper to taste. Cook 8 (oz.) pkg. of noodles, drain and give cold water bath. Add mixture to noodles. Put in casserole dish. Sprinkle with 1 lb. cheddar cheese. Bake for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: tasty oyster stuffing(for 12 pound turkey)
directions: Break up bread into small pieces and add mushroom juice.
Dice oysters, mushrooms and celery.
Mix all ingredients with bread; add boiling water to desired moistness and stuff.

title: jalapeno squares
directions: Layer cheese and peppers in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat together and add Pet milk, eggs, Tabasco and flour.
Pour over cheeses. Heat at 350° for 25 minutes or until mixture bubbles.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour in 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sugar and spice cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and molasses; blend well.
Sift together next 6 ingredients.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Form balls, using 1 teaspoon dough.
Roll in sugar and place about 2-inches apart on a greased baking sheet. Bake 10 minutes or until golden brown at 375°.
Place a red cinnamon candy in middle of each cookie.
Yield: 3 dozen.

title: bourbon slush
directions: Add tea bags to boiling water.
Steep 20 minutes.
Mix together with remaining ingredients and freeze solid.

title: chuck wagon beans(club member: mindy daniels)
directions: Boil beans until tender; add chili powder. Add chopped onion and hamburger meat. Bring to boil again; simmer for about 20 minutes. Good served with rice. May substitute 1 large can Ranch Style beans or add bell pepper if desired.

title: yum-yum salad
directions: Cook pineapple and sugar over low heat until sugar dissolves. Mix Jell-O with boiling water; add pineapple mixture.
When Jell-O is partially set, mix in cheese and Cool Whip.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and Milnot to soft ball stage.
Set off heat and add vanilla and peanut butter.
Don't beat too long.
Pour and mark.

title: french fried eggplant
directions: Peel the eggplant.
Dip in the seasoned flour and fry in hot oil for 1 minute or until golden brown. Drain on paper towels and serve. These may also be fried in butter and sprinkled with oregano and Parmesan cheese.

title: "kim-she"
directions: Melt margarine and garlic salt; add pork strips and saute. Add vegetable mix and cook on medium heat for 20 minutes.
Then simmer until vegies are tender.
Serve over rice.

title: hawaiian pineapple pie
directions: Combine milk and lemon juice on low speed of mixer.
Drain pineapple and to milk.
Add Cool Whip and nuts.
Pour into pie crust and chill several hours.
Store in refrigerator.

title: sauerkraut salad(serves 6)
directions: Mix and pour over other ingredients. Let set several hours in refrigerator.

title: chicken bombay
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
On a sheet of waxed paper, mix together the spices.
Roll chicken in spices.
In skillet, melt butter. Add chicken and broth.
Sprinkle with garlic and onions.
Cover tightly and simmer about 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Put rice in pan with 1/4 cup oil and brown slightly; add tomato juice and all spices, hamburger and onion.
Simmer for 1 hour, then add olives and stir.
Grate cheese on top.
Bake in pan of water at 350° for an additional hour.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar with electric beater at high speed for 5 minutes or until sugar is dissolved. Add oil, flour, cinnamon, soda and salt;
beat at medium speed until well mixed.
Mix in apples and nuts. Batter will be thick.
Spread in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool in pan. Cut in squares and sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: pumpkin casserole
directions: Melt margarine in glass loaf dish.
Combine the other ingredients together and pour into loaf pan.
Mix 1 teaspoon sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Very good with ham or turkey.

title: jello de "light"
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in apple and pineapple. Add diet Mountain Dew.
Let chill.
Serve alone, with Cool Whip or over angel food cake.
Great refresher!

title: erin's snow white frosting
directions: Combine sugar, 1/2 cup water, cream of tartar and salt in a 2-cup glass measure.
Cook on 70 (Roast) for 4 to 5 minutes or until mixture boils.

title: french pastry
directions: Cut the flour, salt, sugar and Crisco all together.
Pour beaten egg over top of mixture.
Add vinegar to cold water.
Add the liquid, 1 teaspoon at a time.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 425°. Makes 4 crusts.

title: joe klein's favorite taffy apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Mix flour, sugar, pineapple juice, egg and vinegar in a small pan.
Stir over medium heat until thick.
Refrigerate mixture until cool.
Fold Cool Whip, fruit and half the nuts into cooled mixture.
Sprinkle the other half of nuts over top.

title: john's appetizer
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and salsa together.
Top with shredded lettuce and other fresh veggies of your choice.
Top with shredded cheese.
Serve with dipping chips.

title: easy taco salad
directions: Layer lettuce, tortilla or nacho chips and ground beef.
Mix tomatoes, black olives and Cheddar cheese.
Layer in bowl or glass baking dish.
Then pour salsa over.
Let set 1 hour in refrigerator.
Serve as is or can toss lightly.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla. Combine dry ingredients.
Stir.
Pour into greased baking pans. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: zucchini pie(mock apple)
directions: Peel zucchini; cut lengthwise in half.
Remove seeds.
Cut into large chunks as you would cut apples.
There should be 8 cups.
Put in large saucepan; add lemon juice.
Cook over low heat until crisp-tender but not soft.
Stir in sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg; simmer only until sugar dissolves.
Cool; stir in flour. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until crust is golden.
Cool on wire rack.
Serve warm.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken or ribs
directions: Cook first 8 ingredients for 10 minutes.
Add ketchup.
Cook for another 10 minutes.
Makes 1 quart.

title: pineapple-zucchini bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until thick.
Stir in zucchini, pineapple, flour, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, raisins and nuts.
Blend well.
Pour into two 5 x 9-inch greased loaf pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Saute pepper and onion in butter.
Put eggs, milk and seasonings in a bowl and mix.
Add the meat, cheese, flour, baking powder, pepper and onion.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into pie shells.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: black forest pie
directions: Melt chocolate in condensed milk in heavy saucepan over medium-low heat.
Remove from heat and stir in almond extract. Pour into large bowl.
Cool or chill.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in whipped cream and pour into pastry shell.
Chill 4
hours or until set.

title: apple-raisin slaw
directions: Sprinkle lemon juice over coarsely diced apples and stir well. Mix in raisins and shredded cabbage.
Add mayonnaise and season to taste.
Toss and serve at once.
Makes 8 servings.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook lasagna as directed.
Brown meat and chill.
Mix Ricotta, parsley, nutmeg, cinnamon and eggs.

title: berry pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in medium bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups whipped topping. Spread evenly in bottom of crust.
Press strawberry halves into cream cheese layer, reserving several for garnish.
Pour 2 cups milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat with wire whisk 1 minute.
Let stand 1 minute or until thickened.
Gently stir in 1 cup of whipped topping.
Spoon over strawberries in crust. Refrigerate 4 hours or until set.
Garnish with remaining whipped topping and reserved strawberries.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cookies and cream
directions: Variation (Call it Dirt!):
Substitute chocolate pudding for the vanilla.
Top with gummy bugs or worms.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Soak oats in sour milk for 1 hour.
Mix shortening, brown sugar and egg together.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Stir in alternately with oats and milk.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and butter.
Bring to a boil over low heat.
Pour hot syrup over beaten eggs.
Let cool.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 300° for 35 to 40 minutes longer.

title: shawn's shrimp scampi
directions: Steam shrimp in beer.
Melt butter in frying pan; add garlic and half of lemon juice.
Put steamed
shrimp in mixture of butter, garlic and lemon and simmer for 5 minutes.
Transfer to baking dish.
Add remaining lemon juice and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until brown, then serve with lemon wedges.

title: cottage cheese-cool whip salad
directions: Mix dry jello with cottage cheese.
Add drained fruits and Cool Whip.
Mix well and refrigerate for 30 minutes before serving.
Keeps for a week in refrigerator if covered tightly.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until very creamy.
Add one egg at a time; mix well.
Blend in flour, salt, baking powder, and enough milk to moisten.
Add flavorings.
Pour into well-greased tube pan and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: banana-oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugar, butter and shortening.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with bananas.
Add oatmeal and if desired, the nuts.
One cup chocolate chips may also be added. Drop on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: dutch fluffy pancakes
directions: Mix eggs, milk and flour until smooth.
Pour melted butter into pie plate, then pour egg mixture into pan and top with a bit of nutmeg.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Top with favorite toppings from fresh fruit to syrups

title: angel biscuits or rolls
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in Crisco.
Dissolve yeast in 5 tablespoons warm water.
When dissolved, add to buttermilk.
Stir yeast and buttermilk into the dry ingredients.
Knead thoroughly and store in plastic bag in refrigerator.
Take out as needed.

title: blueberry-banana muffins(sugar-free)
directions: Beat together banana and egg until creamy.
Add milk and oil; beat well.
Gently mix in blueberries.
Spoon batter into oiled and lightly floured muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Serves 12.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Blend the first 4 ingredients together to make dressing.

title: chunky potato soup
directions: Melt butter; add flour until smooth and cook 1 minute. Gradually add milk. Stir in potatoes, onions, salt and pepper. Cook on medium, stirring frequently until thick and potatoes are done. Serve with shredded cheese, bacon and French bread.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the sugar, oleo and eggs. Add bananas, flour, baking powder, soda and buttermilk. Grease bread pans (2 large or 3 small).
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: Break lettuce in small pieces in bottom of a 9 x 12-inch Pyrex pan.
Put celery, pepper and water chestnuts on lettuce.
Cover this with onion slices.
Spread mayonnaise and then put the bacon on this.
Cover with the cheese.
Can be made a day ahead.

title: autumn pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine eggs, oil and water in a large bowl. Add salt, cinnamon, vanilla and sugar; beat well on low speed. Add pumpkin; mix well. Mix flour with baking soda and stir into batter. Fold in nuts and raisins. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake 1 hour. Cool in pans or on wire racks.

title: low-fat pasta
directions: Prepare pasta as per package directions.
Heat soup, 1/2 can of water and chopped mushrooms (amount determined by your taste). Salt and pepper to taste.
Drain pasta and mix into heated soup mixture.
Serve warm.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix and bake 45 minutes.

title: pecan delights
directions: Place sugar and egg whites on slow heat and heat until warm. Remove from heat and continue beating until mixture stands firm. Fold in chopped pecans.
Drop batter by teaspoon and bake on lightly greased cookie sheet at 325° for about 12 minutes or until firm.

title: squash puppies
directions: Mix and deep fry.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Place drained asparagus in bottom of casserole dish, then put the cheese slices on top of asparagus (spread evenly).
Spoon soup on top; do not stir.
Add crushed crackers on top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Heat over to 350 degrees.
Stir together flour, granulated sugar, 2 Tbsp. cocoa, baking powder, and salt.
Mix well.
Add milk, oil and vanilla with a fork until smooth.
Stir in nuts. Spread evenly in a 9 X 9 inch ungreased pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and 1/4 c. cocoa.
Pour hot water over batter.
Bake 40 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Cut into squares.
There will be a thick chocolate sauce underneath the cake when you take it out. Top each square with ice cream and spoon sauce over it.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan; add peaches and syrup to melted butter.
Combine remaining ingredients, pour over peaches and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm with cream.
Yields 12 servings.

title: fruit punch for 35
directions: Mix well.
Freeze
some
mix to keep punch cool without diluting.
(Freeze in tube pan.) Add 2 quarts ginger ale.

title: choc-oat-chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat together margarine and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add combined flour, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in oats, chocolate morsels and nuts; mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes.

title: crispy potato skins
directions: Wash potatoes, dry and prick with a fork.
Bake at 425° for 50 to 60 minutes, until soft.
Cool potatoes slightly; cut into quarters (wedge-shaped) and scrape out almost all pulp.
Place, skin side down, on baking sheet.
Brush with melted butter.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Return to oven and bake 10 minutes longer or until crispy.
Makes 16 wedges.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef; add remaining ingredients and simmer 30 minutes. Serve hot.

title: chocolate popcorn(hunky-dory: norweigan)
directions: To cover larger batch of popcorn, double amount of ingredients.

title: cashew chicken salad
directions: In a bowl, combine all ingredients except nuts and lettuce. Mix thoroughly. Add cashews and toss lightly.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Serve on lettuce leaves, if desired.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Simmer syrup
and
margarine in a 10-inch skillet for 2 minutes.
Add
carrots.
Cook
for 10 minutes or until carrots are glazed, stirring frequently.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: mini apple nut loaves
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
In a large bowl, cream the shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat until well blended.
Stir in half the flour mixture.
Mix in apples, evaporated milk and walnuts.
Add remaining flour mixture; blend well.
Grease 6 miniature loaf pans (approximately 4 x 2-inches) and line bottoms with waxed paper.
Pour into small pans, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until tops spring back when lightly touched.
Remove warm loaves from pans.
Peel off waxed paper.
Allow to cool on rack.
Makes 6 (4 x 2-inch) loaves.

title: cranberry-apple punch
directions: Mix well.
Chill.
Pour over frozen punch molds and decorate with lemon slices.
Serves 60.

title: lemon softies
directions: Mix together and make into small balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Place 1 1/2 inches apart on cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Remove from cookie sheet and cool.
Do not overcook or they will get too hard.

title: fruit bowl supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Chill one hour.

title: teriyaki sticks
directions: Combine all ingredients, except steak.
Cut steak across the grain into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Thread each slice onto a bamboo skewer and place in a container.
Pour marinade over meat. Marinate overnight, turning occasionally.
Place skewers on grill; cook 3 to 4 minutes on each side.

title: peanut butter cookies(diabetic)
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add softened butter, vanilla, peanut butter and Sucaryl and blend thoroughly.
Add enough water to hold together.
Form into a roll and wrap in wax paper and chill.
When thoroughly chilled, slice and bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: bob's cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Top with blueberry sauce.

title: chocolate covered cherry cookies
directions: Combine butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Shape into 1/2 to 1-inch balls.
Place cherry into indented center.
Cover cherry with chocolate topping.
Melt one 6-ounce bag chocolate chips.
Add 1/2 cup condensed milk plus 4 teaspoons of cherry juice.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in punch bowl.
Add frozen fruit ring or spoonfuls of sherbet.

title: italian love cake
directions: Mix cake and put in 13 x 9 x 2-inch ungreased pan.
(Mix cake according to package.)
Mix cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla until blended and pour over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes. Mix instant pudding and milk and fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on cake after cooled, then refrigerate.

title: creamy green onion spread
directions: In small bowl, beat cream cheese and milk until smooth.
Stir in chopped onions.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: sliced cucumber pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onion, celery and salt.
Let stand 1 hour, do not drain.
Add sugar, vinegar, mustard seed and celery seed. Will keep up to three months in refrigerator.

title: out of this world cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well by hand.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not preheat oven.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Grease dish.
Place bacon in bottom of dish.
Put rice on bacon and chicken on rice.
Mix water, soup and spices.
Pour over rice and chicken.
Bake at 350° for about 2 hours.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Coat 12 muffin pan cups with vegetable cooking spray.
Combine both flours, baking powder, cinnamon and salt in large bowl.
Whisk milk, sugar, oil and egg whites in bowl until blended.
Stir in zucchini.
Stir milk mixture into dry ingredients just until moistened.
Spoon into muffin cups.
Bake 18 to 22 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center of a muffin comes out clean.
Makes one dozen.

title: lemon kissed chicken
directions: Dip chicken pieces into beaten egg and milk mixture.
Coat with cornmeal and place pieces into ungreased baking pan.
Pour lemon juice and margarine which have been heated together over chicken.
Season with salt and pepper.
Top with sliced onion rings.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° without turning.

title: pork fried rice
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons of oil to 375° in wok. Scramble beaten eggs. Remove. Set aside. Heat 2 tablespoons oil to 400° in wok. Stir-fry rice, breaking up lumps by pressing rice against the pan and stirring quickly and consistency. Add salt, soy sauce, peas and carrots, pork, scallions and scrambled eggs. Stir-fry to heat thoroughly.

title: fruit salad
directions: Place drained fruit in large bowl.
Mix pudding mix with 1 cup drained fruit juices.
Blend with fruit and refrigerate.
Kiwi fruit may be sliced and added as a garnish.

title: finger gelatin
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Set aside.
Dissolve unflavored gelatin into cold water.
Stir the two mixtures together, stirring well.
Add the lemon juice.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate to set.

title: microwave spicy cheese dip
directions: Brown meat and drain; set aside.
Cut cheese into cubes. Place cheese and tomatoes in covered casserole dish for 10 to 12 minutes on Medium power of microwave until cheese is melted.
Add meat and serve.

title: southern salad
directions: Cook peas according to directions on package; drain and cool. Add celery, tomatoes and French dressing.
Toss lightly and serve on watercress or lettuce with a garnish of onion rings.
Serves 4.

title: hawaiian kisses
directions: Beat sugar and margarine at medium speed until well blended. Blend in vanilla and salt.
Reduce speed to low.
Add flour; beat until well blended.
Shape dough into small balls.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Place on baking sheet; press thumb in the middle. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until edges are brown.
Spoon cream cheese into indentation.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown beef with onion until tender.
Drain.
Blend in mushroom soup and sour cream.
Add broth, water and noodles.
Bring to a boil, cover and cook over low heat for 10 minutes or until noodles are done.
Stir often.

title: bisquick sausage balls
directions: Mix and form into balls.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: raisin pie
directions: Pour some boiling water over raisins.
Let set 20 minutes. Drain.
Beat egg yolks with a fork in sugar.
Mix all other ingredients.
Last, fold in slightly beaten egg white.
Pour into shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese crisps
directions: Mix all ingredients together and knead until smooth.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter or pinch into balls and then flatten. Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: spicy cabbage, beef and rice
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven, cook beef over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, until meat loses its pink color, 5 to 7 minutes.
Drain off any fat.
Add sausage and rice.
Cook, stirring, until rice turns translucent, about 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir in green pepper and onion and cool 1 minute.
Stir in water, tomatoes with their liquid, salt and cayenne.
Heat to boiling. Spread cabbage over meat mixture. Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir cabbage down into dish and cook 5 minutes longer or until rice is tender.

title: english sweet mustard sauce(this is a wonderful mustard sauce for ham or other meats!)
directions: Melt butter in a heavy pan.
Add flour and soup stock.
Cook until thick.
Add other ingredients slowly.
Remove from heat and cool.
Sauce can be kept in fridge or freezer.
Serve either warm or cool.
Great on sandwiches.

title: "watch u call it" casserole
directions: Drain all ingredients.
Mix all ingredients, except the onion rings,
together.
Place
in casserole and top with the French fried onion rings.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese straws #2
directions: Cream all ingredients together and press through cookie press. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: southwestern baked corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Grease a 2-quart casserole. Combine all ingredients in the order given and pour into prepared casserole. Bake for 45 minutes at 375°. Lower temperature to 325° and bake for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: easy oven potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place margarine, oil and Mrs. Dash in a 13 x 9 baking dish and let margarine melt.
Add potatoes and stir.
Bake about 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook ingredients slowly for 30 minutes.
Put in hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: sweet potato pie(first place winner, 1980)
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon, allspice, mace, and salt.
Stir in sweet potatoes.
Combine eggs, milk, and melted shortening.
Add to sweet potato mixture.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in a hot oven (400°) about 40 minutes, or until the filling is set.
Makes one nine inch pie.

title: green beans and new potatoes
directions: Prepare beans and place in Dutch oven.
Cut bacon into large cubes and add to green beans.
Cover with water.
Cook until water is almost cooked away.
Add onion and potatoes; cook until potatoes are tender.
More water can be added at this point, if needed.
Continue cooking on low heat.
Add salt and pepper; cook until water is almost completely reduced, being careful not to burn.
Serve.

title: hawaiian bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into two (8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch) loaf pans and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot olive appetizer
directions: Spread mixture on very thin bread.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Cut into quarters.

title: ricotta cheese cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add eggs and cheese and mix well.
Add vanilla, salt, flour and baking soda.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.

title: bill's pancakes
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, sugar and salt; add egg yolks, milk and oil together.
Add to flour mixture.
Mix to moisten. Beat and fold in 2 stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake on lightly greased griddle or 375° electric skillet.
Turn only once, when bubbles appear and break over top and around edges.

title: broccoli and corn bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients, except bread crumbs and butter.
Add to a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs and butter.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: ahwahnee tenderloin tips
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Blend in flour; gradually stir in bouillon.
Add bay leaf and cloves.
Heat, stirring constantly, to boiling.
Simmer 2 minutes; remove spices.
Brown meat in hot oil; season with salt and pepper.
Add green pepper; cook until tender. Cook mushrooms until tender in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add bouillon mixture, lemon juice and tenderloin strips.
Heat to boiling.
Trim with pimento strips if desired.
Serve over rice.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Line 9 x 13-inch greased pan with broccoli.
Mix rice with onions.
Mix rice, onions and cheese. Put over broccoli.
Pour soup over rice.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: decadent french toast
directions: Cook first three ingreadients until syrupy and pour into greased 9 x 12 inch baking dish.
Top with bread slices.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix ingredients in a bowl.
Shape mixture into about 24 balls. Put on a plate and serve.

title: chili
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in 1 tablespoon butter or margarine.
Brown meat and drain.
Mix all ingredients in large pot, bring to a boil and let simmer at
least 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pork and vegetable stir-fry
directions: Partially freeze pork; slice thinly into bite-size strips. Stir together soy sauce, cornstarch, and ginger; set mixture aside.

title: orange salad
directions: Combine all dry ingredients with 1 1/2 cups water in saucepan; boil 1 minute.
Mix fruit and mix together in bowl.
Chill 24 hours.
Add 1 large container Cool Whip.
Mix and serve.

title: baked mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until tender; drain.
Place in a large bowl. Add milk, salt and 1 tablespoon butter; beat until light and fluffy.
Fold in egg, sour cream, cottage cheese and onions. Place in a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.

title: endive soup with chicken broth
directions: Use 1 whole chicken.
Cover with water.
Cook approximately 1 hour on medium heat (until fat globules appear on surface).
Remove chicken; cut or pull into small pieces.
Add parsley, basil, onion, garlic, salt and pepper to soup.
Take crushed clean endive and cut into small pieces (diced).
Cook into soup on simmer with chicken pieces.
Beat eggs and cheese.
Add to simmering soup, stirring in egg mixture gradually (1 1/2 minutes).
Serve with Rose wine in soup (optional).

title: spinach roll-ups
directions: Defrost and drain spinach; chop with knife and make sure it's patted dry.
Mix all other ingredients together and add spinach and spread evenly over shells.
Roll up and refrigerate overnight in covered container.
Cut into 1-inch slices.

title: pork tenderloin with sauce
directions: Step 1:
Melt 1/4 cup margarine in heavy skillet.
Saute onion and carrots until tender, remove with a slotted spoon and save for later.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Bake for about 45 minutes to 1 hour to 350°.

title: cherry nugget pie
directions: Mix together condensed milk and lemon juice.
Add cherries, nuts and whipped cream.
Fold into mixtures; pour in vanilla wafer crusts.
Put in hot oven for 3 minutes, then refrigerate for at least 6 hours.
Makes 2 pies.

title: raw cranberry salad
directions: Grind or use blender for all ingredients, except pineapple juice and strawberry jello.
Heat pineapple juice and add jello. Once jello is dissolved, add remaining ingredients.
Can refrigerate or freeze.

title: oatmeal-raisin cookies
directions: Cream together the sugars and butter.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until smooth.
In another bowl, mix rest of ingredients, including the raisins.
Add the dry mixture, a little at a time, to the butter mixture, until all is blended.
Roll dough into small balls and put on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Salt and pepper the chicken pieces. Then rub chicken with mayonnaise.
Place 1 cup of raw rice in bottom of a 2-quart casserole dish.
Then place chicken pieces on top of rice.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix flour, butter and brown sugar with tips of fingers until thoroughly blended.
Add cornflakes and mix well.
Peel and slice apples into buttered baking dish, 10 x 6 x 2-inch.
Pack firmly. Sprinkle with lemon juice and top with cornflake mixture.
Bake in a moderately hot oven (375°) for 30 minutes or until apples are tender.
Serve warm or cold with cream.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: mom's vinegar pie
directions: Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: chocolate candy
directions: Melt the chocolate and butterscotch chips.
Mix nuts into melted chocolate and then drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Add water, salad dressing and vanilla.
Mix together and bake at 325° to 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Put potatoes in bottom of 2 1/2 quart baking dish.
Over potatoes, layer butter, onion, beans, rice, green pepper, tomatoes and ground beef.
Season with salt and pepper; cover evenly with soup.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are done.
If it starts to get too brown, cover with foil the last 30 minutes.

title: onion beef stroganoff
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, cook beef in oil until no longer pink.
Stir in soup mix, potato soup, milk and mushrooms.
Cover and simmer for 35 to 40 minutes or until meat is tender.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken until tender and cut in pieces.
Save broth. Saute onion in margarine; add soup and chicken.
Cook spaghetti in broth and add to chicken mixture.
Place in large dish, sprinkle with cheese and bake until hot and cheese is melted.
Add a little broth, if needed.

title: party eggnog
directions: Beat cream thick and combine with sugar and egg yolks which have been beaten together, then add the brandy (quantity may be increased or decreased to suit taste) and stiffly beaten whites of eggs.
It may require more sugar according to taste.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Keep cool until served for 8.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Brown stew meat well; drain fat.
Coat meat in flour.
Add wine.
Cook over low heat 1 hour.
Add carrots, onion and mushrooms.
Cook 2 1/2 hours on medium heat.
This should be loose, not runny, if thickens too much, add a little water for right consistency.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: squash dressing casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except eggs.
Add eggs last. Bake in casserole at 350° until brown.

title: oven french toast
directions: Dip bread slices and place on greased baking sheet.
Bake in hot oven at 500° for 10 minutes or until browned.

title: oven ranch potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes approximately 5 to 7 minutes, just until tender (do not overcook).
Drain and place in a baking dish.

title: turkey roll-ups
directions: Cook stuffing mix according to directions on box.
Cool stuffing.
When cool, place 1 thin slice of turkey breast and spoon in a tablespoon of stuffing.
Roll up.
Continue doing until all turkey breast is rolled up.

title: sure-jell pepper jelly
directions: Finely chop seeded peppers in food processor; do not puree!

title: dinner rolls
directions: Heat butter, sugar and cream slowly until butter is melted. Then cool. Soak yeast, warm water and 4 teaspoons sugar until it foams a little.
Then add butter mixture, beaten eggs, salt and a little yellow cake color (if you prefer) to yeast and water.
Add enough flour just so you can handle them.
Pour a little vegetable oil over dough when you are done.
Let raise 2 times.
Use a little oil to make dinner rolls.
This can also be used for cinnamon rolls.

title: green beans supreme
directions: Boil beans 4 to 5 minutes.
Mix sugar, soy sauce and sesame oil; set aside.
Heat pan with peanut oil; then add garlic.
Add pepper and green beans to oil and garlic.
Heat until brown.
Then add sugar, soy sauce and sesame mixture to pan.
Soak.

title: classic hollandaise sauce
directions: In small saucepan, stir egg yolks, half the butter and juice from lemon; stir briskly with wooden spoon.
Stir over very low heat until butter is melted.
Add remaining butter, stirring briskly, until butter is melted and sauce thickens.
Serve hot or at room temperature.

title: lemonade
directions: Squeeze lemon juice from lemons into pitcher.
Add sugar and water.
Stir.
Add lemons, if desired.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: mom's old fashioned molasses stack cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add lemon extract and blend.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Add molasses, blending well.
(Mommy never used nuts or candied fruit in her cakes, but these can be added if desired, also raisins.)
Bake in 4 or 5 small round cake pans at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours or until a clean broom straw inserted into the middle of cake comes out clean.

title: pork chops with rice
directions: Prepare chops in skillet (regular or electric) and remove from pan.
Pour into skillet 3 cups boiling water and 4 bouillon cubes; stir until dissolved.
Add one cup uncooked rice and celery.
Stir well.
Place chops on rice.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes until meat and rice are tender.
Add water to prevent sticking, if necessary.

title: grape jelly
directions: Stir sugar into water.
Place on high heat and, stirring constantly, bring quickly to a full rolling boil that cannot be stirred down.
Boil hard for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pectin.
Add thawed grape juice and mix well.
Pour jelly immediately into hot jars and seal.
Makes about 10 half pint jars.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix well.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Then make rolls and let rise.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: fluffy fruit dressing
directions: In saucepan, beat the egg and add the sugar and peels and lemon juice.
Cook over low heat until thick, while stirring, about 5 minutes.
Cool and fold in the whipped cream.
This yields about 2 1/2 cups.

title: mrs. van's divinity
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water.
Cook on medium heat to hard ball stage (260°).
Pour in a fine stream onto 2 beaten egg whites. Beat until it loses its gloss.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Spoon onto waxed paper.
Makes about 50 pieces.

title: pickled beets
directions: Mix together the last 3 ingredients.
When beets are tender, pack into hot jars.
Cover with the mixture.
Put 1 teaspoon pickling spice into each jar.
Cool jar lids, then seal.
If more liquid is needed, mix another mixture.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook meat and onion until
tender, about 2 hours.
Drain water and add sour cream and soup.
Cook on low heat 20 minutes more. Serve on noodles or rice.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients, using only 1 cup of the tomato sauce.
Pat out about 1-inch thick and sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Roll (approximately 10 x 4-inches) and seal edges.
Put in a shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Drain and pour the rest of the sauce over the meat.
Bake for 15 minutes more.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Roll in tiny balls. Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 375°
for 5 - 10 minutes.

title: venison roast
directions: Season roast with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Place in a roaster or Dutch oven.
Combine soup with water.
Add to roast. Cover roast with sliced onions.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 4 hours. Pull meat off of bones and combine with gravy.

title: cheese ball 2
directions: Grate all cheeses.
Add all ingredients into mixing bowl and mix until all ingredients are completely blended.
Place Saran Wrap in the bottom of a bowl and spoon in the cheese mix.
Cover top of mixture with the edges of the Saran Wrap and refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: crab cakes with avocado sauce
directions: Mix crabmeat and all of the ingredients with the exception of the breadcrumbs.
Add breadcrumbs and toss lightly.
Divide mixture into 4 patties.
Handle gently, it should barely hold together.
Heat skillet and add oil.
When hot, add patties carefully and saute gently over medium heat for 3 to 4 minutes on each side.

title: vegetable cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans.
Shape in ball and roll in pecans.
Serve with crackers.
Can also make finger sandwiches.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all together and let chill.

title: butternut cake
directions: Cream Crisco and
sugar
well.	Sift plain flour, self-rising flour and baking powder
together.	Add
eggs
one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour alternately with milk. Add flavoring.
Mix well.
Bake in 3 layer pans at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Boil rice and drain.
Add all ingredients together and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all dry ingredients in a large bowl. Beat eggs and mix with oil; stir this into dry mix and add frozen strawberries, juice and all; add nuts.
Divide mixture into 2 floured and greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans.
Bake for 1 hour or until bread tests done in middle.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Do not use mixer to mix.

title: raw cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries and sugar and let stand overnight.
Drain off juice and add remaining ingredients.
Fold all together gently. Serve on lettuce leaf.
A very good salad-dessert plate.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Chill until set.
Mix next 5 ingredients in order.
Cook until thick.
Remove and add cream cheese.
Cool this mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip. Spread on top of jello.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift
dry ingredients.	Stir in onions.
Combine water, egg and milk.
Stir until well blended.
Drop by teaspoon into hot fat.

title: barbecued hot dog bites
directions: Cut hot dogs into chunks.
Mix mustard and jelly.
Pour over hot dog chunks and heat.
Keeps well in crock-pot.

title: elisabeth's eclair pie
directions: Make pudding according to directions.
Mix pudding and Cool Whip.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Spread half of the pudding mixture over crackers.
Cover pudding with another layer of crackers and top with remaining pudding.
Cover pudding with another layer of crackers.

title: spaghetti salad(make 2 days ahead)
directions: Add the following just before serving:
cooked chicken, shrimp or crabmeat.
Top with sliced almonds.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, butter, sugar and onion until tender and let cool. Beat together milk and eggs and add to squash mixture. Add salt and pepper to taste. Cover with cheese and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix well, folding in broccoli last.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (use nonstick spray on pan).

title: dressed-up spiked baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in a baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Mix well first 4 ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, potatoes and water.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Bake in 1 pound coffee cans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: peanut butter loaf
directions: Put all in a blender.
Blend until smooth.
Steam for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Place in a pan of hot water, covered to steam. Keep water on low boil to create steam.
Best served cold in slices for sandwich or on crackers.
May be sliced and browned in a little or no oil.

title: ma's bars
directions: Mix margarine, brown sugar, water, flour, soda, white sugar, egg yolks, vanilla and salt together.
Spread and press onto greased cookie sheet with sides.
Sprinkle chopped nuts and chocolate chips on top and press in slightly.
Whip egg whites until stiff and add 1 cup of brown sugar and beat well.
Spread over top of dough.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool and cut as brownies.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients together.
Cook at low heat.
Do not stir too often.
Cook until syrup is dark brown and peanuts are cooked brown.
Remove and add soda.
Pour into buttered pan and let cool.

title: coconut-crunch cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars.
Add beaten egg and vanilla extract. Mix well. Sift together flour, baking powder and baking soda. Combine mixtures. Add oatmeal, cereal and coconut.
Mix well. Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook peas
and	butter	beans while preparing the rest. Bring all to a
boil and boil for 30 minutes.
Seal in sterilized jars.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine in a 2-quart casserole.
Mix together next 4 ingredients.
Pour over melted margarine, then add any fruit of your choice on top; juice and all.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Add butter to Stove Top. Mix half of Stove Top mixture to zucchini mixture. Place in 2-quart baking dish. Top with remaining Stove Top mixture. Cover and bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Remove cover and bake 5 to 10 minutes.

title: tuna loaf
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Fold in egg whites.
Turn into well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream shortening, add sugars and beat well.
Add the eggs and vanilla, stir to blend well.
Add the dry ingredients at one time, mix to blend thoroughly.
Last stir in oatmeal, nuts, chocolate chips and raisins. Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet and bake for 13 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.
This dough freezes well and can be sliced later to make fresh cookies. Makes 4 dozen large cookies.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Saute onion in margarine until tender.
Mix drained broccoli and onion with remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch casserole at 375° for 45 minutes.
Spread crushed saltines over top; drizzle with 1/2 stick melted margarine.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and salt.
Add eggs, butter, milk and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: black magic cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
Add eggs, coffee, milk, oil and vanilla. Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes (batter will be thin).
Pour batter into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes for oblong pan, or 30 to 35 minutes for layer.

title: easy italian casserole
directions: Combine meat, onion and garlic in large skillet.
Cook over medium heat until meat is browned and onion is tender.
Drain. Stir in spaghetti sauce, water, basil, oregano, sugar and pepper, mixing well.
Cook over medium heat for 2 minutes.

title: chinese chews
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Stir in dates, walnuts and eggs. Pour into greased
and
floured 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake	in a 350° oven about 15 minutes.
While warm, cut in bars.
Cool.
Remove from pan.
Roll in sifted confectioners sugar.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: pat's king ranch chicken
directions: Cook chicken in boiling water to cover for 45 minutes or until tender.
Remove chicken, reserving 3 cups of broth in a Dutch oven.
Let chicken cool, then skin, bone and cut into bite-size pieces.
Set aside.
Bring reserved broth to a boil.
Cut tortillas into quarters and dip into broth for 5 seconds to soften.
Set aside.
Place half of tortillas in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Layer with half each of chicken, onion and green pepper.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle top with cheese, chili powder and garlic salt.
Combine soups and spread over cheese. Top with undrained tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cooked through.
For a slightly different flavor, you may marinate the chicken overnight in Italian dressing and pineapple chunks.

title: jo's sauerkraut
directions: Drain sauerkraut through a colander.
Pour 2 cups water through the cabbage.
Cook with water and pork for about 2 hours.
Add oatmeal.
Season with salt, pepper and cumin as desired.
Cook for 20 minutes more.
Cut in kielbasi in 1/2-inch sections.
Cook for another 20 minutes and serve over peeled (cooked in their jackets) potatoes.

title: boneless chuck roast
directions: Sprinkle meat with salt and black pepper.
Place into a heavy casserole with a tight lid.
Add onions, celery, parsnips and carrots.
Pour in the tomatoes and juice.
Sprinkle with thyme and add bay leaf.
Cover.
Place into cold oven.
Bake at 300° for 2 to 3 hours.
When ready to serve, remove vegetables and meat onto a serving platter.
Discard bay leaf.
Heat pan juices to boiling. Boil over high heat until reduced, thickened and shiny.
Whisk in mustard during boiling.
Reduce juices to about 1 1/2 cups. Spoon over meat and vegetables to glaze.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: super stuffed potatoes
directions: Prick potatoes all over with fork. Arrange in microwavable dish; microwave on High for 15 to 18 minutes, turning halfway through until tender. Preheat oven to 400°. Halve potatoes and scoop out insides, leaving 1/4 inch shell.
Mash cooked potato with cottage cheese in bowl. Stir in ham, Cheddar cheese, onions, salt and pepper. Spoon into shells. Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: almond butter crunch pinwheel(easy candy)
directions: Cook all in small skillet over medium heat 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour in buttered aluminum pie pan.
When cool, break into pieces or leave as a pinwheel.

title: squash and corn casserole
directions: Bake at 350° until brown.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix together and pour over strawberries in the bottom of a graham cracker pie shell.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Over medium heat, melt together the first 3 ingredients. Place broccoli in colander and run warm water over it to thaw. Mix cheese mixture, broccoli and rice.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until smooth, about 1 minute.
Bake in greased 8-inch square pan in 425° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine in casserole and bake, covered, in microwave on High for 15 minutes, stirring half way through cooking time.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Saute sausage in skillet until brown.
Stir frequently.
Place bread cubes, sausage and cheese in greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Combine milk, eggs, salt and mustard in bowl and mix well. Pour into baking dish.
Cover tightly.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.
Uncover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into unbaked crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: wheat oat pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients and mix well. Pour filling into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350 degrees for 30-35 minutes or until set. Cool on a wire rack. Serves 8.

title: cheese grits
directions: Pour 1 cup of grits into 4 cups of boiling water with 1 teaspoon salt; boil for 3 minutes.
Stir in butter and garlic cheese.
Add slightly beaten eggs.
Pour into greased casserole. Bake at 325°, uncovered, until firm (40 to 45 minutes).
Remove from oven and top with grated Cheddar cheese; sprinkle with paprika.
Return to oven to brown.
Serves 8.

title: illinois sugar cookies
directions: In a large bowl, stir together the flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In a mixing bowl, beat the butter or margarine for 30 seconds.
Add the sugar and beat until fluffy.
Beat in the eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add the dry ingredients and beat until just mixed.
Drop the dough by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in a 375° oven for 9 to 11 minutes or until the edges are golden.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: joggin in a jug
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in cool place.
Drink 2 ounces a day, morning and evening.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Roll biscuits out flat.
Put sausage on the edge of biscuits and roll up.
Place on a baking sheet and bake until biscuits are done.

title: fresh easter ham
directions: Crush garlic and spread in bottom of roasting pan.
Add bay leaves.
Place the ham on top and salt and pepper to taste.
Add apple juice.
Cover and roast at 275° for 4 hours or until meat reaches 175°.
Remove rind and outer layer of fat.
Glaze with honey and pineapple.
Return, uncovered, to 375° oven for about 10 minutes or until glaze is nicely brown and bubbly.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Mix together until crumbly the butter, pudding and flour. Then add egg and milk.
Place in a buttered pie plate.
Drain a can of sliced peaches (save the juice).
Place peaches in pie shell.
Now mix the cream cheese, sugar and peach juice.
Spoon on top of peaches (not too close to edge).
Sprinkle top of pie with cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mulled pineapple cider
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Strain and serve hot.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Pound beef with mallet until thin.
Cut into strips about 1-inch wide.
Melt the 1 tablespoon butter in pan.
Saute onion for 2 minutes.
Then saute beef quickly in the butter, about 5 minutes. Turn; brown evenly.
Remove the beef; keep it hot.
Add the 2 tablespoons butter in pan.
Melt.
Add mushrooms.
Add beef. Season with salt, paprika, nutmeg and basil.
Add and heat, but do not boil, the sour cream.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies(no bake)
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a boil. Remove from heat. Then add peanut butter and cornflakes. Mix well. Spoon onto wax paper. Let cool. Store thoroughly tight with Saran. Do not refrigerate.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar gradually; cream well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well.
Add milk and flour that has been sifted with salt and soda.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 320° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: baked rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake at 350° to 400° about 1 hour to 1 1/2 hours, stirring about every 15 minutes until thickens. The more it's stirred the pudding will be more creamy.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: In a large skillet, saute chicken in 3 tablespoons olive oil until cooked through; remove chicken.
Add 1 tablespoon oil to skillet and cook onions and mushrooms until tender.
Stir in chicken, paprika, dill weed, pepper, salt and chicken broth. Cover and cook over low heat 10 minutes.
Add cornstarch mixture and bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in yogurt.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients with canned evaporated milk until it reaches desired consistency.
Drop by tablespoons into deep fryer (these will be pretty and round if you use an ice cream scoop to pick up small amounts, easier too).

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Shred zucchini; add onion, one beaten egg and cream of chicken soup.
Top with Pepperidge farm dressing mix and put in buttered casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine apples and cranberry sauce in mixing
bowl.
Combine brown sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg in a separate mixing bowl; add to apple mixture, mixing well.
Turn into pastry lined pan.
Cover with top crust. Crimp edges and slit top.
Bake for 1 hour or until crust is golden and filling bubbles.

title: golabki (stuffed cabbage)
directions: Mix all but cabbage together.
Peel off individual cabbage leaves.
Wrap each around a tablespoon of meat mixture.
Place in layers in deep casserole dish.
Add 1/2 cup of water; cover tightly with lid or foil.
Bake at 375°
for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Remove cover; drain off liquid.
Pour Red Sauce over top.

title: michael's peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix everything in a large bowl with a fork.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Roll dough, by teaspoonful, into a ball and place on pan and flatten.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: yankee doodle macaroni salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine sour cream, mayonnaise, vinegar and salt. Add the macaroni, celery, onions (include some of the green tops), peas, pimentos and eggs. Toss to coat. Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.

title: tangy tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour. Serve with seafood.

title: jenniffer's crock-pot stew
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add water, onion soup mix and tomato paste.
Simmer.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot and cook until tender, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a pie shell and bake for 25 minutes at 425°.

title: baked macaroni and dried beef
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole dish.
Let stand 4 hours or overnight.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes, then uncovered for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: jello pretzel salad
directions: Bake 15 minutes at 350° and cool completely.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Fry
sausage;
drain and cool.	Grease 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix eggs thoroughly; add milk.	Break bread into small pieces and
add to
mixture.
Stir
in salt, dry mustard, cheese and mushrooms. Add
green	pepper	and
onion if you elect to use them
in
this recipe.
Pour in pan.
Cover and let set overnight	in refrigerator.
Cook
for 45 minutes or until set at 350°.
Let set for 5 minutes before cutting into squares.

title: trini's pork chops
directions: Brown the pork chops in a skillet.
Sprinkle with the soup mix, mixed with the cornstarch.
Add the mushrooms.
Simmer until done.

title: chili
directions: Combine meat, garlic, onion, salt, pepper and paprika.
Cook until all water cooks out.
Brown flour in dry skillet; add to meat mixture.
Add cumin, chili quick and powder.
Add hot water until desired thickness is reached.
Add catsup, if desired.

title: cream of wheat bread
directions: Sift Cream of Wheat and flour with baking powder, salt and sugar together.
Add oil and milk to flour mixture.
Add egg and stir until well mixed.
Bake at 450° until brown and crunchy.

title: punch *
directions: Mix and chill.
When ready to serve, add 7-Up (10 ounces). Add two pints of pineapple or lime sherbet.
Makes more than one gallon.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325° to 350°.
Melt margarine in bottom of pan.
Spread evenly graham crumbs and pat down.
Add coconut.
Add nuts.
Add chocolate chips.
Add butterscotch chips.
Spread condensed milk as evenly as possible on top.
Bake for 30 minutes or until browned.
Remove and cool completely before cutting into bars.

title: easy turkey salad
directions: In a large bowl, stir together soup and mayonnaise until smooth.
Chop turkey, celery, red peppers and onions; fold into soup mixture.
Add black pepper.
Serve mixture on leaf lettuce. Cover and save any remaining mixture in refrigerator.
Makes about 5 cups or 8 servings.

title: chess pie
directions: Melt butter; set aside.
Combine other ingredients; add butter.
Put in unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: beef bisso
directions: Simmer beef, celery, onion and garlic in oil.
Add remaining ingredients, stir and simmer over low heat until meat is cooked (about 45 minutes).
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Blend dry ingredients well with Crisco.
Beat egg and add along with milk mixture and blend together.
Put lots of flour on your surface board and knead extra flour into dumplings.
Roll out very thin.
Cut in squares.
Have your chicken cooked and remove from broth.
Bring the broth to a rolling boil and drop butter and dumplings in.
Stir often and add black pepper to taste.
After all the dumplings have been added, turn the heat down to low.
Put lid on pot and simmer about 15 minutes.
Add the boned chicken and let simmer with dumplings.

title: fresh carrot cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put flour, sugar, baking soda and salt into ungreased 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Stir with fork to mix well.
Add carrot; stir until thoroughly blended.
Add remaining ingredients; stir to blend.
Using rubber spatula, scrape down any ingredients clinging to sides.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan; cut into 9 squares.

title: corned beef potato salad
directions: In large bowl, toss potatoes, meat, pickle, celery and onion. In covered jar, shake oil, vinegar, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Pour over meat and potato mixture; toss.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip bread
directions: Beat oil and sugar together.
Add eggs; mix well.
Combine dry ingredients and water to sugar, oil and eggs.
Mix in pumpkin, then add chocolate chips.
Grease loaf pan; spoon batter into pan. Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: lime jello and cottage cheese
directions: Add water or part pineapple and lime jello.
Put in 2 cup glass cup.
Put in microwave oven to boil.
Stir.
Add Miracle Whip and stir well.
Add pineapple and cottage cheese after jello thickens. Return to refrigerator to fully jell.

title: mama's spice cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients; set aside.
Cream shortening with sugar. Add eggs and beat well.
Add chocolate or cocoa and potatoes. Blend well and add dry ingredients alternately with coffee and vanilla, beating until smooth after each addition.
Add 1 cup chopped walnuts.
Blend well.
Grease 2 (9-inch) layer pans or 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Frost with buttercream frosting.

title: strawberries romanoff
directions: Remove stems from berries; rinse, drain and pat dry.
Place in bowl with 1/3 cup sugar and Grand Marnier.
Using a potato peeler, cut around orange to produce a very thin spiral of peel.
Do not cut into white pulp.
Add peel only to strawberries.
(Eat the orange.)
Cover and refrigerate.
Whip the cream with remaining 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Serve cream with strawberries.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Clean chicken breasts and lay in pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Spread rice in corners and between breasts.
Heat together the soup, milk and margarine.
Pour over the chicken and cover with foil.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hamburg pie
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Put in a deep 9-inch pie plate. Combine Bisquick, eggs and milk.
Beat vigorously.
Pour over hamburg.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: florida key lime pie
directions: Separate eggs. Combine the egg yolks and milk. Mix well. Slowly add juice until smooth and creamy. Pour into graham cracker pie crust. Bake for 10 minutes in 350° preheated oven. Serve chilled with whipped cream.

title: crusty pound cake
directions: Mix Crisco or Snowdrift and sugar together; beat 3 eggs and 1 cup flour in and then add 3 eggs and remaining flour in.
Add flavorings.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix sugars, Ultra Promise, vanilla and egg white in large bowl.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt. Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop dough by rounded spoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto ungreased nonstick cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: pork chops a la orange
directions: Combine flour, seasoned salt, paprika and pepper.
Reserve 1 teaspoon of mixture.
Coat chops with remaining flour mixture. Heat oil in skillet and brown chops.
Add orange juice and cloves. Cover and simmer for 45 minutes or until tender, turning occasionally.
Add orange slices and cook 5 minutes longer. Remove chops and orange slices to serving platter.
Remove cloves and discard.

title: spanish flan
directions: Caramelize 1 1/2 cups sugar and 1/3 cup water until golden brown.
Pour caramelized sugar into bottom of 7 x 11-inch Pyrex dish.
While sugar and water cook, beat eggs well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well together with eggs.
Pour over caramelized mixture.
Bake in water bath at 300° about 1 3/4 hours.
Cool and invert on serving tray.
(Do not overbake.)

title: cold stuffed mushrooms
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with other ingredients.
Fill mushroom caps with cheese mixture (you can use pastry bag for eye appeal).
Top each with small sprig of parsley.
Serve on lettuce leaves on platter.

title: spanish hash
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.

title: savory cheese loaf
directions: Cut bread diagonally, almost through the loaf, about 1/2-inch slices.
Mix butter, chopped onions, poppy seeds and prepared mustard.
Spread all but 2 tablespoons of mixture between bread slices.
Place cheese between each slice.
Spread outside of loaf with remaining butter mixture.
Press loaf together; arrange bacon slices on top of loaf.
Place in shallow pan or cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: patricia liston's frozen waldorf salad
directions: Mix eggs, lemon juice, sugar, pineapple juice and salt and cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Let cool. Mix together with remaining ingredients (excluding lettuce leaves), gently.
Put into muffin cups and let freeze.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Place in 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: nacho pizza dip
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients together.
Spread on bottom of pie plate.
Pour pizza sauce on top.
Put favorite pizza toppings on next (i.e., pepperoni, ground beef, mushrooms, etc.).
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for about 15 minutes in oven or microwave until cheese is melted.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook turkeys or chicken legs until tender.
Cut in small pieces.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, Miracle Whip, chopped onion and salt and pepper together.
Mix all together.
Add peas.

title: jalapeno cheese squares
directions: Mix well and bake in a 9 x 9-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°. Cut into squares.

title: crunchy rice salad
directions: Sprinkle apples with lemon juice blended with water.
Mix with rice, celery, walnuts and relish; blend Thousand Island dressing and pepper.
Toss with rice mixture.
Serve on salad greens if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: aunt jenny's hamburg balls
directions: Combine meat, onion, green pepper, cornmeal, seasonings, milk and egg.
Mix thoroughly; make balls.
Place on cookie sheet; bake until brown.
Place in casserole.
Place drippings and bacon grease in skillet.
Heat; add flour to make paste.
Add tomato to make gravy.
Pour into casserole and bake at 375°
for 45 minutes or longer.

title: chicken cheese puff
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Use
an
8-inch square baking dish. Place
chicken
in dish.
Top chicken with gravy.
Bake for
10 minutes.
Beat egg whites with salt until peaks form. Set
aside. Beat
egg
yolks until thick.
Fold in whites and the
Parmesan cheese.
Pour egg mixture over chicken mixture. Top with almonds. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil 1 small potato and mash it.
Add confectioners sugar till cookie dough consistency.
On wax paper - sprinkle confectioners sugar and roll dough to about a pie crust thickness. Spread peanut butter (thin layer) on the dough.
The sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Roll into a log roll.
Let chill approximately 1 hour or overnight in the refrigerator.
When set (hard), slice into bite size pieces.

title: cucumber dressing
directions: Mix well all the ingredients.
Slice cucumbers and onions and add mixture.

title: luncheon dish
directions: Place a layer of sliced potatoes in a buttered casserole, then the following in layers, ending with a layer of potatoes:
