1 medium finely chopped onion, 2 Tbsp. uncooked rice, 1 lb. lean hamburger, salt and pepper to taste, 1 c. tomato juice, and 1/2 pint boiling water.

title: chili
directions: Cook up hamburg and onions until brown.
Add beans, salsa and chili powder.

title: make ahead chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before baking.
Stir well; spoon into a 2 or 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Dip chicken in egg and milk. Dredge in flour mixed with seasonings.
Place in shallow dish.
Pour margarine over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Serves 4.

title: mexican pork chops and beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place flour in 1 large size oven cooking bag, then place bag in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Add salsa, juice, chili powder and garlic powder to bag.
Squeeze bag to blend ingredients.
Place pork chops in bag.
Spoon beans and peppers around pork chops.
Close bag with nylon tie; cut 6 half-inch slits in top.
Bake until pork chops are tender, 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand in bag 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg and add syrup. Sift together
flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add dry ingredients to mixture;
stir
until
smooth.
Add boiling water and again, stir until
smooth.
(Do not beat.) Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to
25 minutes.
Serve
with sliced banana and whipped cream.

title: rice krispie bars
directions: Melt in saucepan or double boiler 6 ounces chocolate bits and 6 ounces butterscotch bits.
While cooling, bring to boil in large saucepan 1/2 cup white corn syrup and 1/2 cup sugar.
Remove from burner; stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla and 3/4 cup peanut butter.
Mix well.
Quickly add 3 1/2 cups Rice Krispies and mix thoroughly. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with melted bits.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: becky's bean salad
directions: Combine, drain, and rinse all beans.
Set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Add beans to mixture.
Marinate overnight.	Serve 8-10.

title: grandpa's chili soup
directions: Chop onions and saute in large skillet.
When translucent, add hamburger and cook while chopping until well done and crumbled.

title: vegetarian spanish rice
directions: Cook Rice: Combine 3 cups water and 1 1/2 cups long grain white rice. Bring to boil; reduce to simmer. Cover and cook for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: karen's potato chowder
directions: In
a
large
kettle
combine
potatoes, onion, carrot, salt, pepper, parsley and bouillon.
Add enough water to just cover vegetables;
cook
until vegetables are tender.
Do not drain. Scald milk.
Remove 1 1/2 cups milk and add butter and flour
to hot milk.
Stir with wire whisk.
Add remaining hot milk
to undrained vegetables, then stir in the thickened milk mixture. Simmer 15 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, onion and green pepper, if desired, in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with sugar and stir well.
Cover and chill for 2 hours.
Combine vinegar and remaining ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring, until salt dissolves.
Pour hot vinegar mixture over cabbage mixture.
Toss well.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Serve with a slotted spoon.
Yields 6 servings.

title: happy face pancakes
directions: Make pancake mix. Separate a portion of mix and add food coloring.
Heat pan and drop small drops of batter into the pan in a happy face design with eyes, nose and a smile.
Cook for 1 minute, then pour batter over and around the face.
Cook as usual.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In 2-quart casserole dish spoon in 1 can of pie filling.
Sprinkle 1/2 of cake mix.
Dot with 1/2 of margarine and nuts.
Repeat layers.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes until brown.

title: doughnuts
directions: Mix, cut and deep fry.
Sugar the doughnut holes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Cook at 400° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil, mix melted butter into casserole and bake an additional 5 minutes, uncovered.

title: cheddar pecan crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Beat together butter and cheddar in a bowl with an electric mixer until smooth, then beat in remaining ingredients.

title: billy goat cookies(andrew jackson's)
directions: Drop cookies (makes several).
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes. Put cookies in tight container.
Will keep a long time.

title: quick-n-easy fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and mixed fruit; save pineapple juice only (about 1 cup).
Put fruit cocktail and pineapple together.
Empty pudding in a bowl.
Mix pineapple juice into the dry pudding mix. Add orange juice and blend.
Combine pudding mixture with the fruit and pineapple.
Add the bananas.
Chill.

title: august pasta
directions: In large serving bowl, combine tomatoes, zucchini, oil, parsley, basil, garlic, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook pasta in salted boiling water until just tender al dente.
Drain in colander and immediately toss drained pasta with sauce.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Adjust seasoning, if necessary, and serve immediately.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Use the same saucepan for the first 4 steps.
Cook and drain broccoli and place in large mixing bowl.
Saute onion in margarine and pour over broccoli.
Cook rice according to package instructions and add to bowl.
Heat the soup and Cheez Whiz until cheese melts and mix together with contents of mixing bowl.
Place in foil-lined 13 x 9- inch pan or shallow casserole dish.
Crush croutons and sprinkle on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until bubbly (about 30 minutes).
You may substitute onion powder for the onions if you like.

title: bud's favorite rhubarb
directions: Remove crust from bread and cube.
Melt butter and dash of red coloring.
Coat the bread with butter mixture and add sugar; mix well until the bread is sugared.
Fold rhubarb into sugared bread mixture.
Pour into baking dish.
Put 1 tablespoon water in each corner of pan.
Do not mix.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Good as a vegetable or dessert.
Serves 6.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: May cook onions and celery a little.
Mix in the remaining ingredients, except cracker crumbs.
Put in casserole dish. Cover with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: party potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except potatoes and Parmesan cheese. Stir in potatoes.
Spread in ungreased casserole dish and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake for one hour at 325°.
Uncover and bake another 30 minutes.
Can be sprinkled with paprika before serving, if desired.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Mix avocados, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
On large platter, spread bean dip. Top with seasoned avocado mixture.
Layer with sour cream/mayo mixture.
Sprinkle with chopped onions, tomatoes and olives. Cover with cheese.
Serve with large round tortilla chips.

title: tamale tempters
directions: Cut tamales into 1 inch pieces.
Wrap each in bacon, fasten with a toothpick and broil until bacon is crisp.
Easy and good!

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: coca cola chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken and place in skillet. Mix Coke and catsup and pour over chicken. Bring to a boil. Lower heat to simmer and cook until chicken is tender.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until done.
Mix everything else together.
Pour mixture and carrots together and refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Better if carrots are barely tender.

title: corn-broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Add thawed broccoli, the corn and the crackers.
Put all ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tex-mex chili(mexican-american)
directions: Coarsely grind meat in food processor.
Marinate overnight in orange juice (orange juice tenderizes the meat without adding flavor).

title: french fried squash or eggplant
directions: Combine eggs, milk and salt to make a batter.
Dip squash in batter, then roll in cornmeal.
Fry in deep fat until golden brown.

title: strawberry nut cake
directions: Combine cake mix, Jello and strawberries with mixer.
Add eggs and beat 2 minutes.
Fold in coconut and nuts. Pour into sheet cake pan and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: easy brunswick stew
directions: In large soup pot, combine shredded chicken, tomatoes, tomato sauce, onion, bell pepper, parsley, vinegar and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium.
Combine 1/2 cup water with flour and stir until smooth.
Add to meat mixture. Add remaining water, salt, black pepper, turmeric, Tabasco, and Worcestershire sauce. Cook over medium heat for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Stir in corn and butter.
Simmer, covered, for another 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 1/2 gallon.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash with onion until tender and drain.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with a few more crushed crackers.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: holly's famous potatoes
directions: Place hash browns in a 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Melt oleo and mix with sour cream, onion, chicken soup, and grated cheese. Spread this over hash browns.

title: cheddar potatoes
directions: Mix above ingredients together.
For topping, mix 2 cups crushed corn flakes and 1/2 cup melted margarine together and sprinkle over top of potato mixture.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10 plus.

title: bubble bath soap
directions: Store in tightly covered bottle or jar.
Add 1 to 2 tablespoons to running water.

title: strawberry-pecan freeze
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients together.
Spread evenly in baking pan (use cookie sheet).
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Stirring occasionally with fork, sprinkle 2/3 crumbs in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
(Line with tinfoil if tin pan.)
Combine egg whites, sugar, berries and lemon juice in a large bowl; beat at high speed (almost 10 minutes) until stiff.
Fold in Cool Whip; spoon over crumbs.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Freeze 6 hours or overnight.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugars and margarine; add oil and eggs.
Beat well.
Add all of the other ingredients, mix well.
Roll in balls the size of a walnut.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Dip a smooth-bottomed glass in sugar and press cookies.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Loosen cookie on sheet and let cool on sheets.
Very crisp and good.

title: quiche
directions: Prebake pie crust for 5 to 6 minutes at 450°.
Beat eggs and milk; add cheese and broccoli.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake quiche at 325° for 50 minutes or until center is set.
Let cool for 10 minutes before cutting.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients and cut out like biscuits.
Or shape rolls.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together well.
Bake in 350° oven for about 45 to 55 minutes. Makes best in large cast iron skillet.

title: mud pie
directions: You will need 1 small child's sand bucket and shovel.
Cream the cream cheese and milk; add the Cool Whip and 2/3 of the cookie crumbs.
Mix until blended.
Save 1/3 of the crumbs to sprinkle on bottom of container and top.
Make a day before serving and refrigerate.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook beef, onion, green pepper, salt and chili powder in skillet until beef is browned and crumbly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook 30 minutes or until rice is tender, stirring often.

title: pineapple shrimp appetizers(makes 30 appetizers)
directions: Combine all ingredients except cucumbers in medium bowl.
Cut cucumbers in 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick slices.
Spoon heaping teaspoonful of pineapple mixture on top of each slice.
Garnish with additional dill or minced green onion, if desired.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Melt chocolate chips and 14 ounces of almond bark in a 2-quart bowl in microwave on High for 2 minutes; stir and continue microwaving 1 to 2 minutes or until smooth, stirring every 30 seconds.
Stir in marshmallows, cereal and nuts.
Pour into buttered 12-inch round pizza pan.
Top with red and green M&M's. Microwave remaining almond bark and oil; melt until smooth. Drizzle over candy.
Refrigerate until firm and store at room temperature.
Cut into wedges.
Makes about 12 pieces.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook sliced squash and onion in boiling water for 15 minutes; drain.
Combine soup and sour cream in large bowl. Fold in drained squash and onion.
Combine stuffing mix and oleo. Spread half of stuffing mix in bottom of 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mixture on top.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing over squash.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 6 or more.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In a heavy skillet, make a roux with flour and oil, stirring constantly, until medium brown.
Add onion, bell pepper, celery and saute until tender-crisp.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, bay leaf and water.
Cook on medium heat until thickened, about 10 minutes.
Add shrimp and green onions; cook until shrimp are done, about 7 minutes.
Season as needed with pepper, lemon juice and garnish with parsley.
Serve over cooked rice.
If you like spicy use whole can of Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Serves 4.

title: date orange slices
directions: Cook together dates, sugar, water, 2 tablespoons flour and 1/4 teaspoon salt until thick. Remove from heat. Add orange slices and coconut. Cool. Mix together remaining ingredients and pat half of it in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with filling and spread remaining dough on top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Cut when cool.

title: party hot dogs
directions: You will need toothpicks for serving.

title: butterscotch sticky buns
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in 13 x 9-inch baking pan in preheated 375° oven.
Unroll dinner rolls; separate into 16 triangles.
Sprinkle triangles with 1 1/2 cups morsels.
Starting at shortest side, roll up each triangle.
Arrange in prepared baking pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes until lightly browned.

title: chocolate candy cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend salad dressing, cake mix and eggs at low speed with electric mixer until moistened.
Beat on medium speed 2 minutes.
Stir in candies (dough will be stiff).
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes or until almost set (cookies will appear soft).
Cool 1 minute.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Makes approximately 4 1/2 dozen.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Add flour, sugar and brown sugar.
Beat until well blended. Blend in melted butter. Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake for 1 hour.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat in a small amount of water.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Add soups and mix well.
Stir
in rice.
Lay chicken on mixture.
Cover with foil and bake 60 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook hamburger and onions together.
Drain.
Add Veg-All, tomato sauce and beef stew seasoning.
Simmer.
At this point, the base can be stored in refrigerator a couple of days or frozen. When ready to use, heat and add V-8 juice and cubed potatoes (if desired).
Serves 38 to 40.

title: mustard greens
directions: Wash mustard greens well and let drain.
Add water, meat and salt.
Cook 1 hour on low heat.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lemon baked chicken(heart healthy)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except chicken and parsley.
Place chicken in a shallow pan.
Pour mixture over chicken pieces.
Bake for about 50 minutes, until chicken is tender.
Baste several times with liquid in pan during baking. Garnish with parsley.

title: three cheese-ham puff
directions: Lightly
grease
quart
round casserole.
Beat eggs. Beat in	baking	mix and milk until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients;
pour	into
casserole.
Bake at 350° until knife inserted near
center
comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: corn relish
directions: Cut the corn from the cobs.
Chop the cabbage, seeded peppers and celery in a food chopper using the coarse blade.
Mix these with the rest of the ingredients and boil the mixture for 30 minutes.
Jar and seal.

title: french bread
directions: Put shortening, salt, and sugar into large mixing bowl.
Add 1 cup boiling water; cool to lukewarm by adding 1 cup cold water. Blend in yeast and add flour, 2 cups at a time.
Knead and place in bowl to rise.
Punch down and let rise again.
Turn out on floured board; divide into two loaves.
Slash tops and place on cookie sheet.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 400 degrees for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350 degrees and bake for another 35 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Chill thoroughly, mixing well. Add ginger ale last.

title: creamy peach salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Blend yogurt into whipped topping, then blend in gelatin.
Stir in peaches and nuts.
Pour into an 8 x 4-inch pan.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Unmold.
Garnish with additional peach slices.

title: fontenot crawfish
directions: Clean crawfish tails.
Place in deep dish.
Add lemon juice and boil for 20 minutes.
Salt to taste.
Place in icebox for 30 minutes.
Serve with piquant sauce.

title: oatmeal cookies(with filling)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients and add oats and coconut. Drop by teaspoon on well-greased sheet 2 inches apart.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a pan and freeze.
Cut into squares.

title: cheddar and tuna stuffed pita
directions: Combine and serve in 1/2 pita bread lined with lettuce leaf.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Cover beef lightly with flour.
Heat oil in large frypan. Brown the beef.
Drain all excess oil.
Saute all chopped vegetables with beef.
Now, add stewed tomatoes and tomato sauce. Let simmer for 1 hour.
Serve over cooked noodles.
Can be served with rice.

title: easy chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. With mixer, beat cheese until fluffy, gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth. Add egg, vanilla; mix well. Toss chips with flour; stir into cheese mixture. Pour into pie crust. Bake 35 min or until center springs back when lightly touched. Cool and top with glaze. Serve chilled. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix it all up (after mixing the pudding) and chill it for a few hours.

title: mini bacon bites
directions: Flatten out crescent rolls.
Press seams together to form solid dough.
Mix cream cheese, pepper, bacon bits and onion. Spread onto crescent roll dough.
Roll dough to form a log.
Slice into 1/2 sections.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 minutes or golden brown.

title: hearty vegetable barley soup
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, brown meat in oil.
Add onion and garlic; continue cooking until onion is tender.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients except green beans.
Cover; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer 50 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add green beans; continue cooking about 10 minutes.
Add water if soup becomes too thick upon standing.
Makes 12 (1 cup) servings.

title: cheesy meat pie
directions: In skillet, melt margarine over medium heat.
Add hamburger and onion; brown.
Remove from heat; drain.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Spread beef mixture over pie crust.
Spread cheese over beef mixture.
Blend well the milk, eggs and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over meat and cheese.
Set pie pan on cookie sheet. Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes at 400°.
Let cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add white and brown sugar; mix well.
Add eggs and blend well.
Mix all dry ingredients and add to mixture raisins and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: french bread
directions: In a 4-quart glass bowl mix warm water and dry yeast.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Add sugar and oil.
Stir in flour (will be sticky).

title: barbecued green beans
directions: Brown bacon and onions in skillet, add catsup, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Place beans in greased casserole and pour bacon mixture on top.
Do not stir.
Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Take out of oven just before serving and stir the bacon mixture through the beans.

title: homemade pineapple cake
directions: Beat butter until creamy.
Add 1 cup sugar and beat well.
Add the other cup of sugar and beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each.
Add vanilla and stir.
Mix in 1 cup flour and part of the milk.
Add flour and milk alternately until milk is gone, then use juice.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: aunt mable's chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt together.
Put oleo, water and cocoa in saucepan.
Bring to boil and pour over flour and sugar mixture.
In another bowl, put eggs, baking soda, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture and mix well.
Bake in greased and floured shallow pan (15 1/2 x 10 x 1-inch).
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Start icing last 5 minutes cake is baking.

title: pam's cheese soup
directions: Melt 6 tablespoons butter; add flour, then milk to make a white sauce.
Add cheese and remove from heat.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in another pan.
Add vegetables and cook until tender.
Add chicken stock and mix well.
Combine the 2 mixtures and spices. Heat, but do not boil.

title: easy cream pie
directions: Cook to a boil over medium heat, stirring to keep from sticking.
Cool 10 minutes.
Pour into 9-inch baked pie shell. Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: creamy chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Stir in chicken, 1/2 cup picante sauce, cream cheese and cumin.
Heat thoroughly.
Remove from heat and stir in 1/2 cup Cheddar and 1/2 cup Monterey Jack.
Spoon 1/3 cup of the chicken mixture down center of each tortilla.
Roll up and place seam-side down in baking dish.
Spoon remaining picante sauce over tortillas.
Mix remaining cheeses with the soup and the milk.
Spoon mixture over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 25 minutes, until thoroughly heated.

title: honey-dill cole slaw
directions: In small bowl, combine honey, sour cream and dill. In large bowl, toss cole slaw mix with onion and honey-sour cream mixture. Season with salt and pepper. Serve immediately. Makes 4 servings.

title: brownies you'll crave
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and heat to boiling.
Remove from heat and add powdered sugar; return to full boil for two minutes. Remove from heat a second time and add vanilla.
Pour over brownies and spread smooth.
Let set several hours.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Measure dry ingredients and stir together. Measure other ingredients into large mixing bowl.
Mix until well blended. Slowly add dry ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Put all ingredients except rice in large saucepan.
Add 1 cup water; bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer covered for 15 minutes.
Top each serving with 1/2 cup hot cooked rice.
Serves 6.

title: sweet-sour pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain and rinse with cold water.
Place in a large serving bowl.

Add the onion, tomato, cucumber, green pepper and parsley; set aside. In a saucepan, combine the last 5 ingredients to make the dressing. Cook over medium-low heat for about 10 minutes or until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over salad and toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours. Serve with slotted spoon. Yields 16 servings.

title: nacho dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and taco sauce and spread over serving platter or on bottom of large bowl.
Add chopped lettuce to cover and top with tomato, cheese and olives.
Use nacho chips to scoop up dip.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Rinse off the kidney beans in sieve and remove any stones. Soak overnight.
Drain the water.
Add fresh water to cover by 2 inches.
Cook until tender.
Drain again.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly spray 9-inch pie plate with nonstick cooking spray.
Place spaghetti in pie plate.
Top with cheese and sauce.
Bake 15 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes. Sprinkle with chopped fresh parsley, if desired.
Cut into wedges. Serves 4 to 6.

title: election day cake
directions: In a large bowl, thoroughly mix 1 3/4 cups flour, sugar, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, mace and undissolved yeast.
Add margarine.
Gradually add very hot tap water to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer.
Add eggs and 3/4 cup flour or enough flour to make dough thick batter. Beat on high speed 2 minutes.
Add raisins and citron; stir well until mixed.
Put into greased pan; cover and let rise in warm place until double, about 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.

title: tuna sopa soca
directions: Note:
I use flour tortillas; we think it is better.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix everything together and stir in refrigerator.

title: vegetable bean soup
directions: Saute oil, flour, onion and garlic and add to soup.
Add lemon juice.

title: chicken elegant
directions: In a saucepan, heat all ingredients, stirring occasionally until hot and bubbly.
Serve over baked Pepperidge Farms patty shells.
(Shells are bought frozen.)
Remove centers as directed on package.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt onto wax paper.
Put shortening, peanut butter, sugar and light brown sugar in mixing bowl and cream until well blended.
Add unbeaten egg and vanilla and beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients and blend thoroughly to make a stiff dough.
Shape dough into balls with hands, using about 1 tablespoon of dough for each ball, and place directly on greased baking sheet.
Flatten each ball with fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Remove cookies immediately from baking sheet to rack to cool.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oil, lemon pudding mix and eggs; mix well. Stir in 7-Up until smooth.
Turn batter into 2 well-greased 8-inch cake pans and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until cake springs back when touched.
Cool, then frost and stack layers, covering top and sides with Coconut-Pineapple Frosting.

title: pretzels
directions: Stir the yeast, sugar and warm water together in a large bowl until the yeast is dissolved. Set aside to "proof" or get foamy (about 15 to 20 minutes).
After the yeast proofs, stir in the flour, a little at a time, until the dough is stiff.
Knead on a floured surface for 3 to 5 minutes.
Form the dough into a ball and place it in a buttered bowl. Cover with a dish towel and let it rise in a warm place until doubled in size.
After the dough has risen, punch it down (the fun part!) and roll it into a rectangle. Cut fat strips to shape into pretzels.
Any shape your child comes up with is a pretzel!
Beat the egg with a fork and brush onto pretzels.
Sprinkle on salt to taste. Bake in a 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken medley
directions: Prepare dressing according to directions on package.
(I am sure you may use another brand.)
Place in bottom of 10 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cook broccoli; drain and arrange on top of the dressing.
(Don't overcook broccoli).
Cut the cooked chicken in pieces and place on top of broccoli.
Mix mayonnaise, soup, lemon juice and curry. Pour over the chicken.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Cover with buttered crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for approximately 40 minutes or until brown and bubbly.
(This casserole will freeze well.)
Serves 10 to 12.
Garnish with parsley.

title: cheddar chicken rice casserole
directions: May layer ingredients in casserole dish or mix.

title: pig lickin' cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a floured and greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: walnut pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350 degrees for about 45 - 50 minutes until set firm.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook and drain the broccoli in the water and salt.
In double boiler, melt the cheese roll and add the soup.
In 2 tablespoons butter, saute the onion, celery and mushrooms.
Saute only until clear and add the two sauces.
Combine all ingredients in double boiler and mix well.
Serve hot from chafing dish.

title: chipped beef spread
directions: Soften cream cheese. Add milk and sour cream. Beat in mixer. Beat in remaining ingredients by hand. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cut flowerets from broccoli.
Peel broccoli stems and dice. Bring to boil water, broccoli, onion, bouillon, garlic and thyme. Simmer about 15 minutes or until tender.
Cool slightly.
Puree all but about 2 cups of broccoli mixture.
Melt butter in different saucepan over medium heat.
Stir in flour.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add pepper and half and half.
Cook until thickened.
Add to broccoli puree.
Add reserved cooked broccoli mixture.
Serve hot.
Serves about 8. Can be frozen for later. Enjoy!

title: old fashion banana pudding
directions: Mix flour, salt and 1/2 cup of sugar.
Put in top of a double boiler and add milk slowly.
Stir constantly over boiling water until thickened.
Occasionally stir while cooking 15 minutes more, uncovered.
Beat egg yolks in bowl and stir into custard mixture gradually.
Return to heat.
Stir constantly and cook 5minutes more.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.

title: buffalo chicken
directions: Slice chicken into strips.
Chop or slice onions and celery. Coat chicken with garlic, vinegar and Tabasco sauce (to taste). Add onions and celery to baking dish with chicken.
Cover with aluminum foil and cook at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar and water 3 to 4 minutes.
In a bowl, pour over peanut butter and marshmallow.
Mix well.

title: chicken fried steak
directions: Cut meat into four pieces,
Pound the meat until tender.
Mix flour, salt and pepper together in a pie pan; dredge steak in mixture.
Cook in hot melted shortening over medium-high heat until brown, turn and brown on the other side.
The quicker the meat cooks the juicier it stays.
Don't overcook steak. Make the gravy in the next recipe for the steak.

title: grilling marinade
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Use to marinate chicken, beef or pork two to three hours before grilling or broiling.
Makes 1 cup.

title: fruit cake
directions: Soak marshmallows in Eagle Brand milk.
Add fruit, raisins and nuts to marshmallow mixture.
Gradually add graham cracker crumbs. *
Butter and crumb cake pan.
Pack cake firmly in pan.
Leave cake in pan overnight.
Warm pan before taking cake out of pan.

title: cheese meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients, except sauce and cheese, together.
Roll mixture out on waxed paper.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Roll up like a jelly roll and put into pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Drain out grease.
Pour on can of tomato sauce and bake another 30 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Layer in casserole the first 5 ingredients.
Mix the sour cream, soup and 1/3 of corn juice; pour evenly over vegetables. Cover top of casserole with cheese and crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Spread popcorn and nuts in large shallow pan.
Place in preheated oven at 250° to keep warm.
Combine butter, brown sugar, syrup and salt in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until sugar dissolved.
Wash sugar from sides of pan.
Boil until mixture reaches 248° (firm ball stage).
Cook 5 minutes at that degree. Remove from heat and stir in soda.
Pour mixture over corn.
Stir to coat.
Bake 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
When cool, store in tight container.

title: cheese filled meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients well (except cheese).
Line loaf pan with 2 or 3 layers waxed paper.
Spread 1/2 of mixture in pan. Cover with cheese and remaining meat.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Let stand 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: baker's monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in fourths.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together. Melt butter.
Mix or shake biscuits and cinnamon/sugar in bowl. Place half of biscuits in tube or Bundt pan.
Pour half of melted butter over biscuits.
Repeat.
Pour remaining extra sugar/cinnamon over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: corn pudding souffl
directions: Mix all together. Bake 1 hour at 400°. Stir once after 30 minutes.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Follow directions on package for cooking pie.
Beat egg whites and mix with sugar until smooth.
Slowly fold this into the hot pie filling.
Put into graham cracker pie crust.
Put in the refrigerator for about 4 hours.
Very easy and very good.

title: mexican taco dip
directions: Fry ground beef, drain and add beanless chili.
Grate cheese and set aside.
Add enough sour cream (1/4 pint) to refried beans to make smooth.
Spread into a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Layer the beef and chili mixture on top of the refried beans.
Top with the cheese.
Spoon red and green taco sauce on top of cheese.
Bake at 350°
for 35 minutes.
Top dish with remaining sour cream and serve with corn chips of your choice.

title: apple cake(my favorite)
directions: Beat eggs and sugar for about 5 minutes until creamy.
Add oil. Start adding flour; put rest in by hand.
Add apples and nuts. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to a hour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put powdered sugar on top.
(Some only use 1 cup sugar and 1 cup oil if you don't like it sweet.)

title: easy chicken with onions
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Add onions.
Mix soup and sherry.
Pour over chicken.
Grate cheese over top.
Bake in a 350° oven, covered for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 to 45 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: broiled steak with mushrooms
directions: With a sharp knife, score both sides of steak with diamond pattern, cutting about 1/4-inch deep.
Brush steak and mushrooms with oregano, salt and pepper.
Broil steak 2 inches from heat for 5 minutes.
Turn steak.
Add mushrooms to broiler pan and broil 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown steak in shortening.
Remove steak.
Blend in flour. Add ketchup, water, soy sauce, black pepper and garlic salt.
Bring to boil and simmer for 20 minutes.
Drop in meat and cook until tender (10 minutes).
Add pepper and onion rings.
Cook until tender on low.
Best cooked in crock-pot.

title: strawberry slush
directions: Place berries and juice in a blender or food processor.
Blend until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Makes 3 (1/2 cup) servings.
If you prefer less sweetness, fresh berries or a banana can be added, too.

title: pigs 'n blanket
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown sausages (if link), drain on towel (Viennas do not have to be cooked).
Cut biscuit in half. Roll thin.
Put sausage in slice of cheese and roll up.
Then start at end of biscuit.
Roll up and pinch ends.
Put in 350° oven and cook until biscuits are brown, about 10 minutes.

title: strawberry eggnog milkshake supreme
directions: Beat egg yolks well, then beat in sugar, then cream and flavoring.
In separate bowl, whip egg whites until stiff and fold into egg mixture.
Combine ice cream and mashed strawberries and beat vigorously until smooth and creamy.
Blend in 2 cups of eggnog.
Serve in tall glasses with a dash of nutmeg.

title: toll house chocolate chip cookies
directions: In small bowl combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside. In large bowl combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded measuring teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 100 (2-inch) cookies.

title: bread and butter pickle slices
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions, green peppers and salt.
Cover with crushed ice.
Let stand several hours.
Drain well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour over cucumbers.
Bring to a full boil.
Fill hot pint jars with vegetables and liquid, leaving 1/2-inch headspace. Process in boiling water, 5 minutes.
Start counting time when water returns to boil.
Makes 8 pints.

title: white chocolate drops
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix the first 4 ingredients until smooth. Add melted chocolate.
Mix well. Stir in combined dry ingredients and white chocolate. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 7 to 9 minutes until cookies are almost set.

title: enchiladas fantastic
directions: In a 10 inch skillet, cook beef until it loses its pink color, breaking into small pieces with spoon.
Add 1 cup of the picante sauce, spinach, 1 1/2 tsp. of cumin and the salt.
Cook and stir 5 minutes or until most of the liquid has evaporated.
Add cream cheese, stirring just until melted; remove from heat.
Spoon about 1/3 cup filling down center of each tortilla; roll up and place seam side down in lightly greased 13 x 9 inch baking dish.
Combine tomatoes, remaining 1 cup picante sauce and remaining cumin; mix well.
Spoon over enchiladas.
Bake at 350° 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese; return to oven 2 minutes to melt cheese.
Top as desired and serve with additional picante sauce.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugar,
shortening
and	eggs.
Sift dry ingredients.
Roll dough, cut and sprinkle lightly with sugar.

title: chess pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze.
Will keep in freezer for several weeks.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine everything and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: jake's favorite
directions: In skillet, brown meat and drain.
In large pot, combine tomato juice, onion, pepper, celery and mushrooms.
Add meat and season to taste.
Cover and simmer 1 to 2 hours.
Cook noodles and drain, then add to mixture and serve.

title: rice fiesta
directions: Cook onion in oil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add next 4 ingredients. Bring to a boil, cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Put half of rice mixture in a baking dish; top with half of chili and then cheese slices.
Repeat layers with remaining rice, chili and cheese slices.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts, about 15 minutes.

title: amish potato pancakes
directions: Process the ingredients in a blender in order given.
Fry in hot oil.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with applesauce, plum sauce or sour cream.

title: pepper steak
directions: Trim fat from beef and cut into thin strips.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Add beef and stir-fry for about 5 minutes.
Add onions and bell peppers and cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Add water, gravy mix, salt and ginger.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Blend cornstarch and soy sauce; stir into beef mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Cook 1 minute.
Serve over rice.

title: strawberry sheet cake
directions: Bake cake to directions in sheet cake pan.
After cake is cool, mix jello, water and soda pop together.
Poke holes all over top of cake with fork.
Pour jello over top of cake.
Chill.
Mix pudding and milk, then add Cool Whip.
Spread on top like icing.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk in a large saucepan.
Bring to a soft boil (boil at least 3 minutes).
Remove from heat, add vanilla and peanut butter.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Let cool.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Put some water in drip
pan in oven.
Brown hamburger in iron skillet. When nearly brown, add small cup of hot peppers, chopped fine, on top evenly.
Make corn bread mixture of corn meal, eggs, oil, milk, onions, creamed corn and baking powder.
Put grated cheese on top of hamburger and hot peppers.
Add corn meal mixture on top of cheese (do not stir).
Put skillet on rack over water. Bake at 350° about 40 to 50 minutes. (Water keeps corn bread from becoming too dry.)

title: wacky chocolate cake
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients into ungreased 9-inch baking pan. Make 3 holes in flour mixture.
In one hole, put in the vanilla and vinegar.
In the second hole, put in the salad oil and in the third hole add the cold water.
Mix all together with a fork until well blended.
Bake at 350°.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Add chopped mixture and have hot when put into sterilized jars.
Seal.

title: breakfast cakes(from 1975 edition)
directions: Mix baking powder and flour and add shortening.
Mix with hands.
Save some crumbs for top.
Add egg and milk and mix.
Put crumbs on top.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and mashed bananas.
(I like to mix my baking soda and baking powder with just a little water.)
Add flour, then add mixture of baking powder and soda. Add nuts, if you want.
Put into a greased loaf pan; stir until mixed (do not beat).
Bake at 350°.

title: cheesy beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat in skillet. Drain. Stir in water. Bring to a boil. Stir in noodles. Reduce heat to medium-low. Cover. Simmer 8 minutes or until noodles are tender. Add Velveeta, soup and pepper. Stir until Velveeta is melted. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: turtle cake frosting
directions: Melt margarine, cocoa and evaporated milk.
Remove from heat and add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Spread over cool cake.

title: polar bears
directions: Melt paraffin and white
chocolate
in	double	boiler, about 1/4 bar of paraffin
for
pound of white chocolate. Remove wrappers from caramels.
Soften
caramels in microwave. Flatten caramel and dip in	chocolate
to
coat
the bottom of each caramel piece.
Place 2
pecan
halves on top of caramel. Spoon white chocolate on top to cover pecans and caramel.

title: good hot mustard
directions: Mix in blender mustard and vinegar.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Combine in double boiler the honey and eggs. Add
the mustard
and
vinegar
mixture and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Store in refrigerator.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Let stand in cold water overnight.
Pack into hot jars.
To each quart add listed amounts of alum, garlic, dill and pepper.
Combine vinegar, salt and water.
Heat to boiling. Fill jars and seal.

title: hot mustard
directions: Cut ends off peppers and soak in salt water overnight.
Put peppers in processor and chop.
Mix sugar and flour in pan; put in vinegar and mustard.
Add peppers.
Stir often on medium heat. Bring to boil and keep stirring for 20 minutes.

title: five bean soup
directions: Simmer first 7 ingredients for 1 hour.
Add stewed tomatoes and then simmer 1/2 hour.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating between each egg.
Add alternately flour and evaporated milk, starting and ending with flour.
Line bottom of three greased loaf pans with wax paper.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: salmon souffle
directions: Make a white sauce with the butter, flour, milk and salt. Add salmon.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare brownies according to instructions.
Cool. Break into small pieces.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour cherries and peaches in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Pour dry cake mix on top; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until brown on top.

title: beef ball
directions: Chop onions and beef, and mix with other ingredients.
Mix well with hands and form into a ball.
Cover well with plastic wrap.
Chill and serve.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, 4x sugar, egg, walnuts, dates and fine coconut together with hands.
Shape into balls.
Melt paraffin wax in double boiler with chocolate chips.
Dip balls into chocolate. Place on cookie sheet lined with waxed paper and refrigerate.

title: punch recipe
directions: Mix ingredients and serve.

title: easy sugar-free pumpkin pie filling
directions: Prepare pudding according to package instructions.
Cook pumpkin, egg and spices until the mixture thickens (5 to 10 minutes).
Combine pudding and pumpkin.
Pour into pie shell.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine first six ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients; add this to dry ingredients and mix only until moistened.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until bread is a golden brown and tests done.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: microwave potatoes
directions: You will need a 2-quart covered casserole.

title: rosemary lemon grilled chicken
directions: Marinate overnight with following marinade.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all together and pour into a greased and floured 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost with your favorite icing.

title: holiday salad
directions: Pour hot water over jello and mix, then add pineapple.
Pour mixture into dish and congeal.

title: hello dolly bars
directions: Melt margarine directly in the 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Layer on top the graham cracker crumbs, coconut, chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour milk over it all.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Cool, then cut into squares.
Yield:
16 squares.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift flour, cocoa, sugar, soda and salt together in a bowl. Add shortening or oil, water and vinegar; mix well.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
This is a very soft cake, best frosted in the baking pan.
Use any frosting, or top with whipped cream.
Also good plain.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: In a medium saucepan, stir together sugar, cornstarch and flour.
Gradually stir in water.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat; cook and stir over medium heat for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir about 1 cup of the hot mixture into beaten egg yolks; pour yolk mixture into remaining hot mixture in saucepan.
Bring to a gentle boil; cook for 2 minutes more, stirring constantly.	Remove from heat; stir in butter and shredded lemon peel.
Slowly stir in 1/3 cup lemon juice.
Keep filling warm while preparing meringue.
For meringue, in a large mixing bowl, beat egg whites and one tsp. lemon juice. Beat with electric mixer on medium speed for about 1 minutes or until soft peaks form.
Gradually add 6 Tbsp. sugar, beating on high speed about 4 minutes or until stiff peaks form and sugar dissolves.	Pour warm filling into cooled crust.
Immediately spread meringue over filling, carefully sealing to edge of crust to prevent shrinkage.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.	Cool on a rack for 1 hr.
Chill 3 to 6 hours before serving.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and bananas.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Then stir in pecans.
Bake in a greased loaf pan at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: potato patties(makes 6 patties)
directions: In medium
saucepan,
bring water, butter and salt to a boil; remove from
heat.	Stir
in
milk and 1 1/2 cups flakes until moisture
is
absorbed.
Stir
in egg and chives.
Using 1/3 cup mixture
for
each,
shape	into
patties;	coat with remaining flakes.
In
large	skillet, brown patties in oil on both sides. Serve hot.

title: sour cream fruitcake
directions: Combine shortening and sugar; cream together. Add eggs, sour cream, milk, salt, baking powder and flavorings. Mix well. Add 2 c. flour; blend well; dust the nuts with the remaining cup of flour; add to batter. Mix into batter. Pour into large, greased and floured tube pan or 3 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.

title: tuna roll
directions: Mix well and chill.
Roll in parsley flakes and chopped pecans.

title: ground chuck casserole
directions: Cook ground chunk in large container until it changes color; add chili with beans and tomato sauce.
Cook a few seconds.
Stir good.
Put in three large baking pans.
Spread 1 layer of cheese over the tops.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and reserve broth.

When chicken is cool enough, remove all the skin and bones and tear the chicken into bite-size pieces or cook the chicken breast in a pan on top of the stove. Use a can of chicken broth and enough water to make the mixture moist.
Stir together the first 3 ingredients; add the chicken and broth.
Pour into a greased casserole and bake 45 minutes to an hour at 350°.
It should be a nice golden brown.

title: today's meat loaf
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Do not drain.
Mix into meat.
In skillet, saute onion and pepper in butter.
Add water.
Cover and cook for 5 minutes.
Add with meat along with remaining ingredients except bay leaves.
Mix well.
Shape into loaf.
Press bay leaves on top.
Place on rack in shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: old fashion dried apple cake
directions: Put egg in a large mixing bowl and beat well.
Add all the other ingredients, except flour.
Mix well, then add flour to make a very firm dough.
Put the dough out on a dough board which has been sprinkled with flour.
Knead with hands to make the dough smooth.
Pinch off a ball about the size of a small orange. Spread in bottom of 8-inch cake pan.
Repeat with other dough to make as many layers as you want.

title: tempt me truffles(no bake)
directions: Gradually add powdered sugar to cream cheese; mix well.
Add chocolate and vanilla; mix well.
Chill several hours.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in nuts, cocoa or powdered sugar.
Chill.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine soups and 1 can of milk. Layer:
chicken, approximately 1/4 of soup mixture, sliced cheese, 1/4 of soup mixture, cooked spaghetti and remainder of soup mixture.
Sprinkle Parmeasan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325° for glass pan or 350° for aluminum. Combine flour and sugar and cut in cold butter until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.
Press firmly in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; freeze in 9 x 13-inch pan. Cut in squares and garnish with pecans.

title: tuna cheese pie
directions: Cook onions in oleo.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease baking dish (8 x 8-inch).
Sprinkle tuna in bottom of dish.
Layer cheese and then onion over tuna.
Mix Bisquick, milk, eggs, salt and pepper until smooth.
Pour over tuna, cheese and onion.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Brown onion and celery in butter.
Add soup, broccoli and rice.
Cook on stove for 15 minutes.
Pour mixture into casserole dish; top with cheese.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: broken glass salad
directions: Make each package of Jell-O for salad (1 cup hot, 1/2 cup cold water), except lemon in separate square or rectangular containers. Mix the lemon Jell-O with 1 cup of boiling pineapple juice.
Let it cool and add to it 1 package Dream Whip prepared according to directions and let this set until firm in a square pan.
Cut each flavor of Jell-O, after it has become firm into 2-inch squares and arrange in a clear serving dish by combining in a checkerboard effect in layers.

title: deviled eggs with crab
directions: Thaw crabmeat or drain canned crabmeat.
Peel eggs and cut lengthwise.
Remove yolks, put in bowl and mash well.
Add celery, mayonnaise and the seven seasonings.
Add crabmeat and mix well.
Stuff eggs and chill before serving.

title: blueberry bran muffins
directions: Pour 2 cups boiling water over bran mixture.
Cool.
In a separate bowl, cream together sugar and Crisco.
Beat eggs and add.
Add flour and salt.
In a large bowl, stir buttermilk and soda together.
Add flour mixture and stir.
Add cooled bran mixture.
Batter may be kept covered in refrigerator for approximately 1 month or bake and freeze.
Add blueberries to each muffin before baking.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cranberry iced tea
directions: Pour cranberry juice cocktail and tea in a glass.
Add sugar; stir until dissolved. Add ice and garnish. Makes 1 serving.

title: pecan tea biscuits
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients together; cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Combine egg and milk; add all at once to dry mixture, stirring just to moisten.
Stir in pecans. Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheet.
Combine 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over.
Bake at 425° about 10 minutes.
Makes 36.

title: camp beans
directions: Wash, cover beans with 5 cups of water.
Soak 8 hours or overnight.
Then add 2 cups water, mustard, pepper and next 8 ingredients.
Boil, covered, about 1 hour or until skins of beans begin to wrinkle.

title: cheese cranberry bread
directions: Halve berries and set aside.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add berries and nuts to dry ingredients, coating well.
Combine milk, egg, orange rind and melted butter; add to dry ingredients along with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Stir only to moisten ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 5 x 3-inch buttered loaf pan and spread evenly, making corners and sides slightly higher than center.
Bake 1 hour or until done.
Turn out of pan and cool.
Bread slices more easily if stored overnight.
Bake in 350° oven.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring first four ingredients to boil.
Cook until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into buttered pans.

title: pickled squash
directions: *Or instead of pickling spice, can use 1 teaspoon celery seed and 1 teaspoon mustard seed.

title: aunt blanche's cookies
directions: Mix and divide into 2 batches.
Chill 2 hours.
Roll to 1/8-inch.
Cut.
Place on tinfoil lined pan.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: cherry jubilee
directions: Make a crust of graham cracker crumbs, butter and sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 325°.
Save a few crumbs to sprinkle on top. Cool crust, then add cherries, Dream Whip and cream cheese.
Mix Dream Whip just like on package.
Whip cream cheese separate.
Add 1 cup powdered sugar and whip with cream cheese.
Place cherries in the bottom of pie crust but save enough for the top of the mixture.

title: best ever chicken and dumplings
directions: In a large pot or skillet, melt butter.
Saute vegetables for 3 minutes.
Stir in flour.
Cook 1 min.
Add broth, chicken and spices.
Bring to a boil; then simmer for 5 min.
Tear biscuits in half.
Drop into broth.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes more.
No peeking.
Move dumpling gently and add Half and Half.
Serves 6.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan; add sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, mix well, add flour, nuts and cocoa.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 X 13 pan.
Bake for 30-35 at 325°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with one small pkg. marshmallows while hot; cover with the frosting immediatly.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Combine chicken, 6 ounces of the cheese and 1/4 cup bell pepper.
Separate the dough into 8 triangles, placing equal amounts of the mixture on each.
Roll corners (loosely) over top of mixture into a ball-like shape.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom

title: banana bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Slice the cucumbers very thin, place in glass bowl and sprinkle with salt.
Let stand 1 hour or longer.
Remove cucumbers from bowl.
Squeeze liquid out of cucumber; combine remaining ingredients and pour over cucumbers.
Mix and serve.
Serves 4.

title: peach pie
directions: Put melted butter in pan.
Pour peaches in pan.
Mix sugar and flour together. Add milk and eggs.
Pour over peaches.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: taco dip 1
directions: Combine cream cheese and taco seasoning mix in a medium size mixing bowl until well blended.
Spread on the bottom of a 1-quart casserole dish.
Top mixture with a layer of each of the following ingredients in the order listed: lettuce, tomatoes, cheese; pour taco sauce over the top.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: turkey tacos
directions: Brown the ground turkey.
Follow directions on mix package. Cut pita bread in half.
Fill bread with 2 tablespoons of meat mixture.
Let family top their own with remaining ingredients.

title: tasty noodle bake
directions: Brown beef then add onion and celery and cook 10 minutes.
Mix in the cooked noodles, tomatoes, cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: aunt sis macaroni
directions: Cook the macaroni and mix together with other ingredients. Crumble roll of crackers and sprinkle on top.
Melt 3 tablespoons of butter and pour over crackers.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° or until cheese is melted.

title: cauliflower-broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli and cauliflower.
(Note:
Be sure and just use the flowerets; any part of stem is hard and also looks unattractive.)

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Flatten chicken.
Saute onion, pepper and garlic in 2 tablespoons butter.
Stir in 2/3 cup stuffing, water, salt and pepper.
Spread stuffing mix on chicken breasts.
Fold; secure with toothpicks.
Brown chicken in 2 tablespoons butter.
Place on 9-inch pie plate.
Combine soup and wine.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon dressing.
Cover.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt together.
Add well-beaten egg yolks.
Add lemon and milk; mix well.
Fold in beaten egg whites. Set dish in pan of warm water.
Bake like custard for about 35 minutes at 350°.
This recipe forms a little light cake on top and a smooth delicious sauce underneath.
Serve cold with whipped cream or just plain.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Soften yeast in
water	which
has been placed in large mixing bowl.
Add	other ingredients.
Using a bread hook, mix for 8 minutes.
Let
rise
until double in bulk.	Likely 1 1/2 hours. Punch down.
Form
into
2	loaves	and place in bread pans.
Let rise until dough is above top of pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple coconut inside-out cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat cake mix, 1 package pudding mix, eggs, water and oil in large bowl with electric mixer on low speed 1 minute.
Beat on medium speed 4 minutes. With wooden spoon, stir in1 1/2 cups of coconut.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch round pans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean when inserted in cake.
Cool 15 minutes.
Pour milk into large bowl.
Add remaining package pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes or until thickened.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Mix 1 1/2 cups of the pudding mixture and pineapple.
Slice each cake layer in two, making 4 layers. Frost cake layers with pudding-pineapple mixture.
Frost top and sides of cake with remaining pudding mixture.
Press remaining coconut on top and sides of cake.
Refrigerate.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients, cutting in shortening.
Beat egg and add water and vinegar.
Mix with fork or hands.
Makes 2 (8-inch) double crusts.

title: turkey ala stew
directions: Combine broth, wine, lemon juice and mustard; set aside.
In nonstick skillet heat margarine and oil together until margarine is bubbly and mixture is hot.
Add turkey and saute, turning once, until lightly browned and cooked through 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove turkey and keep warm.
In same skillet saute almonds over heat, stirring frequently, until golden brown.
Thicken with flour; gradually add broth mixture.
Reduce heat and add capers and parsley and cook, stirring frequently, until mixture thickens, 4 to 5 minutes.
Pour almond mixture over turkey and serve immediately. Yield:
2 servings.
Carbohydrate 3 g, protein 28 g, fat 10 g, calories 230.
One serving = 3 protein exchange, 1 fat exchange.

title: grilled pork roast
directions: Marinate pork roast in lemon juice 3 to 4 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Place pork roast on aluminum foil and spread margarine all over it.
Sprinkle all over with lemon pepper.
Wrap roast in aluminum foil and place on grill.
Cook over medium heat for 45 minutes, turning every 15 minutes.
Remove foil and cook over low heat for 15 minutes more or until browned.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix according to directions.
Press into a greased 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Mix the cream cheese and 2 beaten eggs; add powdered sugar.
Mix until smooth.
Pour over bottom layer.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar; cut into squares.

title: shrimp bisque(cajun soup)
directions: Melt the butter and add the onion, pepper, celery and garlic. Cook gently to soften.
Stir in the mustard, cayenne, paprika and flour.
Cook about 3 minutes over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Pour on the stock gradually, stirring until well blended.
Add the thyme and bay leaf and bring to a boil.
Reduce the heat and simmer about 5 minutes or until thickened, stirring occasionally.
Add the shrimp and cook until pink and curled, about 5 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper to taste and top with snipped chives before serving.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring brown sugar, corn syrup, pecans and butter to boil. Simmer for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and stir in baking soda.
Pour mixture over popcorn; mix well.
Bake in a 250° oven for 1 hour; stir every 15 minutes.

title: walnut frosties
directions: Combine butter, brown sugar, egg and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Gradually add to sugar mixture.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Make a depression in center of each cookie.

title: skillet halupki
directions: Brown ground meat and onion in skillet.
Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook for 1-1/2 hours.
Let stand in steam until cabbage is tender.

title: original chex party mix(microwave recipe)
directions: Melt butter, salt and sauce in small bowl; mix well.
Pour cereal, nuts and pretzels into 2 gallon plastic bag.
Pour butter mixture over cereal mixture.
Seal top of bag and shake until evenly coated.
Pour bag contents into large bowl, microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes.
Spread on paper to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: asparagus bake
directions: Microwave frozen asparagus 3 minutes on High.
On 12-inch round microwave platter, arrange asparagus spears spoke fashion with tips to center.
Melt butter (1 tablespoon) and add to bread crumbs.
Set aside.
Sprinkle onion, celery and tomato pieces over asparagus, drizzle with remaining butter.
Sprinkle with basil and thyme.
Cover with plastic (vented); microwave 10 to 11 minutes, turning platter after 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and buttered crumbs.

title: fluffy fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: snappy party snacks
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In large bowl combine cereals and nuts with soup mix; then add butter and mix thoroughly.
Turn into shallow baking pan.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: jim's taco meat
directions: Separate meat so it is loose and brown in an uncovered deep 5-quart pot.
When browning is completed, drain juices into bowl. Put meat back into pot and add 5 to 6 teaspoons juices, discarding the rest.
Add all ingredients.
Mix well and, covering pot, cook over lowest heat possible, for 5 or more hours, stirring about 30 minutes.
After 4 hours, taste occasionally, and add more of whatever ingredients you want to highlight.

You should be aware however, that the longer you cook the mixture, the better the flavor develops and adding more of an ingredient is rarely needed. When done, put about 1 serving spoon of meat in each taco shell and top with whatever degree of "hot" taco sauce you desire.
I personally prefer a mild taco sauce such as La Victoria chili dip along with shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes and shredded Cheddar cheese or anything else you prefer.
If any meat is leftover, it may be frozen.
Makes 3 large tacos.

title: broccoli balls
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and drain.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Roll into balls.
Bake in 325° oven 20 to 30 minutes. Freeze well.

title: make-your-own christmas ornaments
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Use enough water until you have formed a ball.
Knead 10 minutes.
Use cookie cutters to make into shapes; don't forget to make holes at the top if you're planning to hang these from your Christmas tree.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer the ingredients.
Mix sugar and Hellmann's; layer that, then sprinkle the top with cheese.
Leave in fridge overnight.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and drain.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased baking dish 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook hamburger until it's brown.
Add onion, celery, green pepper, rice, tomatoes, sugar, salt and pepper.
Cook 15 minutes. Add cloves and cook on low for 1 hour in electric skillet or 1 hour at 350° in oven.
Stir once in a while and add extra water, if needed.

title: easy any fruit cobbler
directions: Empty pie filling into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Top with dry cake mix.
Melt margarine and drizzle over top of cake mix. Sprinkle spice on top.
Bake at 350° until pie filling bubbles.

title: mandarin orange congealed salad
directions: Drain juices and add water to make 4 cups.
Soften Knox gelatine in juice, then heat and add jello to dissolve.
Pour over fruit in 9 x 13-inch pan and congeal.

title: meat loaf
directions: Soak the onion soup in the tomato juice.
Slightly beat the eggs. Add to the hamburger and the oatmeal.
Add the soup mixture and mix.
Shape in loaf and bake for about 1 hour at 375°.

title: teriyaki potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes; scrub thoroughly.
Cut tiny new potatoes into quarters or the medium potatoes into 1-inch pieces.
Place potatoes in 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe casserole.
Add butter, teriyaki sauce, garlic salt, Italian seasoning and peppers.
Toss to combine.
Cover.

title: english scones for tea time
directions: Blend flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt with butter or margarine with fingers.
Sprinkle through raisins.
Mix together with buttermilk.
Save a little to brush tops.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick; cut into rounds.
Brush tops with milk.
Bake at 425° for 6 or 7 minutes.
Turn; bake approximately 3 minutes more. Serve with butter and jam if desired.

title: microwave corn pudding
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart microwavable bowl with top, put 1 can of corn.
Add flour and sugar; stir well.
Beat eggs and 1 1/2 cups of milk.
Pour into bowl with corn, flour and sugar.
While stirring, add 1 to 1 1/2 cups more milk and stir until all ingredients are mixed well.
Dot top with butter or margarine. Microwave in covered bowl for 7 minutes at Power 7.
Remove and stir well.
Return to microwave for 5 minutes at Power 10.
Turn midway 1/2 turn.
Remove and sprinkle top with paprika. Microwave 8 minutes more at Power 7.
Let set 5 minutes and serve warm.

title: fudge cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugars.
Add eggs and stir.
Add rest of ingredients and stir until well mixed (do not use mixer).
Spoon into 3 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Make a stiff dough.
Dissolve soda in water.
Roll out and cut in squares.
Bake in moderate oven. (Use all-purpose flour.)

title: pork chops with onions
directions: Trim excess fat from chops.
Place chops in skillet with about 1 tablespoon cooking oil.
Brown on both sides for about 5 minutes.
Remove chops from skillet and stir in onions for about 5 minutes.
Add water, rice, marjoram, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Return chops to skillet and cover.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and cook for 18 to 20 minutes or until tender.

title: buns burner chili
directions: In a cup, combine onion and garlic in 1/2 cup water.
Cook and drain sausage and ground chuck.
In large pot, mix all ingredients.
Simmer until well done, about 1 hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain each fruit separately. Combine juices or use the juice you like best with the instant pudding.
Add from 1 1/3 to 1 1/2 cups of juice to mix with the pudding.
Mix by hand. Fold in fruit, leaving bananas out until the day you plan to serve.

title: 1 minute pizza
directions: Spread 1 to 2 tablespoons pizza sauce on English muffin (squeeze bottle works well).
Top with 2 to 3 pepperoni slices (or other favorite topping).
Sprinkle with cheese.
Microwave on High until cheese melts.

title: mom's christmas candy
directions: Mix well sugar, milk, cherries and dates.
Cook until it forms a ball in water, then take from fire and add nuts.
Stir until impossible to stir.
Place on oiled cloth and let cool before cutting.

title: quick pineapple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: christmas fruit cookies
directions: Chop up nuts and fruit.
Mix with 1 cup flour; set aside.
Mix sugars, shortening, eggs and vanilla until smooth.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Mix.
Add fruit and nuts.
Roll into logs. Refrigerate overnight.
Slice and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: angel pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat in sugar.
Crush crackers and mix with baking powder and nuts. Fold this mixture into egg whites.
Add almond extract last.
Pour into greased and floured tin. Bake at 250° for 20 to 30 minutes. Serve with whipped cream.

title: german dipping sauce
directions: Heat jelly and peanut butter on High in microwave-safe 2-cup measuring bowl for one minute.
Stir and repeat.
Stir mix again until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and microwave at 50% power for 2 additional minutes.
Serve with Hillshire Farm 'Lil Smokies.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a large bowl mix pumpkin, sugar and oil, then add eggs, flour baking soda, vanilla, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
After all is blended, add chocolate chips.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet and bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Cool.

title: john's party dip
directions: Brown ground beef, drain and set aside.
In a crock-pot, place cheese, cut into 1-inch cubes and can of Ro-Tel.
heat until cheese is melted, then add seasonings and beef.
Turn crock-pot to low heat.
When thoroughly heated, serve with chips and vegetables.

title: grandma's baluchski
directions: Coarsely slice cabbage and onion.
Saute in butter until transparent.
(Can be steamed to reduce fat.)
Add sauerkraut and stir.
Cook bow ties in boiling water until just done.
Drain and mix with all other ingredients.
Can be served as a casserole or reheated in butter as a leftover.
Great with roast pork or sausage.

title: seafood risotto
directions: In frying pan, saute first 4 ingredients.
In larger frying pan, saute onion and garlic in olive oil.
Add dry rice and stir until lightly browned.
Add the next 4 ingredients, one at a time, and stir until absorbed by rice.
Add seafood.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add about 1/4 cup fresh chopped parsley.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour; add butter, eggs, buttermilk, vanilla and 2/3 of the coconut.
Pour into the shell.
Sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: broken glass salad
directions: Fix 3 flavors of gelatin as directed on the package the day before, except use 1 1/2 cups water to each package.
Put each flavor in a separate bowl to set.
When gelatin has set, cut into 1/2-inch cubes.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Mix butter with crushed Oreos (reserve 1/2 cup).
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with softened ice cream.
Freeze (approximately 2 hours).
Spread fudge on top.
Top with peanuts (if desired), then put Cool Whip.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup Oreo crumbs on top.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: layered crabmeat salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, green onions and mustard; set aside.
In a 3-quart serving bowl layer lettuce, shells, cucumber, tomatoes, crabmeat or tuna and peas.
Spread salad dressing mixture over top, sealing to edge of bowl.
Sprinkle with cheese and cover.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Toss and serve.
This is a wonderful "lite" meal, especially in the summer.

title: rio vista dressing
directions: Blend together and store in refrigerator.

title: golden potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes
Cool.
Peel and grate finely.
Heat butter with soup, then add to potatoes.
Next add sour cream, onions, cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Turn into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.

title: stovetop oriental hamburger casserole
directions: Mix cornstarch and water.
Stir all ingredients together in frying pan and sprinkle with soy sauce until vegetables are tender and crisp.
Stir in noodles and serve.

title: refrigerator potato rolls
directions: Scald milk and add shortening, potatoes, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add with the eggs to the potato mixture.
Stir in enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead lightly.
Place in greased bowl and let rise slightly, about an hour.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.

title: chicken can-can
directions: Grease large casserole with margarine.
Put rice on bottom. Next, put chicken, then peas and soups.
Mix minced onion and poultry seasoning with chicken broth and pour over all.
Top with French fried onion rings.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until good and bubbly.
Will serve 6 for a hearty meal.

title: okra medley(microwave)
directions: Place bacon pieces in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover with wax paper; microwave at High 5 minutes, or until crisp.
Remove bacon; discard drippings.
Crumble bacon; return to casserole.
Stir in okra and remaining ingredients.
Cover; microwave at High 10 minutes, stirring after 5 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: pink lady salad
directions: Combine dry jello and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Add next four ingredients (one at a time).
Refrigerate.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: cranberry jello
directions: Combine and refrigerate until set.

title: tuna mousse
directions: Soften gelatine in cold water.
Heat tomato soup, undiluted. Mash cream cheese, which has been softened at room temperature. Remove soup from heat; add gelatine mixture, then add cream cheese and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; put in blender and mix well.
Pour into 5 1/2 cup fish mold (grease with mayonnaise). Chill at least 2 hours.
Decorate with cucumber and olives.

title: new impossible pie
directions: Mix all together in blender for 3 minutes.
Pour into ungreased pie pan. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Fry
bacon
until crisp. Remove from frypan. Add onions, peppers and garlic to bacon drippings. Cook until just tender. Add tomatoes and shrimp. Cook until shrimp are done and sauce thickens.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix
together
milk,
mushroom	soup, sour cream, Cheez Whiz and
onion, stirring well. Add hash brown potato chunks. Bake
for
minutes.
Remove
from oven. Add corn flakes that have been tossed with butter and return to oven to brown.

title: cranberry relish
directions: First put all the fruit in a food processor and grind up into fine pieces.
When you have the fruit ground up then add 2 cups of sugar to it.
Stir and let sit.
Then add 2 cups of boiling water to the large package of strawberry jello.

title: chicken lentil chili
directions: In a Dutch oven, place lentils, chicken broth, water and salt. Bring to a boil over high heat.
Cover.
Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Simmer in 3 quarts water 1 1/2 hours; drain.
Meanwhile make the sauce.

title: ratatouille(vegetable stew)
directions: In a large frying pan over medium heat, combine oil, onion, pepper and garlic.
Cook, stirring until limp.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for about 35 minutes or until eggplant is very soft; stir occasionally.
Uncover and boil rapidly about 20 minutes, stirring often, until most liquid evaporates.
Salt and pepper to taste. Serve hot.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
(This recipe is from France.)

title: dockside salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain well. In a large bowl, combine spaghetti, peppers and onion.
Add salad dressing and toss to coat spaghetti and vegetables.
Sprinkle generously with paprika and stir well.
Add more paprika to give the mixture a red color.
Stir again.
Refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients except cucumbers.
Pour over cucumbers and stir once a day for 6 days.
Ready to eat.
Must be kept in refrigerator.
There won't be enough liquid to cover the cucumbers the first day.
Don't give up.
There will be more each day.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add beaten egg.
Mix thoroughly. Add butter, vinegar and water.
Cook over low heat, stir until thick and smooth.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Beat eggs until thick and foamy.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla; beat until thick and foamy.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Sift together dry ingredients and add.
Add walnuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° in greased and floured pan for approximately 1 hour or until tested done.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Mix sugars and water together.
Cook over medium heat to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add margarine, salt and vanilla. Beat until creamy and add pecans.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper. Cool.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Add brown
sugar
to
melted butter; cool.
Add egg and vanilla to mixture and blend well.	Add sifted dry ingredients gradually.	Stir
in
chopped nuts.
Pour mixture into 9 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut in squares while warm.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Cook noodles in broth; drain.
Saute onion in Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Melt cheese in a little milk.
Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Place noodles in casserole dish.
Pour half of the soup with milk over this.
Put tuna and rest of soup over that.
Cook 30 to 35 minutes at 400° or until noodles are done.

title: stewed okra
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, trim stems from okra.
Dice onion.
In 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat in hot olive or salad oil, cook onion until tender.
Stir okra, tossing to coat well.
Add tomatoes with their liquid, salt, sugar, pepper and 1/2 cup water over high heat; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 15 minutes or until okra is tender.
Makes 8 accompaniment servings.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni, then drain.
Mix all ingredients, except mayonnaise together.
Stir in mayonnaise until well mixed.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: himmel and erde(heaven and earth - a german dish)
directions: Cook potatoes in salt water, drain off most of water and add apples.
Cook until tender.
Mash the potatoes and apples, season with salt and pepper.
Add sugar and butter.
Slice the blutwurst and fry in the remaining butter until brown on each side.
To serve, arrange the fried sausage over the mashed potatoes and apples mixture.
