title: wisconsin dream bars
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread firmly onto bottom and sides of an ungreased 7 x 11 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix sugar and dry ingredients together.
Add oil and eggs; mix well.
Add buttermilk, nuts, prunes and vanilla; mix well.
Pour in greased tube pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: delicious squares
directions: Blend thoroughly margarine, white sugar and 1/2 cup of brown sugar.
Add egg yolks, water and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Spread batter in greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Cover with chocolate chips.
Make a meringue with the 2 egg whites, beaten stiff.
Add 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Spread this over the chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn heat down to 350° for 15 minutes more.
Cut while still warm.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain off fat and add taco mix and beans.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
In a large bowl add crunched Doritos or corn chips, lettuce, tomato, grated cheese and cooled meat.
Toss with Dorothy Lynch dressing.

title: chicken mushroom and mozzarella
directions: Roll serving size chicken breast.
Saute in 1 Tbsp. of olive oil.
Place in shallow casserole dish.
Put sliced mushrooms on top along with cheese slices.
Add 1/2 c. chicken broth or more. Bake at 350° for 20-30 minutes.

title: raspberry mold salad
directions: Mix and pour into mold or an 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Chill. Serve with whipped cream.

title: butterscotch crispies
directions: Cream together first 5 ingredients; beat in eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and stir into first mixture.
Add last 4 ingredients and mix well.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet about 10 minutes at 350°.
Equally good omitting chips and increasing coconut to 1 cup.

title: bailey's irish cream
directions: Combine all ingredients together and blend for 3 minutes. Allow to thicken in the refrigerator.

title: dessert n.o.s.
directions: Sprinkle macaroon crumbs with rum.
Stir to moisten evenly. Whip the cream.
Mix in the egg yolks, confectioners sugar, crumb-rum mix and bittersweet chocolate. Place in sherbet glasses or a 4 cup mold and chill.
This dessert can also be frozen.

title: six cup salad
directions: Combine all 6 ingredients and stir well until mixed.
Chill in freezer 10 to 15 minutes or chill in refrigerator longer before serving.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water, about 30 minutes or tender.
Chill.
Peel and grate potatoes.
Combine cheese, milk and 2 tablespoons butter in microwave until butter and cheese melt. Remove and stir in sour cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Fold cheese mixture into potatoes.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine and sugars.
Add oil and eggs, mixing well.
Blend the rest.
Dough may be covered and chilled to make handling easier.
Roll dough into walnut-sized balls and place on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Dip bottom of glass tumbler in granulated sugar and press each roll flat.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: fruity jello salad
directions: Mix all together and let set overnight.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar; blend in mashed bananas, eggs and vanilla.
Mix and add to flour, baking soda, salt and buttermilk mixture.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Bake at 325° until done.
Makes 2 loaves or 4 small loaves (takes 45 minutes for small loaves).

title: lemon lush dessert
directions: Mix margarine, flour and nuts.
Press firmly in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Cream together cheese and powdered sugar.
Spread over crust.
Beat pudding and milk; fold in 1 cup Cool Whip.
Pour over cream cheese.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Chill 3 or 4 hours or overnight.

title: marty's recipe for corn pudding
directions: Spray a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish with Pam.
Melt butter in dish.
Combine next 5 ingredients and beat in egg; mix altogether. Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes or check to see when done.

title: broccoli, cheese and rice
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
Also prepare broccoli to package directions.
Put rice and broccoli in a 13 x 9-inch baking/casserole dish.
Melt cheese and milk in saucepan or microwave.
Pour over broccoli and rice and salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until top is golden.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; mix well.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Pour over corn mixture. Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Drain before serving.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well and put into greased loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.
Cover top with additional catsup halfway through baking.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix eagle brand milk and cool whip on one bowl. Slice strawberries and mix with pie filling.
Break up cake.
Layer cake, strawberries and cool whip mix and top off with cool whip.

title: hot 'n spicy punch
directions: Combine all ingredients, except lemon juice; stir to dissolve sugar.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; strain to remove spices and add lemon juice.
Serve hot in punch cups or chill and serve over ice cubes.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: summer tomato sauce for pasta
directions: Place all ingredients in food processor and chop to desired thickness. Make during the day and let sit at room temperature. Serve over hot pasta.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Melt butter.
Add garlic, onions, lemon juice, salt and pepper, bay leaf and 1/2 of the 1/4 cup of wine.
Simmer for 10 minutes. Take out bay leaf.
Add shrimp and cook for 20 minutes on medium heat.
Remove from pan.
Put in dish.
Add rest of wine and chopped parsley.
Stir.
Serve over rice.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Stir milk and pineapple together in a bowl until well blended. Pour into a 4-quart ice cream freezer and add the 2 liter orange. Stir again, and it's ready to freeze.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift and mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Mix oil, sugar and eggs; mix well, then add carrots and mix.
Mix in all the dry ingredients, then add the pineapple, nuts and raisins.
Put in a 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Cream the cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Fold in whipped cream and put in graham cracker crust.
Cook sugar, flour, salt and cherry juice until clear.
Cool about 5 minutes.
Add cherries and butter.
Cool thoroughly.
Place thickened mixture on cream mixture.
Keep refrigerated.
Serves 6.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Mix next 5 ingredients well.
Add oatmeal.
Mix dry ingredients with Crisco mixture. Stir in raisins, if desired.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes. Do not overbake.
Cool and fill with white icing.

title: buttery pineapple yam bread
directions: Pulverize pecans in blender.
Cream sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Beat in undrained pineapple, yams and eggs until mixed.
Combine pulverized pecans with flour, soda, cinnamon and mace; beat into pineapple mixture until blended.
Stir in raisins.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes two loaves.

title: chicken divine
directions: Layer broccoli and chicken in a baking dish.
Mix butter and flour; heat and add milk and cheese.
Cook until thick; pour over chicken/broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Slice apples or other fruits, dip and enjoy.

title: sauce for macaroni
directions: Mix tomato soup, sugar, vinegar and oil very well.
Add the following to cooled and drained macaroni, celery, onion and eggs. Add peppers, sweet pickles and olives.

title: jambalaya
directions: Brown sausage in Dutch oven.
(Cube chicken and set aside.) Fry onion in oil; add flour and cook until brown.
Add water and all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then lower heat and cover. Raise lid occasionally to stir, but not too often.
Cook until rice is tender, 45 minutes.

title: cherry ambrosia(quick and delicious)
directions: Mix all together and serve.
Keep refrigerated.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly, then add all remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and Cool Whip in large bowl.
In separate bowl, mix pudding and milk.
Chop Oreo cookies in blender or food processor until fine like dirt.
Combine pudding and cream cheese mixtures together.
Layer large bowl or clay pot with one layer of pudding, then one layer of cookies and so on, until your last layer is layer of cookies.

title: old fashion cole slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss.
Chill for 1 hour before serving.
Toss before serving.

title: oh no dinner again!
directions: Smash the potatoes.
We make pasta and put spaghetti sauce on it.
You always watch the pasta tape.
Put 2 eggs in the measuring cup and put it in the pasta machine.
When it starts, you put more eggs in.
Then the pasta comes out and you put more eggs on.
We set the table and put food on it and we eat!

title: fried apple pies
directions: Cook apples and water until thick; add cinnamon and sugar. Make biscuit dough; work it out, then put some flour on wax paper. Roll out dough; cut up the size pies you want.
Add apples; close up, then fry in regular Crisco.

title: onion-cheese bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Saute onion in 2 Tbsp. margarine and allow to cool.
Mix Bisquick, 2 oz. cheese and eggs.
Add onion and milk.
Spread in a 9 x 13 pan.
Pour 1 stick melted margarine on top.
Sprinkle lightly with poppy seeds and remaining cheese. Bake until light brown, 20 - 30 minutes.

title: mock crayfish dip
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in oleo.
Add mushroom soup.
Heat 1/2 to 3 minutes.
Add 1 can tuna, flaked.
Add red pepper.
Heat 2 minutes more.

title: oli ole sauce
directions: Saute garlic, onion and basil in olive oil until transparent, but not brown.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with cooked tortellini, cavetelli or linguini.

title: mock oyster casserole
directions: Cook eggplant and onion in unsalted water until tender.
Drain thoroughly.
Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into buttered casserole and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: celebration punch
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a Punch Bowl. The color is festive, and the strawberries take the place of ice cubes.

title: nana's irish potato casserole(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water about 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain and mash.
Beat cream cheese with electric mixer until smooth.
Add potatoes and remaining ingredients except paprika; beat until well mixed.
Spoon mixture into lightly buttered 2-quart casserole; sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from fridge 15 minutes before baking.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: herbed cream cheese appetizer
directions: Combine cream cheese, chopped parsley leaves, grated Parmesan cheese, 2 tablespoons sour cream, chopped chives and black pepper. Mix well.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: classic date bars
directions: Combine dates and water in saucepan; bring to boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat to low and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 3 to 4 minutes or until thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla; reserve.
Combine oats, flour, brown sugar, baking soda and salt in bowl; mix well.
Stir in butter.
Spread 2 1/2 cups oat mixture in bottom of 9-inch square pan; press to make firm crust.
Top with date mixture.
Combine nuts and remaining oat mixture; sprinkle over top.
Gently press into filling.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 36 bars.

title: tomato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325° and grease a 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup bread crumbs evenly on bottom of pie plate.
Arrange half of tomatoes on bread crumbs and top with half onion.
Sprinkle half of cheese on top of onion.
Repeat layering with remaining tomatoes, onions and cheese.
Pour eggs over cheese and add salt and pepper to taste.
Top pie with remaining 1/2 cup of bread crumbs.
Arrange bacon on top of pie and bake on middle rack of oven 45 minutes or until bacon is crisp.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: vittles
directions: Place
graham
crackers
on
cookie sheet and set aside. Mix together
butter
and
brown sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and
cook
for 2 minutes.
Add pecans.
Spoon this mixture over graham crackers and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Store in a loose top container.

title: seasoned pretzels
directions: Mix all together and then stir in 1 bag of pretzels.
Let stand for 2 hours, stirring at intervals.
Place on baking sheet. Bake at 250° for 20 minutes.

title: italian potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes; cube.
Chop green peppers into medium pieces. Chop onion into fine pieces.
Prepare package of Seven Seas Italian dressing.

title: nana's manicotti
directions: Brown beef and onion and drain. Mix salt, garlic salt and oregano with egg and beat. Add to meat and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese. Stuff shells and place in pan. Mix tomatoes, tomato sauce and water. Pour over stuffed shells. Sprinkle rest of Parmesan cheese over top. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove and top with Mozzarella cheese. Re-cover. Cook for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: potato soup
directions: To water add potatoes and onion; cook until tender.
Add corn and milk.
Press down with potato masher a couple of times.
Add salt, pepper, cayenne pepper, chives and parsley to taste.
Add bacon or sprinkle some on top of each bowl as served.

title: barbecued meat balls
directions: Mix beef, milk and bread crumbs.
Make into balls and place in baking pan.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and cherries; save juice.
Combine marshmallows, pineapple and cherries.
Let stand for an hour or two.
In a saucepan, combine beaten egg, flour and juices; cook until thick.
Add vinegar and let cool.
Mix cooked dressing with whipped cream and marshmallow mixture.
Freeze.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: maw maw jean's babe ruth balls
directions: Melt butter.
Mix all together, except chocolate chips and paraffin.
Make balls.
Melt the chocolate chips and small amounts of paraffin.
Dip balls and cool.

title: pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Dissolve yeast in water.
Add honey and salt.
Add flour.
Knead, roll, play and have fun with dough on wax paper until you're ready to cook.
You can make shapes or letters.
Brush with beaten egg.
Sprinkle with salt (coarse) and bake for 10 minutes at 425°.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and drain mushrooms; remove stems and reserve caps.
Chop stems to make 1 cup.
In medium saucepan, cook stems, onion and garlic in margarine until tender.
Stir in bread crumbs and cheese.
Spoon mixture into mushroom caps.
Arrange mushrooms in 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes or until hot and bubbly and heated through.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mash potatoes; add sugar.
Melt margarine; add.
Beat eggs. Add condensed milk and flavoring.
Pour into two 9-inch pie crusts, unbaked.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream salad
directions: Place in strainer the mandarin oranges and pineapple.
In large bowl, mix coconut, sour cream and marshmallows.
Add pineapple and oranges.
Refrigerate, covered, overnight.

title: waldorf coleslaw
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and sugar.
Toss with remaining ingredients.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: golden granola
directions: Combine all ingredients except raisins in ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Mix well.
Bake in preheated moderate oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown, stirring occasionally; stir in raisins.
Cool thoroughly.
Store in tightly covered container in cool, dry place or in refrigerator.
Serve as cereal with milk or as a snack.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: broccoli rice
directions: Boil broccoli until tender.
In saucepan, combine cheese and cream of chicken soup, then add rice. Mix thoroughly and serve.

title: recipe for growing fine dahlias
directions: I have heard of many different "only" ways to grow Dahlias but in truth any one can raise beautiful Dahlias by using a little common sense and investing an amount of effort commensurate with their ambition.

title: radish dip
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Then add radishes and onions and chill.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: soft taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
When almost done, add green onion. Drain.
Add chilies, soup and sauce.
Mix well.
Butter bottom of casserole dish.
Layer with tortillas, meat mixture and cheese. Bake in oven until bubbly.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook oats 2 1/2 minutes.
Sift flour before measuring.
Mix all dry ingredients, except sugar.
Melt shortening and mix thoroughly with brown sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Pour in milk, then dry ingredients.
Drop on greased pan; bake in hot oven at 450°.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Makes 36 cookies.

title: punch
directions: Mix Jell-O by regular instructions, then pour in pineapple juice, orange juice and lemonade.
Freeze.
When ready to serve, pour in ginger ale.

title: evelyn harlow's brunch casserole
directions: Crumble sausage in skillet; cook and stir over medium heat until brown.
Drain well.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish with rolls, firming, pressing perforations to seal.
Sprinkle with sausage, then cheese.
Combine and beat remaining ingredients; pour over sausage and cheese.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve immediately.
Good served with fruit salad and blueberry muffins.

title: twinkie delight
directions: Cut Twinkies down middle lengthwise and place in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Drain pineapple very well; spread over Twinkies. Slice banana and lay over pineapple.
Mix pudding according to box.
Allow to thicken.
Pour over bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip. Sprinkle on pecans.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Flake salmon, discarding bones.
In bowl, combine salmon, crumbs, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Combine milk and egg. Add to salmon mixture and mix well.
Shape into loaf pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin ribbon bread
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and flour together in a small bowl. Add egg and mix to blend.
Stir in orange peel and set aside.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Cook in water, flavored by the bouillon cube, the egg noodles. Brown the garlic, onion and hamburger.
Add the flour, salt, paprika and mushrooms. Stir and let cook for 5 minutes. Stir in the sour cream over low heat and heat well. Serve over the noodles or mix all together.

title: greek salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and let sit at least 2 days before serving.

title: salmon ball
directions: Drain and flake salmon, removing all skin and bones.
Combine salmon, cream cheese, lemon juice, onion, horseradish, salt and pepper; mix thoroughly.
Chill several hours or overnight. Combine pecans and parsley.
Shape the salmon mix into a ball or log and roll in the nut mixture.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: easy artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichokes coarsely.
Combine all ingredients.
This dip can be served warm or cold.

title: summer baked beans
directions: Mix last 5 ingredients together.
Blend well and pour over beans in large mixing bowl.
Add chopped pepper and onion.
Stir until well blended.
Pour in casserole dish.
Top with bacon. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown hamburger meat, then drain.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Simmer on low heat until done.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into a sheet cake pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool completely and frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: * hamburger heaven *
directions: Saute first 3 items in oil until soft.
Add hamburger; stir and fry until color is gone.
Stir in tomatoes.
Add next 5 items, laying noodles on top.
Put cheese over all.
Cover with tight lid.
When mixture boils, stir noodles until completely moist. Cover and simmer until noodles are done, about 20 minutes.

title: dutch pancake
directions: Use a deep cast-iron pan, 2 to 3-quarts.
Put butter or margarine in the pan and put into a 425° oven to melt butter.
Put eggs in an electric blender and whirl at high speed for 1 minute. While motor is running, gradually pour in milk, then slowly add flour and continue mixing for 30 seconds.
Remove pan from oven and pour batter into the hot melted butter.
Return to the oven and bake until puffy and well browned, 20 to 25 minutes at 425°.
Serve hot topped with fresh lemon juice and powdered sugar.
Makes 3 to 6 servings.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 10 x 15-inch pan and line with wax paper.
(If possible, use a 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.) Cream eggs and sugar together.
Mix pumpkin, lemon juice and dry ingredients together and then add to egg-sugar mixture.
Spread on greased and waxed paper-lined jelly roll pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Cool 15 minutes on towel.
Mix cream cheese, margarine, powdered sugar and vanilla together and spread on cooled cake. Roll cake over filling until a log is formed.
Slice into 1/2 to 1-inch slices.

title: taco casserole
directions: Layer crescent rolls in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add a small portion of crushed Doritos (push into the crescent rolls). Brown hamburger, add seasoning mix, 1/2 cup water and sour cream. Put on top of crescent rolls.
Put layer of cheese, then layer of Doritos.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with lettuce, tomatoes and onion.

title: sweet hush puppies
directions: In a heavy 2-quart pan, over medium heat, combine water and margarine.
Bring to a boil.
Blend cornmeal, sugar, salt, baking powder and green onion in large bowl.
Stir boiling water mixture into cornmeal mixture until all ingredients are moist. Let mixture stand until cool enough to handle.
Heat 3 inches oil to 350° or until a 1-inch bread cube turns golden brown in 65 seconds.
Form dough into 2-inch ovals by rolling between palms of hands.
Add 3 or 4
at a time to hot oil; don't crowd.
Cook, turning once.
Cook about 2 minutes.
Drain on paper towels. Repeat until all batter is used.
Serve hot.
Makes about 32 hush puppies.

title: lime zested salmon(makes 4 servings.)
directions: Place salmon in an 8-inch square baking dish.
Combine onions and next 6 ingredients; stir well.
Pour over salmon.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, at 450° for 15 minutes or until salmon flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Serve with mango wedges.
Contains 236 calories per serving.

title: beef roll
directions: Dice the beef and put 1/2 in with cheese roll in other half.

title: fruit ball
directions: Drain fruit real well.
Mix together all ingredients.
Form into a ball.
Roll in nuts.
Spread on cinnamon graham crackers.

title: romme grot
directions: Put cream in a heavy kettle and bring to a boil. Stir constantly.
Boil hard for 3 minutes and then add 2/3 of the flour slowly, stirring vigorously.
Remove from burner and keep stirring until butter forms.
Remove butter and keep for serving.

If butter does not come, you may have to put kettle back on burner and heat slightly, stirring constantly. When you have removed all the butter possible, return kettle to stove and add the remaining flour. After this has been stirred in well, you add scalded milk, gradually.
Stir vigorously again as you keep adding scalding milk until mixture is the desired consistency.
Serve with drawn butter, sugar and cinnamon.

title: milky way cake(pound)
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine with Milky Ways.
Set aside to cool. Cream sugar and 1 stick margarine until fluffy.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating after each.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Mix Milky Ways to egg mixture.
Add dry ingredients and buttermilk.
Mix well. Add nuts.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chinese beets
directions: If you want to make less, divide everything by three.
Use a large shallow pan.
Add all ingredients.
Discard all juice you don't need.
Cut all beets into bite size and dump into pan.
Cook over medium heat for 3 minutes.
Stir all the time until mixture thickens. That's it.
Keeps well in the fridge for salads.
Good hot or cold.

title: day before fruit salad
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients over hot water until thick.
Remove from heat; add 2 tablespoons oleo.
Let cool.
When cool, mix all fruit, then combine with sauce.
Mix whipped cream with 2 tablespoons sugar and fold into fruit mixture.
Mix well before serving the next day.

title: cappuccino cheese cake
directions: Combine nuts, 2 tablespoons sugar and margarine.
Press into nine-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and flour, mixing at medium speed on an electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each.
Blend in sour cream.
Dissolve coffee and cinnamon in 1/4 cup boiling water.
Add to cream cheese mixture; mix well and pour over crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce temperature to 250° and continue baking 1 hour; loosen cake from rim of pan.
Cool before removing from pan.
Chill; garnish with whipped cream and coffee beans.

title: bernice's lemon sauce
directions: Mix sugar and flour, then add enough of the water to make a thick paste.
Add egg and mix well.
Add the rest of the water and the juice.
Cook over medium or low heat until thick, stirring almost constantly.
Pour over bananas that are sliced into serving pieces.
(I use 2 level tablespoons flour; it cooks quicker.
Also, I add 1/2 teaspoon lemon flavoring or more.)
Serve with sliced bananas.
Do not cut bananas until ready to serve.
Sauce can be kept in refrigerator for a long time.

title: pineapple cream cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions on box in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool; cover with pudding (mixed with milk as stated on box). Over pudding, cover with pineapple.
Sprinkle with shredded coconut.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over top. Refrigerate overnight.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Cook and stir beef (chicken) and onion until brown. Drain. Spread 1/2 cup salsa in bottom of ungreased square 8 x
8 x 2-inch baking dish.

Mix remaining salsa, sour cream, soup and pimentos. Layer half of the tortilla strips, beef mixture, soup mixture and cheese. Repeat layers. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven until casserole is hot and bubbly, about 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes. Garnish with olives.

title: apple crisp
directions: Sprinkle white sugar over apples.
Mix brown sugar, butter and flour; sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until set in middle and slightly brown.

title: reilly rice
directions: Saute tofu or brown meat.
Saute onion, peppers and garlic; add to tofu.
Drain meat and add to vegetables.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Put bread cubes in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle sausage and cheese over bread cubes.
Mix eggs, onion, mustard and milk.
Pour over sausage, bread and cheese.
Put mushrooms on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake in a 325° oven, uncovered, for 45 minutes.

title: chicken debra
directions: Dice chicken breast; saute in lemon juice until white. Drain. Cook macaroni. Drain.
Mix in bowl macaroni, cooked broccoli (drained), cream of chicken soup and cheese. Mix in chicken. Put into casserole dish. Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: cheesy cream of broccoli microwave soup
directions: Mix broccoli, celery and onion in 2 1/2-quart glass dish. Microwave on High for 6 minutes, stirring once.
Process cottage cheese in blender until smooth.
Add milk and soup gradually, processing until smooth.
Stir into broccoli mixture.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes or until heated to serving temperature; do not boil.
Add salt and pepper.
Yields 6 servings, 7 g fat.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Mix together all ingredients.
Pour in greased and floured pan.
Bake until done.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: ham and egg breakfast casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs and add milk. Mix well. Gradually add biscuit mix. Stir in ham, chilies and cheese. Pour into buttered 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake for 1 hour or until done.

title: banana fritters from thailand
directions: Heat butter in pan until it bubbles.
Add bananas.
Fry on all sides until golden and soft.
Add sugar and stir until it is dissolved and syrupy.
Mix to coat the bananas.
Sprinkle with lime juice and serve immediately.
Delicious over vanilla ice cream.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in heavy pan and cook to soft ball stage (234° to 238°).
Remove from stove.
Add peanut butter, marshmallows and vanilla.
Mix well, cool and beat, then pour into buttered pan.
Allow to set completely before cutting.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix milk, eggs, sugar, syrup, salt, vanilla and lard or corn oil.
Spread nuts in bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 340° for 1 hour or until done.
(Will be a little firm.
The nuts will be medium brown.)

title: strawberry cooler
directions: Puree 2 cups of strawberries in blender or processor.
Add water, sugar, juice and rind; blend well.
Chill and pour into cups.
Garnish with berries.
Yields 4 servings.

title: magic fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients, except for fruit, and pour in pan on top of butter.
Add fruit on top of mixture.
Do not stir.
Add 1 cup sugar on top of fruit.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add soup, chicken, green sauce and sour cream; mix well.

title: apricot upside down cake
directions: Melt butter in an 8 X 8 baking pan.
When melted add the brown sugar.
Return to oven for sugar to melt in butter.
Add apricots with hollows up.
In a bowl, beat egg yolks, Add sugar and juice.	Add flour sifted with baking powder.
Fold in beaten egg whites last.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate caramelita bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: rhubarb applesauce
directions: Trim the rhubarb and cut it into chunks.
Peel and core the apples and cut them into chunks.
Combine the rhubarb and the apples with sugar in a large pot.
Simmer over medium-low heat until the fruit is soft, 20 to 25 minutes.
Stir in the nutmeg. Serve the applesauce warm, room temperature or cold.

title: sunny autumn cider(microwave)
directions: Combine all ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Heat, covered, on full power for 8 to 10 minutes or until boiling. Continue heating, covered, on cook level 4 for 10 minutes or until mixture has simmered and flavors are blended.
Stir halfway through heating time.
Remove spice.
Serve warm.

title: sweet taters and apples from the ozarks
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake potatoes in skins 1 hour or until tender.
Remove from oven and reduce oven to 350°.
When potatoes are cool enough to handle, peel and cut into 1/2-inch slices. Peel, core and slice apples.
Layer apples and potatoes alternately in 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan, scattering melted butter, brown sugar and nutmeg over each layer.
Cover with foil and bake 30 to 35 minutes until bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: mutabel(called in arabic)(serve as appetizer.)
directions: Grill eggplant or bake for 30 minutes or until it is very tender from inside.
Peel off skin while hot, remove stem and end of eggplant.
Mix lemon juice, garlic, tahini and salt until it's pureed.
Chop eggplant until pureed.
Mix eggplant with lemon-garlic mixture.
Put in a shallow dish.
Garnish with parsley.
Spread olive oil on top.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: taco tartlets
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine beef, taco seasoning and 2 tablespoons cold water.
Press about 2 teaspoons mixture in bottom and sides of 36 muffin cup pans to make shells.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and cottage cheese, sprinkle with Jello.
Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: In large bowl, combine onions and two cans of soup.
In a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan (glass works best) add 4 cups of potatoes and season with salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 of the soup mixture, top with remaining potatoes, then add balance of soup mixture.
Cover pan with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for one hour (consistency will be soupy).
Uncover and bake 30 to 45 minutes longer.
Let stand about 10 minutes before serving.

title: mom's beef stew
directions: Coat chunks (your desired size) of stew meat in flour and brown in approximately 2 tablespoons canola oil.
Add remaining ingredients in order given.
Stir to combine.
Cover.
Simmer (don't boil) for 2 hours.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking. Remove bay leaves and garlic.
Add carrots, potatoes and onion. Cover and cook 30 minutes more until vegetables are cooked.
May thicken with flour, if desired.

title: ann's chicken
directions: Soak chicken in beaten eggs overnight in refrigerator.
Roll in bread crumbs; refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Fry chicken in oil and margarine until brown.
Place chicken in an 11 x 14-inch glass or Corning Ware baking dish.
Add flour to fat in pan; stir gradually.
Add broth and wine; stir well until slightly thickened.
Add mushrooms.
Pour over chicken.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven; place cheese on chicken.
Bake an additional 8 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: christmas fruit and nut bread recipe
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.

title: frito bean salad
directions: Drain and rinse beans.
Mix beans, dressing, tomatoes and onion; do not mix Fritos in until ready to serve.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs on high speed for 5 minutes; gradually add sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice. In a small bowl, mix flour, cinnamon, baking powder, ginger, salt and nutmeg. Fold into the pumpkin mixture. Spread batter in a greased and floured 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan. Sprinkle walnuts and bake in a 375° oven for 15 minutes. Immediately invert cake onto wax paper, sprinkled with powdered sugar. Roll cake jelly roll style, starting from short side. Cool completely.

title: beef brisket
directions: Place brisket in a big piece of heavy foil.
Sprinkle onion soup mix on top.
Mix the other ingredients and pour over brisket. Seal in foil.
Put in covered roaster.
Bake at 300° for 3 1/2 to 4 hours without looking at it.
Take out and slice.

title: blackberry syrup
directions: Simmer berries over low heat. Strain for juice. Cool. (Should make 2 cups juice.) Combine the juice, sugar and Karo syrup. Stir until dissolved. Boil 15 to 20 minutes, stirring once in a while. Put in jars. Refrigerate.

title: crumb top apple pie
directions: Place sliced apples into oblong pan; sprinkle with sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon and cold water.
In separate bowl, combine 1 stick butter, brown sugar, flour and salt.
Mix with fingertips and sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Serve hot or cold with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: mini blinnies
directions: Trim the crusts from the bread; roll flat. Blend until smooth the egg yolk, 1/4 cup sugar and cream cheese. Spread on bread and roll up. Cut to make two. Dip in melted butter (melt about 1 1/2 sticks) and roll in 1 cup sugar with cinnamon. Freeze. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, seam side down.

title: irish stew
directions: Place flour and salt in a plastic bag.
Shake.
Cut meat in 2-inch pieces.
Add to mixture in the bag and shake well.
Brown flour coated meat in bacon drippings and oil in a large pot.
Add more oil if necessary.
Add the water, vegetables and seasonings to the browned meat.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer about an hour.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Clean and slice berries; put milk in bowl and add lemon juice. Stir until thick.
Add berries.
Fold in stiff beaten egg whites. Line dish with cookies.
Put layer of berry filling and layer of cookies until dish is full.
Chill and serve.

title: low calorie chicken orientale
directions: Place the chicken pieces, skin side up, in a shallow baking dish.
Surround with pineapple chunks.
Mix juice with vinegar, soy sauce, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, in moderate oven (325°) for 40 minutes, basting occasionally.
Add pepper strips.
Combine cornstarch with water in a cup.
Stir into liquid in baking dish and bake an additional 15 minutes or until thickened and bubbly.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
Makes 6 servings at 248 calories each.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, chopped onion and chopped green pepper. Drain oil.
Stir in taco seasoning, drained corn and kidney beans. Add sherry, Old Bay to taste and garlic powder to taste.
Serve hot with taco chips.
Top with cheese if you like.

title: strudel
directions: Soften butter and cream cheese.
Mix all of the ingredients and chill in the refrigerator after making dough into 2 balls. After dough is chilled, roll out and spread 2/3 strawberry preserves.
Sprinkle on raisins and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pizza pie
directions: Cook hamburger until crumbly; drain and mix with sauce, onion, mushrooms, etc., and simmer.
Make bottom crust with 1 can rolls pressed into 9-inch round or square pan, pressing seams shut.
Add mix; put cheese on top.
Put 2nd can of rolls on top; pinch seams. Shut and press edges together like pie.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes until golden.

title: oriental rice
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Saute onions and mushrooms until tender, but not browned.
Add a little soy sauce and black pepper to taste.
Add cooked rice and toss to mix, adding additional soy sauce to taste.
Serve hot.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: corn fritters
directions: Drain liquid from corn.
Add eggs, flour, baking powder and nutmeg to corn.
Mix well.
Melt butter in a heavy skillet.
When hot, add the corn batter by tablespoons; brown on both sides.

title: sausage stew
directions: Put all ingredients into stew kettle.
Cut sausage into small pieces and add.
Cover with water and bring to a boil.
Simmer until potatoes are done.

title: ham bake
directions: Butter bread on both sides.
Beat eggs well and blend in milk. Dip bread slices in milk mixture (saturate) and place 1 layer in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover bread layer with half of the cheese and all of the ham, spread evenly.
Cover with another layer of bread slices, buttered and dipped as before.
Cover with remaining cheese.
Pour rest of egg-milk mixture over top.
Refrigerate 1 hour before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry-pretzel stuff(can be used as a salad or dessert)
directions: Break pretzels and roll to about nut size.
Melt margarine and mix with pretzels and 1 tablespoon of sugar.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: charlotte's chili
directions: Brown ground chuck and onions.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients in a large pot.
Simmer for 1 hour for full flavor.
Top with shredded cheese and serve.

title: roman chocolate fudge
directions: In heavy pot, mix sugar, Karo syrup, peanut butter, milk and chocolate.
Boil 6 minutes, stirring often.
Remove from stove and beat well.
Add nuts and butter; beat.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13 inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Put strawberries in baked pie shell.
In saucepan, put sugar, white corn syrup, cornstarch, water and salt.
Cook until thick and clear.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Add 2 tablespoons strawberry jello and some red food coloring.
Let cool a little more, then pour over berries and chill.
Serve topped with whipped cream, if desired.

title: mongolian beef
directions: Cut meat across the grain into thin slices, 2-inches long. Combine soy sauce, 1 tablespoon cornstarch, sugar, salt, cooking wine, pepper, cooking oil and egg in medium glass or plastic bowl; beat lightly with a fork.
Mix in meat.
Let stand 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in peanut butter and sugar.
Slowly add milk, blending thoroughly into mixture.
Fold topping into mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with chopped peanuts.
Freeze until firm and serve.

title: butter brickle
directions: Cream margarine and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Mix flour, salt and soda in separate bowl and add to egg mixture slowly until well mixed.
Add pecans and butter brickles.
Press into greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes or until done.
Cool and cut into squares.
Use 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Heat oven to 350°.

title: golden chex mix
directions: Combine in a large bowl Golden Grahams, Corn Chex, Rice Chex and peanuts.
Combine butter, peanut butter and cinnamon.
Pour over cereal mixture; spread in on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Then add raisins.
Let stand 2 hours.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump cake mix over pineapple and cherry mixture (do not stir). Slice the butter over the mixture.
Place chopped nuts or coconut on top of butter.
Use a long Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Test occasionally or watch closely.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread on cooked crescent crust. Top with veggies of your choice and shredded cheese.

title: cheese crisps
directions: Melt margarine; stir in grated cheese until the cheese melts. Cool.
Add flour and mix well.
Add Rice Krispies and red pepper. Mix well and shape into small balls.
Pat out flat and bake on ungreased baking sheet at 275° for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Do not brown.

title: turkey (chicken) mac(low-fat)
directions: Brown turkey and onion; salt and pepper.
Add all ingredients, except macaroni and peppers.
Cook macaroni; drain.
Mix with turkey mixture.
Chop peppers and mix well.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: blue cheese ball
directions: Mix well and place on waxed paper.
Form into ball; roll in parsley.
Refrigerate.

title: florentine crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Thaw and drain spinach.
Mix together spinach, cheese, crumbs and bacon.
Heat until cheese melts. Unroll dough.
Separate into 16 triangles.
Cut each triangle in half lengthwise.
Spread each with spinach mixture; roll, starting at large side.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Brush with beaten egg.
Bake for 11 to 13 minutes.

title: thistle dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.	Serve cold with tostada or potato chips.

title: continental chicken
directions: Line 13 x 9-inch pan with dried beef; set aside.
Roll chicken into rolls and wrap with half slices of bacon.
Secure with toothpicks.
Place rolled chicken in pan with dried beef.
Combine sour cream and mushroom soup and spoon over chicken breasts.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours.

title: chicken curry(serves 6)
directions: Melt the butter in a saucepan and add the onion, garlic, celery and apple.
Cook, stirring often for 5 minutes.
Blend the flour, curry powder and mustard and sprinkle it over the vegetables, stirring.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Brown chicken breasts; set aside.
Partially cook rice.
Put soup into pan that chicken was fried in.
Add enough water to make it real thin.
Drain partially cooked rice and add to soup.
Place chicken breasts on top.
Cover and cook on low heat until rice has absorbed liquid.
Serves 4.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Let cool and take meat off bones. Place in pot; add 2 quarts water.
Add salt, pepper and garlic. Add to chicken.
Cut tomato in small pieces and add.
Brown 3 tablespoons flour in 1/2 cup Crisco.
Add.
Let cook about 5 minutes.

title: bro. kevin's grilled cheese sandwich
directions: Heat skillet to medium-high, then add butter and stir with spatula.
When butter is almost gone, add bread with cheese in the middle.
Slide around to soak up butter and keep from sticking. Cook on that side until golden brown, then take up sandwich.
Add another teaspoon of butter for other side.
Then repeat process. Some people like to squish the sandwich flat when done.
Then serve with dill pickles and eat while it is still warm.

title: pistachio sundae pie
directions: Spread the chocolate chips in the bottom of the pie shell. Layer the nuts on next. Prepare the pudding mix as directed and pour into the pie shell.
Let firm up in the refrigerator for a half hour.
Top with whipping topping.
Sprinkle with candy bar pieces.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate.

title: 7 cup salad
directions: Mix together and chill for several hours.
Serve on lettuce with mayonnaise or favorite dressing.
Serves 12.

title: spinach ravioli
directions: Place wonton wrappers under moist towel.
Place all other ingredients, except egg, into food processor.
Place one wonton wrapper on board, top with 1 to 2 teaspoons spinach/cheese mixture. Brush edges of wonton with egg.
Top with another wonton and seal edges by pressing them firmly together.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Serve with sauce of choice.

title: company best beet pickles
directions: Combine all but the beets in large kettle. Let boil slowly for a few minutes. Add drained beets. Bring to boil again and put in sterilized jars. Seal. Will make about 6 pints.

title: easy key lime pie
directions: Beat lime juice and condensed milk.
Add Cool Whip and pour into a graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and milk until smooth.
Fold in Dream Whip and chill.
Serve with fruit.

title: burrito burgers on the grill
directions: Combine beans, 2 tablespoons of chili peppers, onion and 3/4 teaspoon salt.
Add beef; mix well.
Form into eight 5-inch patties.
Cut cheese slices in half.
Place 1/2 cheese slice on each beef patty.
Fold to seal cheese inside.
Grill over medium coals 5 to 6 minutes.
Turn and grill 4 to 5 minutes more.
Heat tortillas on grill.
Serve burgers in hot tortillas.
Add the lettuce, tomatoes and remaining chili peppers as desired.

title: dijon chicken
directions: Place
each
piece of chicken between 2 sheets of waxed paper and
flatten
using a meat mallet or rolling pin.
Heat oil
in large
skillet
over medium-high heat until hot.
Add chicken
to skillet;
cook
3 to 4 minutes on each side until lightly browned.
Remove from skillet and set aside.
Combine chicken broth,
wine, mushrooms, 2 tablespoons parsley, onion and
pepper in a skillet.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Remove chicken
and vegetables to a plate using a slotted spoon; keep warm.
Cook broth mixture over medium-high heat until sauce is reduced
to about 1/2 cup.
Remove from heat; stir in 2 tablespoons
parsley and
Dijon
mustard with a wire whisk.
Spoon sauce over chicken. Serve warm.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
Press into bottom of greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the powdered sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs.
Beat for 5 minutes.
Pour over top.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: fish souffle(fiskegrateng)
directions: Flake fish and dice potatoes small.
Add cream to fish and potatoes.
Add 2 slightly beaten egg yolks, salt and pepper.
Whip the egg whites, then fold into mixture.
Blend well.
Put in buttered baking dish; sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400° or until a knife comes out dry.
Pour melted butter and parsley over and serve from the baking dish.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble into small pieces. Using only the flowerette and most tender stem sections of the broccoli, chop into very tiny pieces.
Peel the red onion and finely chop.
In a bowl, combine broccoli, onion, celery and raisins.

title: petite cheese cake
directions: Beat together cheese, sugar, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Line small muffin pans.
Place a vanilla wafer in bottom of each.
Fill cups 2/3 full of cheese mixture. Bake at 375° until set, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Yields 24.

title: uncle max's barbecued chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken in large ovenproof baking pan with high sides.
Add chicken, turning to coat well. Marinate chicken overnight, or at least for 6 hours, turning occasionally.
Bake chicken in marinade at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until nearly done.
Transfer to hot charcoal barbecue. Grill chicken while turning and basting with marinade until completely cooked.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill for at least one hour. Spread on flat flour tortilla and tightly roll.
Slice jelly roll style.
Serve with salsa.

title: melt in your mouth pumpkin bread
directions: Mix oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Combine remaining ingredients and add pumpkin mixture.
Makes 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaves or 3 smaller ones.
Can also make muffins.
Grease pans well and bake at 325° about 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Check center.
Can freeze.

title: green rice
directions: Pour boiling water over chopped broccoli.
Cook 5 minutes; drain.
Saute onion and celery in margarine until tender.
Add mushroom soup and Cheez Whiz to broccoli.
Add cooked rice, celery and onion.
Pour mixture into greased casserole dish.
Cover and cook in 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: carma's rum cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, salad oil, 1/2 cup water and 1/2 cup rum together for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: french onion soup
directions: In a large skillet, saute onions in butter until crisp-tender. Transfer to an ungreased 5-quart slow cooker. Add the broth, Worcestershire sauce and bay leaves. Cover and cook on low for 5 to 7 hours or until the onions are tender. Discard bay leaves. Top each serving with French bread and cheeses.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: chuck wagon mac
directions: Prepare
Kraft	dinner	as
directed.
Brown meat.
Add celery, green pepper and onion and cook until tender.
Stir in corn, tomato
paste,
water,
salt and pepper.
Add dinner and mix well.
Pour into 2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.
Can be made ahead.
Add 1/4 cup water if
baking later.	Serve with green salad and Texas or garlic toast.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix together with hands.
Let stand overnight.

title: quick and easy marinara sauce
directions: Add olive oil to medium saucepan over moderate heat. Add garlic and crushed pepper to the oil. When pepper snaps and garlic sizzles, stir in tomatoes. Season with salt and pepper. Add Italian seasoning. Cook for 5 minutes and stir in parsley.

title: mexican party dip
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain off excess fat and put in a 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Spread the bean dip on top using as much or as little as you like, depending on how hot and spicy you'd like it. Drizzle the taco sauce on top and then sprinkle with the grated cheese.
Heat in a 350° oven until hot.
Serve with taco chips.

title: quick skillet stew
directions: Brown the ground beef and drain off fat.
Add the vegetables and brown gravy.
Cook until vegetables are hot.
Serve with biscuits.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Season chicken and boil with celery and onion until tender. Remove from broth and cool.
Remove meat from bone and save. Place broth in a large roaster and add enough water to equal 3 to 4 quarts liquid.

title: fruit cake
directions: Chop fruit, nuts and dates with milk and coconut; mix well. Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 200° for 2 hours.

title: eggplant country style supper
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole dish.
Saute eggplant 5 minutes in drippings in large frying pan.
Pour mixture into prepared baking dish.
Saute onion 2 minutes in same pan. Stir in tomatoes.
Add parsley, sugar, chili powder, pepper and salt.
Stir and let come to boil.
Pour over eggplant.
Sprinkle generously with crumbs and cheese.
Bake 45 minutes or until top is brown and bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: goof ball candy
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and roll in balls.
Melt the chocolate chips and paraffin. Dip balls in mixture and put out on a pan to cool.

title: chow mein candy
directions: Melt chocolate bits in double boiler or microwave.
Add chow mein
noodles
and
peanuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper and
let set.
Makes approximately 50 to 60 pieces.
Ah So.

title: german springerles
directions: In electric mixer, beat eggs until light; add sugar. Beat until mixture is stiff and light, about 15 minutes at high speed. Add extract, flour and soda. Mix thoroughly. Roll 1/2-inch thick on lightly floured surface with regular rolling pin which has been floured. Lightly flour springerle rolling pin and roll 1/4-inch thickness, pressing only once for clear print. Cut along dividing lines to separate cookies. Place on lightly floured surface; cover with dish towel. Let stand overnight to dry.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 1 minute after each.
Add extract.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately to the egg and sugar mixture.
Stir in coconut.
Bake in Bundt-tube pan (oil and flour the bottom).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Remove from oven.
Prepare syrup and pour over cake while it is still hot. (Poke holes in top with fork before pouring syrup over top.)

title: gloucester fish chowder
directions: Fry out salt pork in saucepan until crisp and delicately browned.
Add onions.
Saute slowly.
Add water and potatoes.
Cook 10 minutes, then add fish.
Cook until tender.
Add seasonings, milk and butter.
Bring just to boiling point.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: blueberry-grape jello mold
directions: Dissolve the 2 packages of grape jello in 2 cups of hot water. Do not add any cold water.
Add 1 can of blueberry pie filling and 1 can of crushed pineapple (in its own juice).
Stir through the grape jello.
Chill.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: cheddar cheese biscuits
directions: Mix flour, butter and sour cream.
Fold in the cheese.
Drop by teaspoon into tiny, greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: lane cake
directions: Combine egg yolks, sugar and butter in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened (about 20 minutes).
Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients. Cool completely.
Yield: 3 1/2 cups.

title: hot wassail
directions: In a saucepan, boil the sugar and water for 10 minutes, or until the sugar is completely dissolved.
Remove from heat and add the cloves, crystalized ginger, and cinnamon stick; let stand one hour and strain to remove spices.
Add the apple cider, lemon juice and orange juice; mix well.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill.
Serve with fresh vegetables or carve out inside loaf of Italian or Jewish rye bread. Cut up portion of bread, cut out into small pieces.
Put dip into cavity of bread.
(Double recipe for this.)
Can use fat free mayonnaise and sour cream for 0 fat recipe.

title: spanish onions on grill
directions: Cut onions in half, leave on all skins.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Pour butter over onions.
Place on hot coals or grill.
Grill for 1 hour, when hearts of onions pop up, onions are done.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind cranberries and apples.
Add pineapple and sugar.
Stir and refrigerate.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger meat.
Drain grease and add Velveeta cubes to the meat.
Stir until all cheese is melted and mixed well with meat.
Slice biscuits in half, entire tray, not just the individual biscuits.
Spread the meat and cheese mixture on the bottom half of tray of biscuits.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: Mix instant pudding and milk together.
Pour in condensed milk and stir.
Add about 1/3 of cool whip and stir.
Layer mixture with bananas and wafers.
Top with remaining cool whip.

title: aunt dean's punch
directions: Add 1 can of punch to punch bowl, then add ice cream scoops. Very important to add 1 (2 liter) Sprite after ice cream to get foaming effect.
Repeat same for 2nd bowl.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray with Pam a 13 x 9-inch oblong dish.
Mix cake mix as given on box.
Sprinkle the nuts
and coconut in bottom of dish. Pour cake mix batter over nuts and coconut.
Cream the powdered sugar, milk and cream cheese.
Drop by spoonfuls on top of cake mix.
Bake for 20 minutes. Take out and cool.
When cooling, cake will crack in all directions.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix bacon, lettuce, cauliflower and cheese together. Carefully mix peas and mayonnaise.
Add to cauliflower mixture.

title: taco joes
directions: In skillet, saute beef, onion and garlic until meat is no longer pink and onion is tender.
Drain.
Stir in tomatoes, catsup, chili powder to taste, salt and mustard.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes or until most of the liquid has evaporated.
Spoon meat mixture into hamburger buns.
Top with shredded cheese and lettuce.
Sprinkle with diced tomatoes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Make your own favorite 9-inch pie crust.
Mix apple juice, flour, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Stir in apples.
Put into pastry lined pie plate.
Dot with margarine and cover with top crust. Flute edges.
You can cover pie edges with foil to keep from getting too brown.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 15 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Put bread in baking dish. Beat eggs and milk; pour over bread. Put your meat on top, then cheese. Cover and set in fridge overnight.
Bake at 305° for 1 hour.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onion, salt and pepper.
Combine all ingredients in a kettle and cook until heated through.

title: homemade pizza dough(for pizza and fried dough)
directions: Put flour in large bowl.
Poke large hole in center of flour. Add crumbled yeast cake and pinch of salt.
Add warm water, 1/2 cup at a time.
Knead dough until all flour and water are used. Knead for about 10 minutes, until round ball forms.
Sprinkle with flour lightly.
Cover bowl with towel and let set 3 to 5 hours or overnight.
Keep in warm place.
Makes large pizza or drop by handfuls into 4 tablespoons of sizzling olive oil for fried dough. Sprinkle with sugar or confectioners sugar.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions, then add rest of the ingredients.
Put in baking dish, bake at 400° until hot, then place on top and bake until biscuits are done.

title: cabbage patch soup
directions: Brown ground beef; add onion and bell pepper.
Cover with water and cook on high 10 minutes.
Add other ingredients.
Cover and cook 30 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Make cake according to box directions in a 9 x 13 inch pan. While cake is cooking, put milk and sugar in a double boiler on low heat and cook until mixture is sticky.
Punch holes in cake and pour sugar mixture over cake.
Cool.
(I put in the freezer to cook for a few minutes.)
Sprinkle some coconut on top of cake. Top with Cool Whip and add more coconut on top.
Refrigerate.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Beat eggs, flour, salt and pepper.
Mix with zucchini.
Drop by spoonfuls in hot oil until golden brown, about 2 minutes.

title: mission inn potatoes
directions: Bring 1 cup water to boil in saucepan.
Add potatoes, onion, garlic, salt and bouillon.
Return to boil, stirring.
Lower heat; cook, covered, 10 to 12 minutes or until potatoes are almost tender.
Pour half the potatoes and their liquid into shallow 2-quart casserole or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with half the cheese and half the chiles.
Top with remaining potato mixture and all but 2 tablespoons of the remaining cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Spread mixture of sour cream and egg on top.
Arrange remaining chiles and cheese on sour cream layer.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 10 minutes more or until golden.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: butter pecan sauce
directions: Saute pecans in margarine until lightly browned. Add condensed milk and water, stirring until blended. Cook for 10 minutes over medium heat until thickened, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat, stir in extract; cool. Yields 1 3/4 cups.

title: stephen's caesar salad(no anchovies or eggs)
directions: In a large salad bowl, add olive oil, then whisk in mustard, garlic and anchovy paste one at a time, mixing until smooth. Whisk in vinegar.
Mix well.
Add Parmesan cheese and croutons after tossing dressing with salad.
Serve soon after mixing in croutons to avoid them becoming soggy.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients in bottom of dish like crust. Beat confectioners sugar, eggs and 2 sticks butter with electric mixer for 5 or 6 minutes or until fluffy.
Pour this mixture over the crust.
Slice bananas and cover the mixture.
Add pineapple (drained) over bananas.
Cover mixture with Cool Whip.
Spread chopped nuts and cherries over top.
Refrigerate.

title: microwave herb-buttered corn
directions: Place corn in a 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish; leave space between ears.
Add the water to the dish.
Microwave, covered, with plastic wrap, at High power until tender, 8 to 15 minutes. Turn ears and rearrange every 4 minutes.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes.
Combine butter, chives, salt and pepper in small bowl. Microwave, uncovered, at High power until butter melts, 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes; stir once during cooking.
Pour over corn.

title: cooking for a crowd church supper chicken pie
directions: Cook until just tender the carrots, onions and potatoes; set aside.
In large saucepan, put soup and cream; heat through.
Add vegetables and chicken.
Pour into a large baking pan about 10 1/2 x 14 1/2 x 2-inches.
Add frozen peas and pimiento.
Sprinkle with gravy mix.

title: macaroni-veggie casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni and vegetables.
Layer casserole dish with 1/2 cup milk, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, macaroni, vegetables, salt and pepper.
Repeat with macaroni and vegetables.
Pour remaining 1/4 cup milk over the top.
Top with the remaining 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, the bread crumbs, garlic powder, parsley and 1 tablespoon margarine.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.
Broil for 5 more minutes.
Great as a main course or a side dish.

title: chicken pie
directions: Blend milk, flour and soup and pour into saucepan.
Add coarsely chopped chicken, peas and carrots, onion, salt and butter.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Pour into pastry lined pan.
Sprinkle top very lightly with thyme.
Cover with top crust; cut slits for steam to escape.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes or until nicely browned and filling begins to bubble through slits in crust.

title: company cream cheese pie
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and powdered sugar and add Cool Whip; pour into crust.
Refrigerate.
Top with fruit (optional).

title: cowboy stew
directions: Melt margarine. Add meat and brown well. Drain. Add onion, celery, garlic, green onions and bell pepper. Saute until soft. Add salt, pepper, chili powder and sugar. Stir well.
Add tomatoes, corn, beans, potatoes and water, if necessary. Stir together and bring to a boil, stirring frequently, to keep from scorching.
Simmer on low 40 minutes until potatoes are tender.

title: sugarless oatmeal cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, combine all ingredients, beating well.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Drop by heaping teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate custard pie
directions: In a heavy-bottomed 2-qt. saucepan over medium-low heat, heat milk slowly.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery in oil.
Add flour; stir until smooth.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, juice and seasonings.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add shrimp.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: easy enchiladas
directions: Brown meat in skillet and drain.
After you drain meat put back in skillet.
Add both cans of soup and the can of Ro-Tel. Bring to a boil and simmer for 10 minutes.
In a 9 x 13-inch cake pan first put in layer of tortillas, put layer of half of meat mixture, layer of finely chopped up onions and layer of half of Cheddar cheese.
Add another layer of corn tortillas, last of meat mixture, layer of finely chopped up onions and top with last of Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is bubbly around the edges and melted on the top.

title: never fail pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and shortening, mixing well.
Add eggs and continue mixing until fluffy.
Alternately add flour, baking powder and milk until all ingredients are well blended.
Add vanilla and pour into a tube pan that has been sprayed with vegetable spray.
Bake in oven at 325° for approximately 1 hour or until brown.

title: play dough for children
directions: Mix ingredients well, then cook over low heat until it forms a soft ball, about 3 minutes, and it cleans the sides of the pan. Store in airtight container or Baggie.
(I knead the hot mixture; it gives a very smooth consistency.)

title: most delicious fruit salad
directions: Drain canned fruit, strawberries and bananas.
Stir in peach pie filling.
Refrigerate.
Will keep 2 or 3 days.
In season you may use fresh strawberries and peaches.
Very good.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, half and half and sugar in a large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently spread on bottom of pie crust. Pour milk into bowl and add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes (mixture will be thick).
Stir in pumpkin and spices, blending with wire whisk.
Mix well. Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours. Garnish with additional Cool Whip and nuts, if desired.

title: grandma's gazpacho
directions: Soak bread in water and ring out quickly. Combine all other ingredients in a food processor and blend well. Strain. Serve very cold with French bread.

title: miss angie's peanut butter pie
directions: Cut peanut butter into powdered sugar until crumbly.
Set aside.
Combine cornstarch, sugar and salt in a heavy pan; add milk and heat until thickened.
Beat egg yolks.
Stir some hot mixture into the eggs and then return it to the pan, stirring all the while.
Add butter and flavoring.
Cool.
Preheat oven to 350°. Sprinkle peanut butter mixture over pie crust, reserving 2 tablespoons.
Pour custard over it.
Beat egg whites until stiff and gradually add sugar.
Beat until it stands in firm peaks. Spread over pie, sealing crust edges.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Bake 7 or 8 minutes to brown meringue lightly.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Line a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish with tortilla chips.
Pour chicken broth over chips.
Add chicken.
Saute onion, green pepper and celery in butter.
Add cumin and chili powder to vegetables. Pour this over chicken.
Mix tomatoes and soups together.
Pour mixture over all.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: crunchy pineapple salad
directions: Mix the first three ingredients and let cool until the consistency of an unbeaten egg white.
Then add remaining ingredients and refrigerate until set.

title: lime chicken with melon
directions: Rub cut garlic on chicken and place in 2 well-buttered 13 1/2 x 8 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch baking dishes.
Sprinkle lime juice, scallions, tarragon, salt and pepper over chicken.
Dot with 7 tablespoons butter.
Add wine.
Bake, uncovered, at 375°, basting every 10 minutes.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme; mix until well blended.
Serve with fresh fruit and cookies as dippers (Pirouettes are nice).
Makes 2 cups.

title: berry blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix together dry ingredients.
Add combined milk, butter and egg mix just until moistened.
Fold in blueberries.
Spoon into greased medium size muffin pan or paper lined muffin cups, filling each cup 3/4 full.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Fry diced onion and diced bacon together, stirring constantly until slightly browned.
Drain fat and add bacon and onion to pork and beans, along with other ingredients.
Mix well; bake in uncovered casserole at 350° for about 1 hour.
Strips of bacon can be put on top before baking if desired.

title: gingerbread boys
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Blend in water, flour, salt, soda and all spices.
Cover; chill at least 3 hours. Roll dough 1/4-inch thick on lightly floured board.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375° or 350°.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Roll into small balls and chill until firm. In a double boiler, melt 1 large package chocolate chips and 1/4 pound paraffin.
With toothpick, dip candy balls into chocolate mixture to coat and lay on waxed paper to cool.

title: divinity
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in 2-quart glass measuring cup.
Cook in microwave on High 19 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Candy thermometer should read 260°.

If not, cook 1 to 2 minutes more. While syrup cooks, beat egg whites very stiff in large bowl. Gradually pour syrup over egg whites and continue beating on High until thick and candy begins to lose its gloss, about 12 minutes. Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper or onto large buttered pan.
Yields 6 to 7 dozen pieces.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Blend sausage and cheese. Work in Bisquick.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° until light brown.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix as you would any other cake.
Grease and flour tube pan. Sprinkle bottom of pan with coconut.
Pour batter over coconut. Bake one hour and fifteen minutes at 325°.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: After grating German chocolate, reserve 1/4 cup for topping.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Mix all ingredients together in saucepan; cook over low heat until done (45 minutes to 1 hour).
Freezes well.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the butter; add sugar and beat well.
Add part of the flour
with salt to creamed butter and sugar;
beat well. Add eggs,
at
a
time,
alternately with remaining flour. Continue to
beat
well.
Pour
batter
in a well-greased and floured tube
or Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes and then turn oven down to 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: egg custard
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into a slightly baked pie shell. Cook at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue cooking for 30 minutes.
During this 30 minute period, open oven door all the way then close two or three times.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix milk and Cool Whip with mixer.
Add other ingredients and pour in vanilla wafer crust.
Chill.
Makes 2 pies.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish or pan.
Mix cream of mushroom soup and milk together.
Add onion soup mix.
Sprinkle 1 cup of rice over mixture.
Place chicken breasts on top.
Cover with foil and bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until tender.

title: tri-level brownies
directions: Stir together first 3 ingredients.
Mix with oats and brown sugar.
Stir in 6 tablespoons butter.
Pat mixture in 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 350°
for 10 minutes.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and rhubarb.
Add orange rind and juice.
Turn into pastry-lined pan.
Dot with butter.
Cover with strips of pastry, lattice fashion.
Bake in preheated 450° oven for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: rose's coconut cream pie
directions: Pie Filling: Mix sugar, flour, egg yolks, milk, vanilla and coconut. Cook on medium heat until thickened. Pour into pie crust.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Mix in a bowl cinnamon, flour, nutmeg and egg.
Mix until mixture is crumbly. Sprinkle over apples.
Melt butter and pour over mixture. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool for 15 minutes.

title: fresh pasta
directions: By hand:
On a clean surface make a well with the flour.
In a measuring cup mix the eggs, water, oil and salt.
Pour the wet mixture slowly into the flour and mix with your 2 fingers until all of the wet is incorporated.
Do not force the dough to take all of the flour.
If you are going to use a pasta machine to roll out the dough, you may at this point form the dough into a disk and cover with plastic wrap.
Place in the refrigerator for 1 hour to rest. If you are going to roll this by hand you should knead the dough on a floured work surface for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cheddar cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine 3 minutes or until soft.
Stir in flour, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook, stirring, 2 minutes.
Stir in broth, carrots and potatoes.
Bring to boiling. Lower heat; cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add evaporated milk and water.
Cook over medium heat until almost boiling.
Do not boil.
Reduce heat to low; stir in cheese until melted.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: blueberry cream cheese pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar until creamy. Mix Dream Whip according to box directions. Add Dream Whip mixture to cream cheese mixture, mix well. Pour mixture into pie crust, cover with pie filling. Chill 5 hours or overnight.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs; add dry ingredients, then oil.
Stir in water; beat in pumpkin.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and add enough water to make 2 cups. Heat and dissolve Jell-O.
Let Jell-O set until like pudding, then whip it.
Chill milk until crystals form around the edges of the bowl, then whip.
Add whipped milk and salad dressing to whipped Jell-O.
Stir in remaining ingredients and chill.
Salad will be fluffier if the milk and salad dressing are beaten into the Jell-O. Cottage cheese will be less noticeable if it is also beaten before pineapple and nuts are added.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Press crescent rolls into a 9 x 13-inch pan for crust. Add sausage on crust; mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper together and pour over crust. Pour hash browns over this. Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: make your own bubbles
directions: Combine all ingredients in a gallon container.
For more sturdier bubbles, add more glycerine.
Use with any bubble blowers and have fun!!!

title: rocky road fudge
directions: Use microwave-safe glass bowl in to melt together chocolate chips and condensed milk until smooth. Add vanilla.
Immediately pour mixture over marshmallows and nuts. Mix together. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan that has been coated with spray or lined with wax paper.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Add to pumpkin mixture along with dissolved soda and milk; mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips, nuts and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Chop and set aside.
Mix 1 stick melted butter, crab meat, bread crumbs, salt, pepper, garlic powder and chopped stems.
Make sure mixture is moist.
If not, add more butter until moist.
Stuff mushroom caps with crab meat mixture.
Place in baking dish.
Pour 1/2 stick melted butter over mushrooms.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until top is brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and form a ball.
Chill.

title: honey french dressing for meats
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and whip for two minutes. Store in refrigerator.
Very good on beef or pork and can also be used to barbecue chicken.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Boil peeled shrimp and put in blender; blend fine.
Add onion, mace and garlic salt.
Add enough mayonnaise to blend the ingredients together to make smooth spread.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.
Delicious!

title: stuffed celery rings
directions: Separate bunch; wash and dry well.
Cut stalks 6 inches long and heart in half.
Work butter and cheese together well and add remaining ingredients.
Stuff stalks.
Reform into a bunch.
Slice and serve plain or on bread.

title: peanut butter fondant
directions: Roll out between waxed paper; spread peanut butter over dough. Roll up like jelly roll and chill.
After chilled, cut in 1/4-inch slices and lay out on waxed paper to dry.
Store in airtight container.

title: chicken amore
directions: Salt and pepper in flour.
Dip chicken in flour and saute. Put olive oil in pan.
Put chicken in pan and saute.
Put everything else in pan over chicken.
Let simmer on low for 35 minutes.
Serve on noodles.

title: turkey stuffed crescents
directions: Combine cream cheese and margarine.
Mix in turkey, milk, onions, salt, and pepper.
Separate the crescent rolls into 4 rectangles and press the dough perforations to seal.
Place about 1/2 c. turkey mixture onto the center of each rectangle and bring the corners up to the center.
Pinch the corners to seal well. Brush each roll with some melted margarine and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage and cheese together.
Mix in the Bisquick a little at a time. Roll into small balls. Bake in preheated 350° oven about 10 minutes or until done.
Don't overbake.
(You may want to grease the pan a little to keep the sausage balls from sticking.)

title: baked potato soup
directions: Bring soup, broth, flour, half and half, parsley, chives and oleo to a boil.
Turn heat down to a simmer and add potatoes (cut into large chunks).
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve with chopped green onions, grated cheese and bacon pieces.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, margarine and baking powder.
Add well beaten eggs.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30-40 minutes or until coconut is brown or until firm.
Makes 2 pies. If using frozen pie crust, place pies on cookie sheet to brown crust on bottom.

title: summer tuna salad
directions: Put the cucumber, onion, parsley, pepper, tomatoes and tuna in a salad bowl. In a separate bowl, combine the oil, vinegar, garlic, salt and pepper. Pour the mixture over the salad; toss and serve. Yield: 2 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Microwave bacon 5 to 6 minutes on High.
Microwave spinach on box 5 to 6 minutes on High.
Soften cream cheese 2 minutes on Medium (50% power).
Crumble bacon and combine all ingredients. Serve warm or cold.

title: hot dirty rice
directions: Cook rice according to package directions; set aside.
Combine water and next 3 ingredients in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes; add chicken livers, and cook 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain, reserving 3/4 cup liquid. Remove meat from wings; coarsely chop wing meat, gizzards, hearts and livers.
Set chopped meat aside.
Brown sausage in Dutch oven; stirring until it crumbles.
Drain and set aside.
Melt butter in Dutch oven; add onion, pepper and celery.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often, 5 minutes or until tender.
Add green onions and cook 2 minutes.
