Add ham, sausage, chopped meat and reserved liquid.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat, and simmer 15 minutes. Stir in cooked rice and parsley.
Serve warm.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: easy fruit dessert
directions: Pour juice from pineapple into bowl.
Slice bananas and put in juice.
Leave for about 10 minutes.
Put pineapple, peach pie filling and strawberries into bowl.
Take bananas out of juice and add to fruit mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix onion and mushroom soup well.
Add eggs and mix.
Add cooked squash.
Beat well and add sugar.
Pour into well-greased casserole half of the squash mixture.
Sprinkle with half of the cheese and half of the bread crumbs.
Add the other half of the squash and spread with rest of cheese and bread crumbs.
Melt butter and pour over top.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: crows nest
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cut up apples and put on bottom.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Mix
flour,
sugar and soda;
add 1 cup Crisco.
Mix as for pie
crust.
Stir in 2 cups buttermilk and 1 package yeast which has
been
dissolved
in 1/4 cup warm water.
Mix well. Cover and put
in refrigerator.
Use as for regular biscuits, rolling and cutting
out.
Dough
will
keep
in fridge for a week.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Crumble half the corn bread in a large salad bowl; combine tomatoes, pepper, onions, pickles and bacon.
Spoon 1/2 of the vegetable mixture over the corn bread.
Stir together the mayonnaise and pickle juice in a small bowl.
Spread 1/2 of this dressing over the vegetables in big bowl.
Repeat the layering with the remaining corn bread, vegetables and dressing.
Garnish as desired.
Cover tightly and chill 2 to 3 hours.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: southern style slaw
directions: In bowl, combine salad dressing, vinegar, sugar, mustard, celery seed and pepper.
Add cabbage and carrots.
Toss gently to coat.
Cover.
Refrigerate until serving, at least 2 hours.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Oil a 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle pecans on bottom.
Layer coconut over pecans.
Mix cake mix according to package directions.
Pour over coconut.
Melt margarine and mix with cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
You may leave in pan or turn out onto board when completely cool.

title: old fashioned potato salad
directions: Mix vegetables together with cut up eggs.
Mix mayonnaise and vinegar together and add to vegetables.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: spanish pork chops
directions: In large skillet, brown pork chops and set aside.
Melt margarine in same skillet and add rice vermicelli mixture.
Cook until vermicelli is light brown.
Add hot water, contents of envelope seasoning and stewed tomatoes.
Stir.
Return pork chops to skillet.
Bring to boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: On cookie sheet, lay out each crescent roll square.
Press seams together to form a large rectangle.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift flour onto plater or bowl and set aside.
In a large bowl, beat corn oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla at medium speed until well blended.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Put mixture in buttered casserole.
Mix 1 stick margarine and crumble cheese and Ritz crackers (enough to absorb butter). Sprinkle over top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: picnic apple pie
directions: Line jelly
roll
pan
with
pie crust.
Sprinkle lemon juice over
apples, which are spread over crust.	Mix together butter, sugars
and
flour and sprinkle over apples.
Sprinkle pecans over top
and bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: mexican salad
directions: Brown ground beef and season to taste.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, cut up lettuce and tomato.
Add cheese, drained kidney beans, crushed chips and ground beef (after it has cooled).
Mix well and serve.
May serve with sour cream, avocado or picante sauce.

title: chicken delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in ungreased casserole dish.
Top with crumbs and poppy seed.
Pour melted butter over entire dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: toledo chicken
directions: Combine milk, flour and onion together.
Cook until thick; stir in 1 cup cheese.
Stir until melted.
Mix with rest of ingredients. Put into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Put biscuits on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle rest of cheese on top and bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Can use crackers instead of biscuits.

title: sue's pot roast
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook until meat is tender.

title: favorite apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Make pie pastry (see following recipe). Mix 1/2 cup sugar, the brown sugar, flour, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, nutmeg and salt in a large bowl.
Add apples and lemon peel; toss until apples are coated with cinnamon mixture.
Turn into pastry-lined pie plate; dot with butter.

title: church windows
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate bits; cool.
Stir in marshmallows and nuts with fork until well
coated.
Roll up in wax paper and store in refrigerator overnight.
Unwrap and slice.
Makes 3 rolls, 15 inches long.

title: strawberry angel food dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 1/2 cups boiling water (if using pineapple, use juice to make up enough water).
Stir in strawberries (frozen or thawed) or drained pineapple, sugar and salt.
Cool until it begins to thicken.
Fold in whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Cover bottom of bowl or pan with torn angel cake.
Pour half of Jell-O mixture over cake.
Repeat with a layer of cake and rest of Jell-O mixture.
Refrigerate until firm.
When firm, spread Cool Whip over top and decorate with strawberries or walnuts.

title: homemade potato soup
directions: Put all ingredients (except evaporated milk and chives) into crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low 10 to 12 hours (high 3 to 4 hours).
Stir in evaporated milk during last hour.
Mash potatoes or cream in blender before serving.
Serve topped with chives, if desired.

title: rich potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, sour cream, onion, cheese, soup, salt, pepper and half of margarine.
Put in buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix cornflakes and remaining margarine and sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken fruit salad
directions: Combine chicken, fruits and celery. In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients, except almonds. Pour over chicken mixture, tossing to coat. Chill. Just before serving, add almonds and toss. Makes 6 servings.

title: bunuelos
directions: Boil together the water and shortening. When briskly boiling, add the flour, stirring thoroughly, until mixture separates from the sides of the pan. Remove from heat and cool. Add eggs one by one, beating well after each addition. Heat enough oil in a deep frying pan. When fat is hot enough, drop flour and egg mixture by spoonful and fry until golden brown. Drain on paper towel and roll in granulated sugar, if desired.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook in double boiler until thick.
Pour into a baked pie shell.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut off tops of peppers and clean out seeds. Steam peppers until just done. Cool. Mix remaining ingredients, except for sauce. Pour sauce in a large pan. Being careful not to split peppers, stuff and lower gently into sauce. Simmer, covered, for about 2 hours. Stir carefully and occasionally during cooking time. Cut peppers in half; lay open on plate and drizzle with spaghetti sauce. Pass extra sauce and additional grated cheese.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients. Simmer 1 hour.
Cool.
Store covered in refrigerator.
Add approximately 1/4 cup to 1 cup of hot boiling water.

title: stroganoff
directions: Cook and stir beef, onions and garlic in a Dutch oven until meat is brown.
Drain fat.
Stir in salt, pepper, mushrooms and soup and heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Gradually stir in sour cream and heat through.
Do not boil.
Spoon meat mixture over egg noodles and sprinkle with parsley.

title: fudgy mocha brownies with a crust
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl, combine 1 cup flour and sugar. Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Arrange all in layers. Pour chicken broth on top and bake at 375°
for 1 hour.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Make your favorite yellow cake mix in 2 round pans and cool. Layer in punch bowl:
1/2 strawberries, 1 cake, 1/2 pudding and 1/2 pineapple.
Repeat and top with Cool Whip.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix and Jell-O.
Add oil and milk.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat after each addition.
Stir in frozen strawberries.
Makes a 3 layer cake.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mom's famous italian casserole
directions: Brown chuck about 5 minutes.
Add onion, celery and carrots. Cool another 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer, covered, 1 hour.

title: super stroganoff
directions: Cook and stir stew beef, hamburger and garlic in margarine in 10-inch skillet until meat is light brown.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook, stirring constantly, 5 minutes.
Stir in soup.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat; simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream; heat through. Serve over hot noodles.

title: broiled cake
directions: Bake cake mix per package in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put remaining ingredients into saucepan.
Melt real good.
Spread over cake and brown under broiler.
Watch closely.
Serve hot.

title: tuna casserole with cheese
directions: In a large casserole dish, combine tuna and mayonnaise.
Set aside.
In saucepan, combine cream of mushroom soup, milk, cheese and mushrooms.
Cook on low heat until thoroughly melted and combined.
Cook rotini.
Combine all together with tuna and mayonnaise in casserole dish.
Add pepper.
Combine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: graham cracker pudding
directions: Evenly coat 8 x 2 x 2-inch baking pan with cooking spray. Layer graham crackers on bottom of pan.
Continue layering until there are 5 layers of graham crackers.
Note:
Some squares will need to be broken to make even layers.
In medium bowl, beat eggs, sugar, milk, vanilla and cinnamon together until well blended. Cover pan with plastic wrap and refrigerate for a minimum of 30 minutes or overnight, as time permits.
Remove plastic wrap from pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until a knife inserted in center of pudding comes out clean.
Note: The pudding should be puffed in the center.
Cool for five minutes. Pudding may be served hot, warm or chilled.
To serve, cut into 9 squares.
Lift out squares of pudding with a pancake turner. Garnish with whipped cream or topping and berries.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: no bake lemon pie
directions: Blend thawed lemonade into Eagle Brand milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add a few drops of yellow food coloring.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle few crumbs of graham cracker crust on top.
Limeade can be substituted.
Use green food coloring. Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: dragon stew
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Add water, seasoning and vegetables.
Cover and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Serve on rice or plain with crackers.

title: egg stuffed peppers
directions: Cut off the top of each pepper; remove all the inside of peppers.
In a 2 to 3-quart saucepan, bring approximately 2 inches of water to a boil; add peppers.
Cover and boil 5 minutes.
Drain and place cut side down to cool.
In small skillet, heat oil; add onions and garlic and saute until soft.
Add mushrooms.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until mushrooms are tender.
Put mushrooms in a medium bowl.
Add all ingredients except peppers; toss to combine.
Stuff each pepper 1/4 with mixed mushroom mixture. Place peppers in a casserole dish in upright position; cover and bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Each serving equals to 2 1/2 serving vegetable, 1 serving fat, 1/4 cup limit vegetables, 1/2 serving bread and substitutes for 3/4 egg.

title: lamb chili
directions: Brown ground lamb, drain.
Slice onion in small pieces and brown.
Mix lamb, onion, tomatoes, beans and tomato sauce.
Heat to a slow boil and dilute to taste.
Add 1 tablespoon chili powder, salt and black pepper to taste.
Simmer 15 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot with Ritz crackers or pour over rice.
Serves 6 to 10 persons.

title: chili sauce
directions: Brown together hamburger and onion.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: layered salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise with sugar.
Spread over layered veggies. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bacon bits.
Let set overnight in fridge.
This will last up to a week, if it's not stirred up.

title: pull apart coffee cake
directions: Cut biscuits in 1/4 with scissors.
Roll in small balls and dip in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Drop in ungreased Bundt pan. Melt oleo and add sugar and vanilla mixture.
Pour over biscuits that are in Bundt pan.
Bake approximately 40 minutes at 350°. Remove from pan and pull apart the desired amount for each individual.
This is good cold, but delicious warm.

title: smashed potato balls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Peel potatoes and cut in halves.
Boil until tender (20 minutes); drain.
Cook bacon in microwave until crisp; crumble into fine pieces.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients.
Grease and flour bread tins and bake for 55 minutes.
Tastes just like a lemon pound cake.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients with butter, shortening and egg, adding ice water gradually.
Roll out on floured table.
Will keep a long time in refrigerator.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix ingredients and drop by spoonfuls onto simmering chicken or beef stew.
Cook, uncovered for 10 minutes; then covered for 10 minutes or until done.

title: peanut butter brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water in a 3-quart saucepan. Cook, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves and mixture boils.
Add butter; cook without stirring until mixture reaches soft crack stage (280°).
Stir and cook to hard-crack stage (305°); remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and baking soda.

title: roast beef au jus
directions: Follow these directions for any size roast.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Rub meat with oil.
Place fat side up in a shallow roasting pan.
Do not cover; do not add water.
Put roast in oven and bake for one hour.
Turn off heat, but do not open door at any time until ready to serve.
Regardless of the length of time the meat has been in the oven, 30 to 40 minutes before serving turn on oven again to 375°.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.	Now open oven door. The meat will be brown and crisp on the outside and pink all the way through, juicy and a medium rare.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat egg well.
Add sugar and blend.
Add oil slowly.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to egg mixture.
Add nuts, carrots, coconut and pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Combine shortening and chocolate in top of a double boiler; bring water to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cook until chocolate melts.
Add sugar, stirring well.
Add eggs and vanilla; stir well.
Stir in flour and salt and mix thoroughly.
Remove chocolate mixture from heat and stir in pecans.
Spread batter into a well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares.
Serve with fudge sauce and whipped topping.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: potato dish
directions: All ingredients need to be diced.
Mix together.
Set overnight in refrigerator.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: tomatoes country style
directions: Beat together garlic, salt, and basil (if desired).
Cut tomatoes into 12 even slices about 1/2 in. thick.
Spread 6 slices with about 2 T. of softened cream cheese then top with remaining slices to make 6 sandwiches.
Dip each in flour then egg mixture and finally in crumbs.
Fry on both sides over medium heat in mixture of butter and olive oil until brown.
Garnish with parsley if desired.

title: can't stop cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Add corn flakes and nuts.
Roll into balls and bake at 350°
for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In small bowl, combine flour, soda and salt; set aside.
In a small pan, melt butter, sugar and water; bring just to a boil and remove.
Add 1 cup chocolate chips and vanilla.
Stir until melted.
Transfer to large mixing bowl and add eggs; gradually mix in flour.
Stir in remaining cup of chocolate chips.
Spread in 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli-ham ring
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coarsely chop broccoli and ham.
Mix together all ingredients, except the crescent rolls.
Arrange the crescent rolls sort of in a sunflower fashion on pizza pan.
Place the ham mixture in a ring on the crescent rolls.
Pull the ends up around the ham mixture.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Beat egg and combine with milk.
Dip chicken in flour, then into beaten egg, then coat with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Quickly saute slices in margarine.
Remove chicken breasts and place on oven broiler.
Top each piece with a slice of Mozzarella cheese.
Broil until cheese begins to bubble.
Pour heated sauce on each serving.

title: pat's catfish stew
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; remove and save for topping.
Add onion and potatoes.
Saute, stirring often, until onions are golden. Stir in seasonings, tomatoes and water.
Cover.
Simmer on low heat about 25 minutes.
Add fish and continue to cook for 20 minutes more or until fish is tender.
Ladle into bowls and top with bacon bits.
Serve with crackers or cornbread muffins.

title: rich sugar cutouts
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Chill dough and bake at 425° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot tamale
directions: Brown onion, peppers, garlic and ground beef together.
Drain off excess fat.
While meat is cooking, soak 1 cup corn meal in 3 cups cold milk.
Add salt, corn, tomatoes, olives and chili powder to meat mixture.
Cook slowly.
Add mixed corn meal/milk mixture to meat and vegetables.
Mix thoroughly.
Remove from stove, pour into large casserole or rectangle Pyrex pan.
Bake for about 45 minutes. Add 2 cups grated cheese and bake additional 10 to 15 minutes. Serves 12.

title: corn chowder
directions: Chop or cut the bacon into 1/2 inch pieces and saute with the onion.
Put the diced potatoes in water to cover and boil until done, 15-20 minutes.
Add the bacon mixture to the undrained potatoes.
Add the evaporated milk and the corn.
Make a roux of the flour and water and add it to the soup to thicken.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve.

title: crab salad
directions: Cook macaroni until done.
Drain and set aside to cool.
Chop pepper, celery and crab meat.
Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: chop stick chicken casserole
directions: Combine soup and water.
Blend well.
Reserve 1/2 cup chow mein noodles for top of casserole.
Add remaining noodles to soup mixture, along with chicken, celery, cashews and onion.
Toss lightly.
Spoon into greased casserole pan.
Sprinkle with noodles.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.
Garnish with orange sections.

title: oven omelet
directions: Arrange cheese slices to cover bottom of 9 x 9-inch buttered pan.
Beat eggs, milk, salt, and pepper.
Add chopped bacon, then pour over cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.
Let stand for 5 minutes before cutting.
May add or use diced ham, sausage, 1/4 cup green pepper, mushrooms or chopped onion.
Double recipe for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: shrimp and crab dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Serve with vegetables, chips or crackers.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Prepare instant potatoes for 12, following package instructions.
While hot, stir in dip and cream cheese.
Stir to mix and put into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika and dot with butter.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350° uncovered. Can be kept refrigerated for several days without baking, but do not freeze.
(Grated cheese can also be sprinkled on top.)
Yummy!

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix milk and both boxes of pudding for 2 minutes.
Add Cool Whip and mix until blended.
Layer pudding, wafers and bananas alternately.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Drain liquid from corn and beans.
Mix soup and sour cream together, then add to casserole.
Mix well.
Melt 1/2 cup margarine and add crackers.
Spread over top of casserole! Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain canned fruits real well.

title: honey puffs
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add milk, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Beat well.
Add flour, baking powder and soda; mix well.

title: yolkless egg salad
directions: Remove yolk from egg; discard.
Chop egg whites and combine with pickle relish and green onions.
Set aside.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: In 11 x 7-inch Pyrex dish, melt margarine.
Set aside.
In small bowl, combine sugar, milk and flour.
Pour into melted margarine.
Do not stir.
Pour peach pie filling over this.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and chill until slightly jelled. Mix in sherbet thoroughly.
Add oranges and pineapple and mix well. Chill until firm.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Heat corn and milk.
Gradually stir in egg.
Add 1 cup crumbs, onion, pepper, and seasonings.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 2 quart casserole.
Melt margarine and mix in remaining 1/2 cup crumbs.
Sprinkle over corn.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift together flour and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Add water, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Roll out on floured pastry sheet.
Put in pie pan, punch holes in bottom and sides.
Flute edges.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hot crab hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cut muffins in half.
Spread on halved muffins.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze until semi-frozen. Remove from freezer and cut each into quarters.
Place in bag and freeze until needed.
When ready to use, place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° until mixture bubbles.

title: honky ponkys(makes 2 packages cocktail rye)
directions: Cook and brown together sausage and beef.
Drain.
Add rest of ingredients and stir well over low heat until cheese melts. Spread on bread and freeze on a cookie sheet.
Store in Baggies.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind all vegetables together.
To this mixture add sugar, vinegar and salt.
Boil 15 minutes.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Saute onion in a large saucepan until soft.
Add soup, sour cream and chilies.
Heat until just warm.
Oil a 9 x 13-inch pan. Place 2 tablespoons of soup mixture on tortilla, approximately 1 tablespoon of Jack cheese and 1 tablespoon of chicken and roll up. Repeat until all are rolled up in pan.
Pour remaining soup mixture over and rest of grated cheese on top.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350° until hot and bubbly.
Serves 8.

title: baked vidalia onions
directions: Scoop out holes approximately an inch deep of each onion. Discard pulp.
Put a pat of butter in scooped out sections, then put 1 to 1 1/2 teaspoon crushed bouillon in each hole.
Top with another dot of butter.
Put onions in shallow baking dish filled with a slight amount of water.
Bake approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour or until onions are done.
Delicious!

title: pineapple ball
directions: Mix all together with only 1/2 cup of chopped pecans.
Form into ball, then roll ball in remaining 1/2 cup of pecans (finely chopped).
Put in middle of plate and place crackers around.

title: baked hash browns with cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl and put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
May be topped with Parmesan cheese, bread crumbs or potato chips, crushed.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine oats and milk; let stand 30 minutes.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt into oatmeal mixture.
Make well in center of dry ingredients and pour in oat mixture all at once.
Stir in until moist.
Fill cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° until golden brown for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix all well.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes in a 350° oven. Serve with Doritos.
This recipe is from my friend, Vicki Pennell.

title: ice cream sundaes
directions: First they grow.
Then they put them in the store.
They you buy them.
Then you take them home in a basket.
Then you wash them.
Then you put sugar on them and eat them.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Layer each:
ham, Swiss cheese and bacon in pie crust.
Blend eggs and whipping cream in blender.
Pour on top of layers.
Dot with butter.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes at 325°.
(Also great for dinner with a salad and bread!)

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix together well. Put in a loaf pan.
Freeze and slice to serve.
Makes 10 or so servings.

title: red cabbage cole slaw
directions: Mix and let set overnight.
Keeps 3 days in refrigerator.

title: pistachio nut cake
directions: Put ingredients in large mixing bowl; blend.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour in greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.

title: deviled crab casserole
directions: Boil flounder until flaky (approximately 15 minutes).
Pick over crab meat and remove all shell.
Combine and mix all ingredients, except buttered crumbs.
Place in shallow baking dish (9 x 13-inches).
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: rev.  gordon smith's "jailhouse" rolls
directions: Mix dry yeast and water.
Mix potatoes, butter and eggs, salt and sugar and blend into flour.
Add yeast water.
Mix well and put into greased bowl.
Cover with a damp cloth and place in refrigerator overnight.

title: stuffed carrots
directions: Peel and cook carrots until tender.
Make ridge on top. Scoop out center.
Place centers in bowl and mash smooth.
Add grated cheese, sugar, salt, Worcestershire sauce and enough mayonnaise to make a paste.
Fill ridge in carrot.
Place in baking dish.
Grate butter toast over carrots.
Bake in hot oven just long enough to brown.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with eggs and salad oil.
Then add vanilla, apples and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes in tube cake pan or three 8 inch layer pans.

title: tuna puffs
directions: Flake tuna and crumble crackers in plastic bag or between two sheets of waxed papers.
Mix soup and milk together.
Fold in tuna and crackers.
Then fold in well beaten eggs.
Bake in square 8 x 8 x 2-inch greased pan at 350° for one hour.
Test with knife.
If it comes out clean, it is done!

title: spicy peanut noodles
directions: Mix all the ingredients together except the linguini.
Combine the linguini with the sauce mix until they are mixed thoroughly.

title: mile high lemon chiffon pie
directions: Cook yolks, sugar, lemon juice, rind and salt in top of double boiler over simmering water . Stir constantly until consistency of thick custard.
Soak gelatin in cold water until dissolved.
Stir into hot custard.
Cool mixture.
Place egg whites in bowl and set in another bowl of very warm (not boiling) water.
Beat until stiff, not dry.
Gradually beat in 1 cup sugar.
Fold completely cooled custard into egg whites.
Pile into a dome shape.
Chill. Serve with a dollop of whipped cream.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, egg and vanilla flavor until light and fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients.
Stir into cream mix and blend well. Add chocolate pieces and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: crumb pudding
directions: Heat chocolate, milk and butter together in top of double boiler until chocolate is melted.
Mix egg yolks and sugar together and add a small amount of hot mixture. Return to double boiler and cook for 3 minutes. Add crumbs and almonds.
Fold in egg whites. Cover double boiler. Steam for 30 minutes. Serve hot with lemon sauce or whipped cream.

title: neat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand.
Form into neat balls. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: quick rice pudding
directions: In a 2-quart glass bowl combine all ingredients.
Heat, covered with wax paper, 11 to 13 minutes until pudding is thickened, stirring 3 times.
Chill before serving.
Approximate cooking time is 13 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar together until smooth.
Mix pudding into milk until thick.
Add to cream cheese mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: punch with a punch(non-alcoholic)
directions: Thaw frozen juices.
Pour into punch bowl; add pop and mix. You may add water, if desired.
It makes the punch a little less tangy.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel, cube potatoes and cook until done.
Let cool.
Cook eggs until done.
After cooking potatoes and eggs, add chopped celery, onions, dill pickles.
Mix ingredients with mayonnaise just enough to coat all ingredients.
Add one tablespoon mustard to give added flavor.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Slice potatoes and onions thin.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish in three layers.
Pour soup over the layered vegetables; season with salt and pepper.
Go light on salt as mushroom soup has salt. Top with layer of uncooked ground beef; cover with foil.
Cook until vegetables are tender.

title: corn relish
directions: Mix each group and layer ingredients in an 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: drop molasses cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, molasses and egg.
Mix dry ingredients together and add with coffee to creamed mixture.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: micro chicken with vegetables
directions: Place chicken breasts in microwaveable dish.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and soy sauce.
Add bell pepper, onion and tomatoes. Cook until chicken is thoroughly done, about 5 to 7 minutes on High.
Serve with cooked white rice.
Serves 4.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Brown
beef and onions.
Drain.
Mix all other ingredients and add to beef and onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: In a food processor chop beef fine. Place in bowl. Blend in processor, cream cheese. Put 1-1/2 tbsp. beef in and mix again. Add salt and worcestershire sauce and blend in bowl. Mix cream cheese mixture with onions by using spoon. Put 1/2 of beef in bowl small enough to cover bottom and a little up the sides. Place beef then cream cheese mixture on top. Put the rest of beef on top of mixture and cover with foil. Chill 6 hours or overnight. Very good with Town House crackers.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and add eggs, one at a time.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk.
Divide batter.
To one part, add spices and raisins; to other part, add nuts.
Bake at 325° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: best cheese cake
directions: Thoroughly blend crumbs, margarine, and 1/3 cup sugar.
Press firmly against bottom and sides of spring-form pan.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually add remaining 1 cup of sugar and vanilla. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Blend in sour cream. Spread in prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until firm.
Turn off oven, leaving door slightly ajar.
Allow cheesecake to remain in oven for 1 hour.
Cool in pan.
Chill for 4 hours or overnight.
Remove side of pan.
Top with pie filling.

title: teriyaki steaks
directions: Mix all ingredients
and marinate sliced meat for 12 to 24 hours.
Cooks very	quickly
on grill.
Great for feeding a large group.
Wonderful left over!

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish with margarine or butter.
In a bowl mix sour cream, cream of chicken soup, onion and 1/2 cheese.
Cook your broccoli according to the directions on the package.
Add broccoli to the mixture in the bowl, add pepper.
Pour the mixture in casserole dish.
Sprinkle other 1/2 cheese on top.
Melt butter or margarine in a saucepan.
Mix the stuffing with the butter.
Pour stuffing over mixture in dish and spread.
Cook, covered, in a 350° oven for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Steam broccoli and put in bottom of baking dish.
Brown boneless, skinless chicken breasts in butter and onion about 20 minutes to partially cook them.
Place on top of broccoli.
Top with shredded cheese.

title: pumpkin pie dessert squares
directions: Crust:
Set aside 1 cup of cake mix.
Mix remainder with 1/2 cup melted butter or oleo and 1 egg.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken, ham and cheese
directions: Lay chicken in pan.
Lay 1 to 2 slices of ham and cheese on each piece of chicken.
In separate bowl, mix soup with water.
If using mushrooms, lay on top of cheese.
Pour soup over chicken. Sprinkle croutons on top. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes. Serve over rice or side dish of rice.

title: klyskis and cabbage
directions: Cook noodles.
Drain and set aside.
Cut cabbage up into chunks.
Fry in large saucepan with oil or butter.
Stir and cook until cabbage is tender and browned.
Add noodles and mix well. Heat and serve.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, cream of tartar, cinnamon and salt together. Cream butter and brown sugar thoroughly.
Add 2 eggs and 1 egg yolk (reserve 1 egg white), beating until light.
Gradually add flour mixture, beating thoroughly.

title: grandma's matzoh ball soup
directions: Place two quarts of water in a pot. Add chicken, celery, carrots, onions, leek, salt, pepper and small bunch of dill. Let cook on medium until chicken is tender.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, flour, milk, butter and vanilla.
Beat and mix well.
Pour over coconut that has been put in pie crust.
Bake at 325° to 350° until lightly brown and set.

title: oven fries
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 2 baking sheets with spray. Combine potatoes, vegetable oil, pepper and rosemary.
Place on sheets.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until brown. Add salt, if desired.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Drain carrots and spread in bottom of casserole dish.
Saute the onions and 1/2 stick of margarine or cook 2 minutes in microwave.
Mix the sauteed onions, soup and cheese and spread over carrots.
Melt the other 1/2 stick of margarine and mix with stuffing.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake until bubbly, 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Layer this in 2 layers. Sprinkle saltine cracker crumbs on top and dot with 4 tablespoons of margarine. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix together sugar, mayonnaise and cocoa.
Mix in flour and soda.
Add water and vanilla.
Bake in greased 8-inch pans until done, about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: french toast casserole
directions: Spray 9 x 13 inch pan with Pam.
Put bread cubes in; arrange cream cheese around top.
Whip eggs and add milk and maple syrup. Pour over bread cream cheese mixture. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serve with pitcher of additional syrup.

title: quick quiche
directions: Saute bacon until crispy.
Drain and reserve 1 teaspoon bacon fat to saute the diced onion in until transparent.
In blender jar, mix eggs on highest speed until fluffy.
Add half and half and blend until frothy.
In pie crust, layer onion, half of the crumbled bacon, cheese, egg mixture and remaining bacon.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour or until almost set.
Quiche will thicken more as it cools.
Can be used for an appetizer, brunch or a light lunch.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix together flour or cake mix, nuts and butter. Spread over bottom of baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool. Mix sugar, cream cheese, cool whip.
Spread over layer.
Mix chocolate mix and milk until thick.
Spread over second layer. Spread cool whip over third layer and sprinkle with slivers of chocolate candy.

title: ritzy broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli in salted water for 5 minutes and drain well.
Combine soup, eggs, mayonnaise and diced cheese.
Mix well.
Add drained broccoli and pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle with Ritz crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
This may also be fixed and frozen until time to bake.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli in water and bouillon cubes.
Do not drain. Into blender pour milk, cheese and flour.
Process 30 to 45 seconds.
Add this mixture to broccoli, then pour in half and half.
Stir over medium heat until thickens.

title: ground beef dinner
directions: Prepare cheese dinner according to the direction on the package.
Brown ground beef, onions and pepper.
Drain and add tomatoes.
Lay 1/2 the cheese dinner on bottom of dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Layer 1/2 of beef mixture on top of this. Repeat layers.
Spoon soup over the top of the mixture. Sprinkle cheese on top if desired.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until soup bubbles.

title: mexican bean soup
directions: Dump in pot and heat about 30 minutes. Top with shredded cheese and fritos.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Melt margarine in skillet; add celery and carrots.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add all the rest of ingredients.
Cover and simmer until tender but yet crisp, about 8 or 10 minutes.

title: sour cream spice cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add egg yolks.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with sour cream to the egg mixture, beating after each addition.
Last, add stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.
May be iced with powdered sugar or cooked icing.
Also delicious split using Date and Nut Filling between layers with plain icing on top.

title: pear preserves
directions: Pare fruit (if hard, cook until tender in water). Make syrup of liquid and sugar.
Add fruit to partly cooled syrup and bring gently to boil. Add lemon, if desired. Boil rapidly until clear and tender. Cool rapidly.
Let stand in syrup to plump. Pack fruit into sterilized jars and add reheated syrup to within 1/2-inch of top.
Seal immediately.

title: braunschweiger ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except 3 ounces cream cheese. Form into a ball.
Frost with 3 ounces cream cheese (a sprinkle of milk may be needed to soften to spread easier).

title: shiitake spread
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter for about 5 minutes.
Add garlic and saute another minute or two.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: "caesar salad"
directions: Break lettuce into salad bowl; sprinkle with salt and plenty of freshly ground pepper.
Crush garlic and add to olive oil.
Pour over greens and toss well until each piece is well coated with the oil.
Then, break in the 1 minute cooked egg.
Squeeze in juice of 1/2 lemon, add anchovies (cut into small pieces).
Add Parmesan cheese and croutons.
Toss and serve.

title: 24 hour pickles(1 gallon pickles)
directions: Boil water, vinegar and canning salt.
Pour over cucumbers and let stand for 24 hours.
Put in refrigerator.

title: golden apricot cake
directions: Mix cake mix, nectar, oil, honey, eggs and apricot preserves with mixer until well blended.
Pour into greased and sprayed Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
After cake has cooled and has been removed from pan, frost with a mixture of the cream cheese, oleo and powdered sugar.

title: pear bread pudding(with caramel cream sauce)
directions: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Puree the undrained pears in the food processor. Combine puree with enough milk to make 4 cups liquid. Combine bread with pear puree mixture. Mix well. Beat together the sugar, brown sugar, eggs, and vanilla extract. Combine with bread mixture. Melt the butter in 9x13x2 inch baking pan. Pour bread pudding mixture into pan and bake for about an hour. Serve with Caramel Cream Sauce.
